REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(688,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n\n[@kor](@uqFI3UmCNGNcG8+25YGYN651jBtb7H7WxNmoHtaNYSY=.ed25519) [shared this picture](%n71p2AVZTsRyqYDe/zT+aYznUm+8EB2dNDPtAadvkNo=.sha256) of [@dominic](@EMovhfIrFk4NihAKnRNhrfRaqIhBv1Wj8pTxJNgvCCY=.ed25519) at the Kiwiriki Bay\n\n![Dominic looks out across a wide green landscape of small mountains and countless trees](&mE5qQ36KhhbgcsqZ3NiSSAJKW40vqT07nUtGYojJwac=.sha256)\n\nand then [this picture](%qeJ23hgujjmFVzE8ciAYilH9j0YsGr0UeOaaCC1EvWM=.sha256) of [@dangerousbeans](@TXKFQehlyoSn8UJAIVP/k2BjFINC591MlBC2e2d24mA=.ed25519) \n\n\n![dangerous beans standing in a small rowboat in a bay backlit by lat day ambient light](&WtT9RRGyq1KKU4ukxPLtmzgIqFm72W23seyU/Qr8mM8=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@nicolas](@nkOzrek79j6ilIk0TYmPMsAfqTiF/PhvwYX9btjQru4=.ed25519) shared this lovely [pinhole camera landscape](%qanr+dBI/hOa0FDI0YXw9vbKKoHk/6mMV+I5n6D9YeQ=.sha256). \n\n![black and white landscape photo with a river, winding between mountains - taken with a pinhole camera](&0ThMld/w1DnHS87iBKMQ8tIne8B8AoNbYjJfIJkr59w=.sha256)\n\nCheck out their feed for many more pretty pictures.\n\n----\n\n[@platteneule](@2knKcpGIimcEYkK4OdzOX3wGImtRbDsQl9U2uitCm50=.ed25519) shared this nice scene from Tokyo Japan.\n\n![many children playing with orange baloons in the middle of a street in Ginza in Tokyo Japan. Their parents walk nearby unconcerned.](&Hrv6CQWC+sop+unFKjG+NxsKT8DPOitwKhqASJAj8uM=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@happy0](@RJ09Kfs3neEZPrbpbWVDxkN92x9moe3aPusOMOc4S2I=.ed25519) shared a story of just [how effective and immersive VR Headsets can be](%bQdJGLvmr8mi1XH9T4/jIkeVM8YwVTzrGsOjCUGKH5M=.sha256). _Knowing_  that what you''re seeing isn''t real doesn''t seem to be enough to overcome years of training that you must believe your eyes to survive. This is great news for the future of immersive video games, therapy tools, and more.\n\n----\n[@Lando](@cnLKkzXHWFfPa2c4N74pMKCpw6Gmp1vnydEF4qlZsTE=.ed25519) shared his "first myco-fabrication" \n\n![a mold made of yellow cardboard and plastic wrap held together by tape. Its curved on one side and zig zag on the other and roughly 10cm tall. Filled with mostly white mycelium with spots of brown sawdust still showing. All on a white background](&N/MBF5WrUDV3bbzNB/3zJX2/YS+d9UJ9ac1Co4xnlFI=.sha256)\n\n----\npost 1 of 5\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(695,replace('[@hoodownr](@YND2Cb9uk3ZdFyzXpaXDH5HZ9udu+qjg4MhNcynK2RE=.ed25519) shared this nice minimal line drawing from their Inktober. \n\n\n![line drawing of a person laying on a table in a hospital room](&3gnRsmGFp2l9egB5yZNBTe+QPSDrEE/qFKiWFG9QoOE=.sha256)\n\nOctober provided us with a lot of great Inktober submissions. I''d especially recommend you check out what [@Gaffen](@zdpL3pz44do6ZK5V9wzuzrponmGlgcVyY7TEYVvkVeE=.ed25519) has been uploading. Lots of great little pieces like this one:\n\n![Inktober Day 24: Dizzy. An improvised temple sculpture based loosely on Aztec portrayals of Quetzalcoatl with spirals in its eyes](&DSLPH0kXYlzmhoH8yYfJ4MH4VQI8nmGJ41EIuiOsbtc=.sha256)\n\n\nThey put together a collage of the full set [here](%7FCJhR0Kk6IzOnbjww3JHqi787hgduLz0fVPnv8KCuM=.sha256), but As you can see from the one above, there''s a lot of detail lost when they''re shrunk down. Go find the "originals". \n\n![A collage of all Gaffen''s inktober entries for 2019](&5ZMygBjGc6bWtklbfhu1q8l6eE+5UnTW6YdauHWOi7g=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n\n[@Aadil Ayub](@y0P7anmcS+TqwiFGlONhFNadXNb9agEAWVRPRk9ed+0=.ed25519) shared this quote from _Permanent Record_ by Edward Snowden:\n\n> How can I explain it, to someone who wasnt there? My younger readers, with their younger standards, might think of the nascent Internet as way too slow, the nascent Web as too ugly and un-entertaining. But that would be wrong. Back then, being online was another life, considered by most to be separate and distinct from Real Life. The virtual and the actual had not yet merged. And it was up to each individual user to determine for themselves where one ended and the other began. \n\n> It was precisely this that was so inspiring: the freedom to imagine something entirely new, the freedom to start over. Whatever Web 1.0 mightve lacked in user-friendliness and design sensibility, it more than made up for by its fostering of experimentation and originality of expression.\n\n[and commented](%Q7GBYuLBoFeloX5JN6FlDmRUXOkbeGluBKvou+9FMkQ=.sha256)\n\n> I think this explains what it is that I love so much about #scuttlebutt, the #fediverse, and #dweb in general.\n\nI couldn''t agree more. I was doing web dev for people back in 1995. The distributed web and Fediverse are _very_ reminiscent of what the internet looked like without corporate overlords shoving everything into walled gardens. The tooling is just more mature and less DIY. \n\nI can''t wait for the eventual implosion of Facebook and Twitter. I''m just hoping that the Distributed Web and Fediverse is ready to fill the void when that happens.\n\nWe''re getting there with great tools like [Mastodon](https://mastodon.social/about) & [Pleroma](https://pleroma.social/) and [Pixelfed](https://pixelfed.org/). The distributed web feels, to me, like we''re getting close. I love SSB (obviously) but onboarding is still a pain, and while we''ve talked a lot about how to handle potential abuse, we''ve still got a lot of code to implement before. we can actually do it. We _could_ be the replacement for Facebook, but right now none of the distributed offerings feel mature enough. \n\n----\n\n[@Matt McKegg](@FbGoHeEcePDG3Evemrc+hm+S77cXKf8BRQgkYinJggg=.ed25519) started [vlogging about their music rig](%RJn+WJB4faSmIhF7xESsfKEqHEQLuuv7SBTWqOG4i5M=.sha256). \n\n![matt looks into the camera while sitting at a desk covered with digital music equipment](&7Vc6imrzz12sNkSA3zcl2RkzQGc0G/jl71SfTlsGEtI=.sha256)\n\n----\n\npost 2 of 5\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(701,replace('[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519) took [the gridbeam idea](%pj8206oQXl5WgqE3VioOaTqvlqWQOzhj3foz5atEMXc=.sha256) and built [jankdesk 1.0](%xnXIygTWuCRLgbx9fx0O3A6KW4iTRDjwEiAtoq3R79I=.sha256)\n\n> Ive been using a cardboard box as a standing desk adapter for a few months and it was starting to get very annoying to use. I saw @mikeys post about Grid Beam and decided to give it a shot. \n\n![Photo of jankdesk, a rectangular prism made of 2x2 with a think sheet of thin particle board on top.](&D7AzC6itV6NR3NTwD50JAWmpW0bXMjtRy2q0GaEPIaM=.sha256)\n\nClick through to see it in action with his snazzy keyboard and monitor on it.\n\n----\n[@Robs Laptop](@2iygl66Z/2VJXZQsT0CGwEbh/X/01QavSYQydsvuqvg=.ed25519) [discovered and shared](%ormjaFQBvzCJwfeaqgUYxLmGw/fGRCk9VYhUfufS7fY=.sha256) a bit about New Zealand''s "...housetrucking movement, which is a cross between van dwelling and tiny homes." Basically, tiny homes on the backs of powerful trucks.\n\n----\n[@SoapDog](@gaQw6z30GpfsW9k8V5ED4pHrg8zmrqku24zTSAINhRg=.ed25519) had [an encounter with a ghost](%Y9cVhTK7sK+jnfNpfxYvF0pTjVUsBPLe3FiHF4o6vN8=.sha256) in the British Library. \n\nShortly after they proposed "[a low-key, informal, crab-meet](%OY2Tn9eYTf1BXZqsQ+mQZhkTNf8z3CjKoRtYgGjnnac=.sha256)". \n\nDid this encounter with the afterlife lead to a desire to connect with the living? You''ll have to show up to find out.\n\n----\n[@polylith](@0nakXtVIodBfdHwRQLVb64p54jTWS+DFHRqg58ky4CI=.ed25519)''s [latest newsletter](%Mi91R5QVXqwhgjB8VmRbbk9Swp6/T2B63DSwOMr4fG0=.sha256) has been released. This one''s entitled "Drift gestures" \n\n----\n\n[@epk](@mfY4X9Gob0w2oVfFv+CpX56PfL0GZ2RNQkc51SJlMvc=.ed25519) may have just coined the term "Butt Life" in this [random slice-of-life post](%OlMNASXjq5ADeZgbKtJzfVHBINRNUOgVrykaOBAqoxI=.sha256) of theirs.\n\nI think we need "Butt Life" stickers now. Just not sure what image should go with the text.\n\n\n## Solarpunk\n[@kira](@C3iYh/12sO1uvKq1KcZXLFxSySzxOkHxXN8rtNB5MGA=.ed25519) converted [a presentation by Everest Pipkin](%4QIVN/pbkuSzwKO/+yBdITlNf5cZc5HUszkVRbiJ+fk=.sha256) to PDF and threw it up on DAT for us.\n\nThe opening slide is:\n\n>  Plant buddies you can find and eat in most American cities as well as many other places where domestic plants have rewilded.\n\n\n![a presentation slide with details about wild onions](&572S0vlY/CtclVt+6jZHLj2wcc1bPyDqaONO0t6pDWw=.sha256)\n\n## Community\n\n[@Aljoscha](@zurF8X68ArfRM71dF3mKh36W0xDM8QmOnAS5bYOq8hA=.ed25519) shared [an update on the February gathering of scuttlefriends in Basel Switzerland](%hUE4MrU7xTNi63VATOcEunXviOnv83LbIynYd6i4dw8=.sha256).\n\n\n----\n\n[@Emmi Bevensee](@5fX6QTmue/udf7tLwW25vQ63wZSENrksghBt6vfL4/I=.ed25519) shared...\n\n> Im working with a group of awesome devs to create easy to use (point and click) [data analysis tools for a variety of platforms with the goal of exposing hate and disinformation networks](%pd7NyvLFoDRE0hQ9IopQR4Iw81jBepmp+NwPHBHl4lg=.sha256). \n\nIf you''re interested in such projects, drop them a line.\n\n\npost 3 of 5\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(714,replace('## Software \n\n[@andrestaltz](@QlCTpvY7p9ty2yOFrv1WU1AE88aoQc4Y7wYal7PFc+w=.ed25519) has [released a new version of Manyverse](%TDhAyEHAz4AxabiRl9oxJ8JR6LiWKrYvQNvL8NGbrvQ=.sha256) with Backup and Restore! ... and other improvements. ;)\n\n![manyverse screenshot with a dialog indicating that an identity has been restored](&8wynlI9ed5KUm4kRevvbWe9G8R5NyhkjZUxkxXEwmHg=.sha256)\n\nThey also [discussed Resisting recency, and zoomable UIs](%UgxCCh+wKDENFVXWuvMJrh81AtFHyawEb998Ca9HtNU=.sha256)\n\n> I think one of the drivers of burnout within SSB and other social spaces is the focus that the Feed puts on a linear timeline where recent content is king. Sorting a timeline of content by recency, and recency only, is useful but it puts emphasis on  well  recency! It makes a lot of sense for Twitter which is a space you enter to take a sample of whats going on at the moment. It makes less sense for social circles like Facebook and Instagram, except if youre gossip/rumor oriented, which is/was Facebooks emphasis. Overall lists of posts are attractive because scrolling is a simple mindless activity that even monkeys and babies can perform. SSB apps, Manyverse included, follow the recency tradition because its familiar and the default.\n\nMuch more in the post. I think he''s on to something important. Displaying content has just been "the way" for so many years that we take it for granted that it is the "right" way. Personally I think it''s an interaction mechanism from a time with less data. You went to someone''s blog and it was just _their_ posts you saw sorted recently. You weren''t looking at the feed of recent posts from _everyone_ you found interesting on a particular platform. Despite multiple prunings, I still follow _hundreds_ of people on Twitter. Because of the way data is presented I am regularly forced to skip large swaths of it because I simply can''t read it all. \n\n----\nSpeaking of backups, [@SoapDog](@gaQw6z30GpfsW9k8V5ED4pHrg8zmrqku24zTSAINhRg=.ed25519) released an early beta of [ssb-backup-tool](%8uA4R1XBJCw7hVQ+Nd21p5wfWLrDw2ZFP/1oYUWP0Yg=.sha256).\n\n----\n[@Rabble](@THUzexG1y6kWofwiN8Lix/jNH/P6roYdlCDgpAn2HSc=.ed25519) noted that Planetary (the iOS SSB client) has moved to TestFlight distribution. Speaking as a beta tester that''s a huge step forward. They''re also working on displaying local and remote peers in the UI. \n\nIn other words, [gradual progress continues to be made](%I/I5GcW48qtCYCdF8tViB2kT3DXzvGBISh8mAdaDRFY=.sha256).\n\n![screenshot of planetary showing connected peers](&yCuYRN5wcex4utDc8nyYKuoRdP9hvfHv33Y42nnNkEI=.sha256)\n\n\n\n----\n[@mix](@ye+QM09iPcDJD6YvQYjoQc7sLF/IFhmNbEqgdzQo3lQ=.ed25519) shared a post (and PDF) discussing some recent work about [trying to figure out who gets to see what information in a tree of human connections and relationships](%vnDRm8VqPIU4iWM2L35i3B4GwWZdSHc5AQ/G/cyNpGo=.sha256).\n\n![example of a whakapapa tree](&L9T8Cdsp1d1zicXjRMKEm0Q+ZJrOSfHoEtjDuz6QFNg=.sha256)\n\n\n\n----\n\npost 4 of 5\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(722,replace('[@duncan](@Wbmkx0zKN/zFC1Li7Mz3IEQlcnHT7gAQ38i3hRCqyp4=.ed25519) says \n\n> Im starting work on a new project. The goal is to improve Scuttlebutts documentation for people who wish to build things upon Scuttlebutt. [I want to make these situations better](%z4bA3ix77rovI+FZOjMG8j1bgpGdJQ1lLabMjmcPTgU=.sha256):\n\n> * I have an idea for something I want to build with Scuttlebutt but no idea where to begin\n> * Is this code I found currently being used, experimental or old and not used anymore?\n> * Where on earth is the code responsible for this part of Scuttlebutt?\n> * How do I change this existing Scuttlebutt client to do what I want?\n\nClick through to learn more.\n\n\n----\n[@Daan](@MRiJ+CvDnD9ZjqunY1oy6tsk0IdbMDC4Q3tTC8riS3s=.ed25519) shared [a quick anecdote](%GONsWGXmUxtTpo/JQbFyuGHiUOlo12ngj266a40fyGA=.sha256) about why offline-first software design is so important. \n\n----\n[@switch](@9OFBA15mnlpqRfjzL8idyOvKj3UbQCA96GOLk4AjmxE=.ed25519) shares a twitter thread and some comments about how [Apple''s new "notarization" policy screws indie, and poor, developers](%PBYdGLMriWWO1/xk97cI0MPsQkFzNCpIT89X+AYTFjM=.sha256) by forcing them to pay to make their software to run on macOS without additional steps on macOS. \n\n## Geeky\n[@keks](@YXkE3TikkY4GFMX3lzXUllRkNTbj5E+604AkaO1xbz8=.ed25519) shared a use case for potentially making a new SSB message type: sharing your public key. [Click through](%Iy3qGmRgGVdoHtc6PmHgtWWdr6/w8Y2AZ5IH8C75bb8=.sha256) to hear their thinking and leave some feedback.\n\n\n----\n[@cft](@AiBJDta+4boyh2USNGwIagH/wKjeruTcDX2Aj1r/haM=.ed25519) shared some [research they''d done](%XNMwjzb/tKiTDyfeDDDNOAV9UQpNxm+f/ZwYO9qonN0=.sha256) about tangles and extending the pub/sub concept throughout the software stack. \n\n![pub / sub structured software stack](&1ZrChMe8zWibkdXpm5z0CW1d/zTQ6Oc1LDh0U6F2qgk=.sha256)\n\nThere''s much more in the post including a chess, and chat proof of concept.\n\n![video:demo-chat.mp4](&bPVbCyCOHXa1rWmhbV6bZl31+rnBvB2nwS4HzC1TwvQ=.sha256)\n\n\n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis summary was curated from 428 threads by 161 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\nAnd, as noted before. Thank you for your patience over the upcoming weeks while I take care of my wife. Posts will continue, they''ll just be somewhat erratic in their scheduling. \n\npost 5 of 5\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(730,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n[@Joey Hess](@BCM6DHYJvWzwWi1lFl2tjDXjaqyZAEmJH5ZONSpXhtc=.ed25519) shared [2" of their New England snow](%GMIHmBoVUDzBNx4TVjiixtTnuBfmaY9Y4pm4wcJjYR0=.sha256) with us. \n\n![2 inches of snow in new england in november](&Ne8wd2xeW+VjbxfbpMVpPFTbIeCcTZRGXSwUsAn+VM0=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Hendrik Peter](@Bp5Z5TQKv6E/Y+QZn/3LiDWMPi63EP8MHsXZ4tiIb2w=.ed25519) is [sharing pics from their new Mavic Pro on Unsplash](%atMKuMZGY3azeA8QqIBks60GR3PY6igawE7EJMBvzLI=.sha256). \n\n![an aerial view of a sweedish house surrounded by tall and thin green trees](&HVpUduPL2CXDVB1NMnt5g/gTjea0vlIk6pzVucnl/DA=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@platteneule](@2knKcpGIimcEYkK4OdzOX3wGImtRbDsQl9U2uitCm50=.ed25519) shared a picture of [Mount Fuji and the moon](%atvTkhBDCRs3inQ5TuTB8ihB0Y4X9WXyQbuDHheKcCE=.sha256). \n\n![mount fuji and a crescent moon](&FOZh/g8PGnLNF/6KzK1UKfj+cnwSPdvgMiA0jFfuBJE=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@nicolas](@nkOzrek79j6ilIk0TYmPMsAfqTiF/PhvwYX9btjQru4=.ed25519) shared another [pinhole camera picture](%5d9Pu2CjF2MCd80N9L77ULrQPAIK7OuyteUzcHTw5Wo=.sha256).\n\n![black and white photo of desert landscape with significant water erosion](&pXC728BsooBYW5A/6bwe4crOp9k9mbXDjeydqwpRhrA=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Richard D. Bartlett](@3r4+IyB5NVl2in6QOZHIu9oSrZud+NuVgl2GX3x2WG8=.ed25519) shares some crafting they''ve been doing lately.\n\n![airship model zeppelin](&d44g177MOf6OyNu2QYcfaD5ed6Ss73R+lbj+qAfNp8Y=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@Rabble](@THUzexG1y6kWofwiN8Lix/jNH/P6roYdlCDgpAn2HSc=.ed25519) started making their own Seitan and [took us along for the ride](%92NeroBFcg52AcgZGyZfg2ADwdBR+HzlEuywwVseKP4=.sha256).\n\n![a bag of Anthony''s Premium vital wheat gluton and an empty bowl on a crowded counter in preparation of making seitan](&vmpShrfeNlTimBWLPZOyJI0gA52x7b7Mm3CNWYQlS6s=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@emile](@2YVYXQclEJHVzCON5dsLRwf65b2S6HnvxpGS8/LwjwY=.ed25519) [opened up their recently deceased GPS](%HytD0mCqvSxpJOrACC6NYD7OyacyCbS45L7a75ibzWU=.sha256) to see what was inside and shared some thoughts on what they found. \n\n![gps antenna](&nzphHhjVUc91K0UNRvX2n3qYFVRqPBf/WK4pk4MvqmU=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@dangerousbeans](@TXKFQehlyoSn8UJAIVP/k2BjFINC591MlBC2e2d24mA=.ed25519) notes that "[@Alchemist](@na1AJv1iWOflQOwsQ4srJJhYynkYawXiWDwM0ln4DgY=.ed25519) is slowly becoming functional." and is starting to [wonder if she can be put to use being useful](%FY1aDiWNlf/vZoin9l7eBikHqNmxSETofo8fDOgr18I=.sha256), as something more than just a pleasurabley thing to spend time on.\n\nAs an aside, they note that Alchemist [now has a solar powered microwave](%EUJc1W7gfn6PxK7wEBSYOSrmeAVuiiK6WJdaIctYamw=.sha256).\n\nand an "[actually clean room](%GkkdFIkD7DSPBwcALQr3yeBFte791HNetB4S3mfhYOA=.sha256)"\n\n![bathroom walls and skylight in alchemist](&WtZn57w8tclepN9kUcONNRKbnP7qCtn1DNJkrxf78gg=.sha256)\n\n\nand [a beautiful view](%j5pqFj18DVCt8B5KUt6wHAfX3bhVEHj3kZKrdfIqxm0=.sha256)\n\n![a colorful sunset seen through the windows of Alchemist](&WcEkQL1W6lxmnLcfO4sURm8yXJ0mJ6+BfVbg7Bq4X2k=.sha256)\n\n\npost 1 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(743,replace('## Community\n[@andrestaltz](@QlCTpvY7p9ty2yOFrv1WU1AE88aoQc4Y7wYal7PFc+w=.ed25519) notes that [SSB has a Wikipedia page now](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secure_Scuttlebutt) :link:\n\nTheir [post is here](%0sGApWhdDK/9NsLkQKG9M4zawZRuiH9zeGSdWUtv7WQ=.sha256).\n\n----\n[@hng](@ySXxRNhuEQj8oUNqDuUNF2stKE4t0BwnWPOjnPGm6ck=.ed25519) notes that [ssb is about to be featured on the Apen podcast](https://medium.com/apen%C3%A3) (Portugese language).\n\n## Software\n[@mnin](@SXVoA/7CuMRS5IDTNsO8HU2PvCIVq8HKUUx/k+idDiQ=.ed25519)''s work has come to fruition and the new Scuttlebutt web site is live. [Check out their post](%ATssjMsgJeymt91dHJZ7gypdlCiCh9IIxZGa9F3J0O0=.sha256) for lots of details.\n\n![screenshot of scuttlebutt.nz](&61H0VtbG4O+AO639E0PgLjOvrjLn2CsG9ysEoUvGYQw=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519) made [a CLI client for Scuttlebutt](%7p73Zaxq/UnCbqVsIgTNPBhpWD4pUYPLe8rnprfkJUo=.sha256).\n\n> Its still under development (and its unearthed a handful of problems in the stack) but Id love thoughts and feedback.\n\n\n----\n[@ Navigator](@z2M8msI2EUubNHnrEJncglDIy2/SUd+36jCyJnfeiHk=.ed25519) has [figured out how to blog on the web via SSB](%1fVaxOurkNIGrphWeXM0h7EYxD6dmvYgxNYbf1+Kci8=.sha256).\n\nThe tldr; seem to be it reads your feed, copies images to a local folder, and runs it thrnough a static site generator. They''ve shared the ruby script that does it too. Cool. \n\n----\n[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519) has released v2.7.0 of Oasis a "Friendly Scuttlebutt interface designed for simplicity and accessibility." Details [in their post](%kb/f/i0pKWlqeQH6uFfOqGAhIaHfusrLFcZWtpBTHCg=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@SoapDog](@gaQw6z30GpfsW9k8V5ED4pHrg8zmrqku24zTSAINhRg=.ed25519) demonstrated how [Patchfox''s sidebar can let you reference other posts](%w5brS4h+1x5OFw7nsrDmD6zXiyWn93F99ND9hPXUh68=.sha256) while creating a new one.\n\n![video:quotes.mp4](&4lS1hQs6SOM86j5q30aQpJhhzV2dB4GQ7YnG1E88vRg=.sha256)\n\n## Geeky\n\n[@keks](@YXkE3TikkY4GFMX3lzXUllRkNTbj5E+604AkaO1xbz8=.ed25519) shared [the minutes from a call](%ho/e1MyrtwpfJiYm5DmlkGiAxe7rOAk5tr2MYC5oYR8=.sha256) with [@Dominic](@EMovhfIrFk4NihAKnRNhrfRaqIhBv1Wj8pTxJNgvCCY=.ed25519) and [@mix](@ye+QM09iPcDJD6YvQYjoQc7sLF/IFhmNbEqgdzQo3lQ=.ed25519) about the new private groups feature.\n\n[This later post](%1qQJ2szfWa/PerVSVPLlwpl8SlyhGsorrwp6jLW+zfA=.sha256) discusses "...use cases where we need to reference a group in a public message, but dont want to leak who created the message." and shares a couple thoughts on that matter\n\nThey "... also we realized that [it would be helpful if a message could be referencing itself](%CD1C8SgKYmghPOpq5tI3nQmGKTewxqBXJCG0bxZyA8A=.sha256)."\n\npost 2 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(754,replace('[@mix](@ye+QM09iPcDJD6YvQYjoQc7sLF/IFhmNbEqgdzQo3lQ=.ed25519) realized they didn''t know [how to decript a private message on SSB](%RouG6IVwpEQhfYLpyFkjyJrj9uhR6GlQDH+4Ngt/6Bg=.sha2569), and then spent some time figuring it out and writing down the details for us.\n\n----\n[@adria0](@ZFWw+UclcUgYi081/C8lhgH+KQ9s7YJRoOYGnzxW/JQ=.ed25519) got ssb `whoami` [working in Rust](%mcs2pQ+uDph77Qsn2O/lTvNeqFAnZfsuYZXX8mmKnRk=.sha256) and shared the source code.\n\n----\n[@corlock](@sHFNLAao6phQ5AN17ecYNUbszDa4Qf6DhyQsjtQfdmY=.ed25519) discovered that there''s no verification of "local" SSB users and thus [you can fake them](%itxbdOh3sCW1YLIDCWzA7UlssaAWXNRi9Jf8ZxebTXY=.sha256).\n\n> Today I made a quick program that simulates the peer-discovery component of the SSB protcol.. and I realized that theres actually no verification that happens before showing users in Local section of your sidebar. This means, its pretty trivial to send a message that makes all SSB users on the local network think that dominic is in the building.\n\nI''m not sure what nefarious purposes you could put this to but I''m pretty sure there are some. \n\n\n----\n[@micro](@wsoeSOhEE3yAIEF1gTVMeStUWnoejIz1P6a3lnvjaOM=.ed25519) shared their [Lua Wireshark scuttlebutt discovery packet dissector](%W4cHMXizTTN/9M9kVcI4/jKhNTV3eitpIl5fCpoGcE4=.sha256).\n\n![screenshot of wireshark ssb packet disection](&2YDIhBDaUoSXpWjI/DOoI+LyW7CXjF6q5yHKUagOal0=.sha256)\n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data \n\nThis weeks summary was curated from 506 threads by 182 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\npost 3 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(760,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n## A note from your curator\nThank you all for your patience and understanding. I think I''m finally able to pick this work back up on a regular basis. This post is going to include a number of "old" posts, because there''s almost a month of stuff to catch everyone up on. \n\nI look forward to joining you more regularly. :) I was a way too long.\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n\n[@platteneule](@2knKcpGIimcEYkK4OdzOX3wGImtRbDsQl9U2uitCm50=.ed25519) [shared a "mix tape"](%ya48fuYN+COZhlreKJe02V3zdFU2WHcAJGS4lJN2O1I=.sha256) that encodes "...the heat of the japanese mid-summer until the golden autumn hits the greater area of Mount Fuji..."\n\n\n![kevineulenbergmixssb.jpg](&0Pk5ecBHYf1O0AUa04q4U8k1/BKKw99ZDxYInYmwiL0=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@MKs BIG MACHINE](@TJ9ZGr9vVDZ3F2+cm4KpS7HYAjrwq1O+ZOYd5dm7O50=.ed25519) [shared a photo](%DvGKxS6bY/ebsBh32QUAKqYcICGWWmcSL5ZW8QP8JS0=.sha256) by [@kira](@C3iYh/12sO1uvKq1KcZXLFxSySzxOkHxXN8rtNB5MGA=.ed25519)\n\n![beautiful plant stem stalk photo.jpg](&RQQOxcxVn/N1mZ9bdjYwCO3hLPTxQGRPVXSIrVgT6/s=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n\n[@emile](@2YVYXQclEJHVzCON5dsLRwf65b2S6HnvxpGS8/LwjwY=.ed25519) shared some [photos from a Danish island](%Xh3q5v+Dm6JL3CXVfG1XCusMnnWxiNpHMriWKIpE6RY=.sha256). \n\n![beach weeds](&BFUuO3mYruEqd6SzlfT3oQuCs6bmMzBkexgSv+8ztCM=.sha256)\n\n![bornholm forest](&VIJFuz1/VdOAbt4YIYMrvgIvbfQ/HWUr7IzjRuR5oVg=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@glyph](@HEqy940T6uB+T+d9Jaa58aNfRzLx9eRWqkZljBmnkmk=.ed25519) asks us to [show them your neighborhood creatures](%PYnjoUzzlGaeYszWJkbj04pJUAsaLMFhsHacVLiMuHM=.sha256) and shares this picture of a turtle that lives near them.\n\n\n![Colour photograph of an angulate tortoise amongst leaf-litter and sticks. The geometrically-patterned tortoise is nestled against a red-brick wall.](&8PK9VUzDV0Y65bOmM/PQTGUO/cnQm+sC7hFKjrtX5ws=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Luandro](@2RNGJafZtMHzd76gyvqH6EJiK7kBnXeak5mBWzoO/iU=.ed25519) started exploring [the mushrooms around their house](%f8CZsB59PgZHb40wC5+b88X+wmqfkPcnpu91h6r9MyI=.sha256) (many pictures).\n\n![mushrooms on the side of a dirt wall by a fallen log](&vRjGnKv2PPDVxqd99Q5vwLaPlGdwUMlG69HeeRn2eWk=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@seanb](@N/vWpVVdD1e8IbACUQE4EVGL6+aodQfbQZ8ByC+k79s=.ed25519) shared [some beautiful photos from their new home in Oregon USA](%RnLSvCWL4n2QEFq6+8NHUzZxUJMF7QROy7QB/Kd0xjc=.sha256).\n\n![a stream running through a forest with brown leaves on the ground and almost none on the trees](&qiqiIMHAtV7r8+ergSLGZQAAh1HEIULqkG+e4NcKlpU=.sha256)\n\n\n----\npost 1 of 4\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(769,replace('[@dangerousbeans](@TXKFQehlyoSn8UJAIVP/k2BjFINC591MlBC2e2d24mA=.ed25519) shares [the consequences of litigious societies and good advice](%Bg6xjk/PINFScmr4L8u6FfiKRJxuB+l5UH7wA32zMSg=.sha256) for those of us in wheelchairs. \n\n![a sign prohibiting wheelchairs in a park where wheelchairs could easily travel.](&FcdoLD9j4sGVA4YKNBuD6jEZrdpobVDvqAms0vxFRXw=.sha256)\n\nThey also [shared a photo](%fsAY4X4DSaR3VBev1XPV6l7Cvo5yaz97mVdfAQDvROs=.sha256) of a Kiwi and a man on a bench\n\n![a kiwi and man on a bench](&JErw6NKK4ozJddOviZ/vLp7WXl9Fc+UO9E39IzpUcpU=.sha256)\n\nand a story about [getting a new anchor chain](%4wrMMWTIBzFG6sAbfk8Gs+xm9Abto6r/GY+0uWAJ5CU=.sha256) for [@Alchemist](@na1AJv1iWOflQOwsQ4srJJhYynkYawXiWDwM0ln4DgY=.ed25519)\n\n![a dinghy floating with a lot of chain in it.](&q6qwgH8eysSpLjOH1cdNeEiPUCIsBMJFLo6lY/HwWD8=.sha256)\n\nand [a ginormous garlic](%WeifYrq++JdnixUMj968+MKBgNQwBYNp7O6I7BNJjeA=.sha256)!\n\n![GARLIC](&0FOT3iY7nPLtgGvHm3WrJ9CcYoHEwqgb4RtbcUOus74=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@andrestaltz_phone](@+UMKhpbzXAII+2/7ZlsgkJwIsxdfeFi36Z5Rk1gCfY0=.ed25519) shares some musical geekery about [their LinnStrument](%25p20vLjFfqQdrqaQgjeMKAsC/LmsnqJchDomI7/Jqc=.sha256)\n\n![LinnStrument, two fingers playing an octave](&KJP7Iy9rEXF2OvmSvdm7sWDvg6p77KynJP82dnPDgcc=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@kira](@C3iYh/12sO1uvKq1KcZXLFxSySzxOkHxXN8rtNB5MGA=.ed25519) failed to go sailing but [had fun with boats none-the-less](%mLOEBaYvrDWFMP6/tKyOezDk9mFzvysyA3ls3RO+M7E=.sha256). \n\n![sailing1.jpg](&R6hQWK2/Xbl6pxfsdMJF3+lk8pp/BxXcBipj7pwnoUg=.sha256) \n\n----\n\n[@micro](@wsoeSOhEE3yAIEF1gTVMeStUWnoejIz1P6a3lnvjaOM=.ed25519) [overcame their fear, learned to ride a motorcyle, and shared photos from their adventures](%0k4mpxxZ5DbQ/8nkDFboDtvZmM+VvnM+oDNJ3j1bbg8=.sha256). \n\n![shot of desert sky and ground, with small cafe racer motorcycle in bottom right corner](&BYCxxGGwZkjpOcmGLon6U7S0NB/OigTUucc9Ywz2v0c=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@enkiv2](@Q6jeOaoJOdFq8/3oFaOYC6bKhaVCD3IIdpjG+7Fab2M=.ed25519) announced [the 2020 No Budget Film Content](%3J9kzgxcRwk+CB4yoSepZyA6AB+l7s3fnqG7QYqLdVA=.sha256). Feel like making something nifty with no budget? Check it out. The winner gets enough winnings to increase their next film''s budget by over 500%!\n\n\n----\n[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519)\nshared [a cat close-up](%Ju08xdFQrVgVtm7rTDGnNdMtzRmYP8nYtcR8TU7EhNw=.sha256). \n\n![Jerome staring into the camera with Christmas lights in the background](&6Z7C9saRG1SW6Remb8gyVX7VENSJezOQ+lCwr63jZUQ=.sha256)\n\n\n\n\n## Community\n\n[@mnin](@SXVoA/7CuMRS5IDTNsO8HU2PvCIVq8HKUUx/k+idDiQ=.ed25519) shared [notes from a call](%OlMJS9MjqLUBnanMvvyU33o1u5Y8VDbKw/56rKRKlbU=.sha256) about the SSB web site, what''s been going on, where we are with its maintenance, who can help, etc.\n\n> A bunch of us butts got together to reflect on a call on the whole process of building the scuttlebutt website thus so far. It was really nice to reconnect after some weeks and months between some of us chatting, and it was reaffirming to hear the lessons learnt and the challenges felt between us all.\n\n----\n[@dan hassan](@NeB4q4Hy9IiMxs5L08oevEhivxW+/aDu/s/0SkNayi0=.ed25519) [shared this guide](%0ZhseZF9VJVWGQ+MftxDJlBug8iaGYvR4FY/ykdoIwo=.sha256) for "What to do if you are witnessing Islamophobic harassment"\n\n![islamaphobic harassment guide.png](&/uetc3IdSSPZls+SFNaLyx3HzrGtvaHlasq2VEZeC30=.sha256)\n\npost 2 of 4\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(783,replace('[@Luandro](@2RNGJafZtMHzd76gyvqH6EJiK7kBnXeak5mBWzoO/iU=.ed25519) shared some gorgeous [pictures of Moinho](%9sXdlzAyjMPeUic/jmnr8RDM9735Yi+tgAxwC4RPn94=.sha256) where scuttlecamp 2 will be. \n\n![entrance to moinho](&f1fWSyO00hoPAt/31Z10/XhsXHvdky/7p7u646tLiYc=.sha256)\n\n\nOn a related note [@glyph](@HEqy940T6uB+T+d9Jaa58aNfRzLx9eRWqkZljBmnkmk=.ed25519) announced that [the Scuttlecamp 2 Web site is live](%kmedw9jxJy1IdGl6551DXOnQWuIAFD2yRm70PmUXmXM=.sha256). \n\n![Screenshot of the background of the Scuttlecamp 2 website. The image depicts a verdant landscape, with grass in the foreground, a mangaba tree (like a mix between an apple and mango) on the left and rolling green hills in the background. Three mangaba fruits can be seen laying in the grass beneath the tree. A robot traveller with backpack is walking away from the tree and appears on the far-right of the image. A blue sky and wispy white clouds complete the scene. White font, centred at the top of the image, reads Scuttlecamp 2. All artwork composing this image was created by the stupendously-delightful @angelica!](&dN1Od5aQ6C4JC7f6hrhsHOmJJLFK4ttlTSacg4vq9yc=.sha256)\n\n\n\n## Software\n[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519) has [released Oasis 2.8.0](%r9nMaZHNBQ5ysnIU5m/N3oUk37MLz+EFjnqKZW0EiEw=.sha256).\n\n> Im happy to announce the latest release of Oasis, the friendly scuttlebutt interface that works in your favorite web browser. There are a handful of small changes and fixes and such, but theres one change Im very excited about: popular posts.\n\n[Check out the web demo](https://oasis-demo.fraction.io/) to see what it''s like.\n\n\nThey also [asked for feedback on how posts should be shown by default](%8r9O7185djNXP2XHn2Rv6l9krmxos8iQu9IavDBA0UE=.sha256). \n\n----\n\n[@corlock](@sHFNLAao6phQ5AN17ecYNUbszDa4Qf6DhyQsjtQfdmY=.ed25519) shared a screenshot from [the project they''ve been working on](%F8Vyn73wTxdOM/xVn+9xa6r4ivR3+UzFu/szLeZ2Jrs=.sha256): scuttle-chat terminal based "Ephemeral chats over encrypted TCP streams for the Scuttleverse"\n\n\n![Screen Shot 20191209 at 1.50.12 PM.png](&QQfknolADwg2FafBRXEwvGhaDw2d1moU9U+TKaMQ36s=.sha256)\n\nIt''s written in rust. \n\n\n----\n\n[@mixmix](@ye+QM09iPcDJD6YvQYjoQc7sLF/IFhmNbEqgdzQo3lQ=.ed25519) [released whakapapa ora](%73IEAkfBlClyHZUx7LZiiRaGxcbEGPMBhefnQYzL2ao=.sha256) a couple months ago, and has been [iterating on it](%C9KCJDMcusW3WjlFsnXQtuzORALg2b/5v1oO/OKoJGk=.sha256) ever since.\n\nIt''s still early stages, and the documentation is limited, but you can use it to keep track of communities, \n\n![whakapapa ora - communities page](&OgJxwcP7fAGKrHkH8VZ6TBX6xtTGFN2Y8eK+2enL/e8=.sha256)\n\npeople\n\n![whakapapa ora - profile page](&Mkz62JFY62MjBOVANnFRU7aMYFny6xlvNrx9VvgQeaE=.sha256)\n\nand family trees\n\n![ahau mix whakapapa](&WpM49KwLhpg8MP0C2QQQFBR4QkseERWuT5l5jsqWzjw=.sha256)\n\nOf course, it all runs over SSB. \n\nThe [source code is here](https://gitlab.com/ahau/whakapapa-ora/) but requires a little familiarity with NPM and the command line to build and run. There are no packaged releases...yet.\n\npost 3 of 4\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(792,replace('[@SoapDog](@gaQw6z30GpfsW9k8V5ED4pHrg8zmrqku24zTSAINhRg=.ed25519) released [a Firefox plugin to remind you to come back to a web page](%AOOjNVXDRxTzO/INAK2JdyuUrVeS6QzgqyT219jXzdo=.sha256) at some date in the future. \n\n![remind me of the page firefox plugin animated screenshot](&TYqxmqrREAgwq7HwK+Ch2DW/6beoppr/6GKsUsBr0So=.sha256)\n\nClick through for details. \n\n\n## Geeky\n[@andrestaltz](@QlCTpvY7p9ty2yOFrv1WU1AE88aoQc4Y7wYal7PFc+w=.ed25519) shared [some sequence diagrams of how SSB "Rooms" work](%cqDk0dbcYc/n+zugT15qVUvnEkwXz+dkfjH/uZxVCWs=.sha256). \n\n\n----\n[@micro](@wsoeSOhEE3yAIEF1gTVMeStUWnoejIz1P6a3lnvjaOM=.ed25519) is \n\n> [Playing around with an idea to create scuttlebutt "gardens"](%Jm+/spO8D/08Uz18HwKb+p/mpkCZ3lTgOWpAgryO10c=.sha256) - an easier way to create and join networks by name. Trying to find ways to make it less intimidating for spawning communities that are not dev firehose content.\n\n![table of 3 name of scuttlebutt networks, and long string of random encoded keys to access those names](&vXp5lhbJRAk12QdmmFTDYzCZ7519IpGQ9PArGv84VHI=.sha256)\n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis weeks summary was curated from 1070 threads by 334 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\npost 4 of 4\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(798,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\nNote: I''m still catching up from my time away. This post has some temporal overlap with the last one. I still have a bit to go to catch up to the present day, but you just write so much good content...\n\n\n## Totally Random\n\n[@Chromodoris](@XY261NcgFjgLXVsnZbeIPGdA8h+6U4VNLErQjvHXDns=.ed25519) shared [some lovely pictures of the outside world](%fY0hzpu5BBnxfc8xTnIk09cktj/uixTLyC7NNHGA6Rw=.sha256).\n\n\n![a close-up of a tree with mushrooms growing on it](&tDDBC/d8gvLT6v2TtrFK/TAg5e3RvfrSDFbHTHEDJHE=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@Daan p20 ](@tUMwMvb+roaOJAyohpGUxgqYo4E7HfBlY0NkUzALqjY=.ed25519) shared [a couple outdoors shots and a book](%gwHC5k09PHLUKPPHsJPcd/tVyrjyEXKVc/7yx7CHqDs=.sha256). \n\n![the sun shining through a high layer of fog over a north hessian landscape](&dNb39aC6SqhuUHnxBa9RINa/dutGwQ3lzAYKn3DW9TE=.sha256)\n\n----\n\n[@emile](@2YVYXQclEJHVzCON5dsLRwf65b2S6HnvxpGS8/LwjwY=.ed25519)''s cat [helped with some Ham Radio contacts](%3rK6epGpy5/dEh0wvpWBK4vz/35AhuD/R+YGETVfel4=.sha256).\n\n\n![cat behind iMac and near a ham radio antenna](&n+OlkmGzVsHV/LrgYOggiLzIszEJv1l3q+XzE46YNVM=.sha256)\n\nThey also [shared a link](%QaX0gB1WsJ3caPoGpi78GfwJjNy2vOBhKWV8bmnWIbA=.sha256) to\n\n"[Mina and me - Toddling across the Norwegian mountains](https://youtu.be/6BEwdDgdOSU)"\n\nA ski tour of Alexander and Mina (age 4!) though the Norwegian snowfields.It''s an interesting looking 26 minute documentary. \n\n\n----\n\n[@Angelica](@eANNuLfzX/9rlGODXHYV8WJb+zw2h+d7YsT4vpYPvD0=.ed25519) found large versions of the Cynthia, Jackie, and Martin characters from the SSB Intro video [and shared them with us](%GNZ4bFJD6LHuGUYLa3eNhw7NulGczsKsvOomdmSgWCc=.sha256).\n\n![cynthia ssb user pic](&6z+EP6Esy8Ft6FsxViBmyUs4986J8oD8oxCoc44TCYI=.sha256)\n\n----\n\n[@sl007](@jX1pC2ZWcoOd0z8IrVxpBX7bpcPfV438t6jsvp3d9Po=.ed25519) joined us and [shared this photo](%y9wrM2McWsNB3T+v41Q8IQgz+6xSNQV9+OseDQpxfwY=.sha256), along with links to many more amazing ones from their time as a photojournalist. Hopefully more will be shared with us. \n\n![hands holding an ak47 machine gun overlooking a mountanous road](&QhEpwwB0e57mgbf/zhBL+DsNP/JwRD92jMnIdaieQHA=.sha256)\n\n[This batch](https://pluspora.com/posts/8f7603c03817013703de005056264835) and story that they linked to are from the Carteret islands which are [nearly lost to climate change](https://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-08-04/the-race-against-time-to-save-the-carteret-islanders/10066958).\n\n----\n[@Agustin Haro](@JMIbfsr2i/DRm+esw+bv0MkxsKuaXgc3rMAje4bhwwk=.ed25519) has a [new family member](%2MajD+/vTLR1I2COXcONuYOGnV19OXk2hD9YryOEh7U=.sha256)\n\n\n![oso the dog looks up](&kb3Vxp8oA2Xj2bt2VnbFnXVGK45UiIWLlKiyHNe6p+E=.sha256)\n\nThey also [shared links to the music they''ve created](%FHCMKNroU0QDjPQNce+tQTzsuIQ4CEtYhCrkETzZcZw=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Ryan](@YcULoiCt35mq9njrahmXFONqX/gGEVN1ffdMt20pzgE=.ed25519) also [got a new family member](%N0mZTPoiCrhKlBtBV7MiaQ4XZtLdQzZU8MB5+h/cHxs=.sha256)\n\n![Honey, an 8 week old golden retriever](&U1zHc0/7kp1dqOT7k2e3KQKpJZzFimaPNw2rhCFgCAE=.sha256)\n\n\n----\npost 1 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(810,replace('[@Aadil Ayub](@y0P7anmcS+TqwiFGlONhFNadXNb9agEAWVRPRk9ed+0=.ed25519) shared [a "p2p Mixtape" on DAT](%i3GFUiACyj7qWHHQxsZ/JFtNBTppyhhfbNDRoBZ0Yfo=.sha256) entitled "Ambient Flow". \n\n\n----\n[@polylith](@0nakXtVIodBfdHwRQLVb64p54jTWS+DFHRqg58ky4CI=.ed25519) released [their December newsletter](%ODx5+mHZdO3W7xoUl45t5zHMbdpEFzpkmYai+Tfxi8c=.sha256).\n\n(I told you I was still catching up. ;) )\n\n> December tends to hang around till the last minute each year. It joins us for a sauna after sunset, packs its things in secret and stashes them in a snowbank. December only leaves after weve counted down from ten, dropped the lantern from the tree, and toasted with kombucha and tea and the odd glass of cider. While were hugging and singing, it slips off down the street in the shadow of the maples. Goodbyes can feel awkward for me too, so I get it. Safe travels friend.\n\n----\n[@dangerousbeans](@TXKFQehlyoSn8UJAIVP/k2BjFINC591MlBC2e2d24mA=.ed25519) shared [Alchemist''s new herb garden](%IFbCilDAe5dBeWniaI/TYgHrQkS4ZcIZc9Wv4+M9M90=.sha256).\n\n![alchemists herb garden](&QQ8l3oYluXhik9+j5Ph1xe2XjM42vcYOooN6hU6twSA=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Mira Mos Crime](@qi+mBq3/BQi5OCHQ28n5Uq1+M6GL85Gnvd6ahLHYK9g=.ed25519) [painted a table](%QA0yjU0DgeeCzj4gqMHqnyPwNTbLInAdNtsA35NEotI=.sha256).\n\n![a small table painted with many lines, shapes, and colors](&W71Ziix5QbuJWVy9gXmaSL8VpmX4ASAbqNbpffS0UA8=.sha256)\n\n## Community \n[@Taeyoon Choi](@W1o0EvTFWz6rOxHl0QYuhWnCYpJ3/lnm1ZuSgUy2kQo=.ed25519) \nshared [some drawings with good advice](%I//yRhRW9Dd2Px3OLjBgK+z2/yFKQPb3jIOKiLfXyc8=.sha256)\n\n![writing about being critical in a constructive manner ](&60pPGYrWcIPk6IuIrXX5bp2DeRRSvzAxfaerJ+4GiUE=.sha256)\n\n\nand [some graphical translation work](%yf5HBlnplp4df28Gtx7WVVDdv3SB98MorldcWpSxcwE=.sha256) about what it means when someone says "Nothing is going to change" \n\n![Korean, Chinese, and english characters writing about awarness, denial, certainty, truth, and more. A person in a cube says "Nothing is going to change"](&7iRnMf1LHlNFHMVuTUS5yVLKTeKw3Fma6HLyj61WA/I=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@beau](@XOJDYE5Ic9IZf4TK0Kaf1p4F2JlObJ4avgveC50dbWY=.ed25519)\nhad [an interesting parody take on scuttlebutt conversations](%hlozRmWT62wypaOYlkTzVTkyEiyZlUd/IYPvanl/3FY=.sha256)\n\nThere''s a lot of truth to it. \n\nHopefully these postings of mine help you find the other bits of interesting out here.\n\n\n\n## Software\n[@andrestaltz](@QlCTpvY7p9ty2yOFrv1WU1AE88aoQc4Y7wYal7PFc+w=.ed25519) [released Manyverse for iOS](%yNkrJtnHyR4LcgzYvJ3nYdvQ1U3i2SlVxzbs7vOH5WU=.sha256)\n\n![ios-launch@2x.png](&6PE8z83sJJd0MFH/ynSM/l63feP+d/7Lzf98/p7zbKk=.sha256)\n\n\nCongratulations Andr.\n\nI''m setting it up now... \n\n----\npost 2 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(821,replace('[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519)\nreleased v0.0.5 released (beta) of the [SSB Backup Tool](%tmQjDsWri6a2kLrFNDnezwfp5sQ+kloDmPVI39fBtIs=.sha256). It''s still early stages, but this is good progress. :) \n\n![backup tool](&16rYIY9Wa3dfs41IbNXmlizTrpTJEQKbgqLhM309yK0=.sha256)\n(Give it a minute and you''ll see more than just a progress spinner)\n\n> This version is a milestone for SSB Backup Tool because it is the first version that is able to start an SSB server on demand. This means that I can now start working on the restore account part of the app. \n\n----\n[@Luandro](@2RNGJafZtMHzd76gyvqH6EJiK7kBnXeak5mBWzoO/iU=.ed25519) shared [a demo](%+Hz7yBq533jDWNzWfflyhWIdfEI79qbCm2aIRwIEsW0=.sha256) of "...Pirania, the mesh captive-portal solution, integrating it with LiMe App and LiMe Packages with tests."\n\n![video:Pirania_demo.webm](&w0jWgEHZfsMthN7tCddRMpO2ZGZX8mfHqvu+lZzv/Fs=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n\n[@Stephen](@YRtB3WcY1zqGAeUx4OWv+p3+hvS7IvrDdUnmlkrz6ZM=.ed25519) [released their side project](%42tChB2BTv77L0ljd1486gEWX4kw1oOd3tVOtWFjgX4=.sha256) called [Fediverse Explorer](https://fediverse.0qz.fun/)\n\n> Every hour its aggregating trending content from 3000 mastodon pixelfed and pleroma servers to produce a trending tag report.\n\nFind a tag that interests you, click it, and see the recent posts with it.\n\n----\n[@ahaproudowl](@cP1iqUv8WYGL0s/5S8Rgx4gaJYxDErKIHVqw4/aB0K4=.ed25519) shared what Patchwork would look like with the Meriweather Open Font. \n\n[More examples in the post](%cZ4txv4Ti67oAxaUX+StWUL+IUKCF/5ZOhzoU46R+mw=.sha256)\n\n![Patchwork with the Merriweather Open Font](&vAMS93+/Rlk+ToD3lKX8RGdtzdDjcSu9uFXrnt+W+aM=.sha256)\n\nI don''t know about you, but this and the other examples make me _really_ want a real Font picker.\n\n\n## Geeky\n[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) shared the [roadblocks they''ve been encountering with Svelte](%PY7CeNmH190OvwjPoMHvG4mRkHbxU01WbrgebDdelko=.sha256) and their effects on Patchfox work. \n\n----\n[@Offray](@QRttJgVouWhDWpnZHo2BoT5LkGA1irFA+fY+HkGSksc=.ed25519) has been sharing some visualizations of their Scuttlebutt stuff, [like this visualization of Scuttlebtut folder sizes](%SS8MrGU2lEi+YMKU5+KiJt8e0oj1PKVshbb81XJqFZ0=.sha256):\n\n![SSB Folder Sizes visualized](&JA7Tx5BcIV4A22gAcaGsAfTsi38QvMtH4vFyXMLbMx8=.sha256)\n\n\n> For the moment, this and others are just starting explorations. My idea is to build a Pharo + Roassal Domain Specific Language to explore and visualize the #scuttleverse and to live code it.\n\n\n----\n[@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519) (me) shared a [personal journey through 30+ years of programming](%wHlaRYCo3jnzKWqqz57EVHyHf/gnzU/9FMZjc2Xsn6I=.sha256). \n\n![a graph of masukomis journey through programming languages](&Nr054t0vTbGe3OUOKJMiF6GBhnBaLOd8NFR5vxrzDE0=.sha256)\n\nI still don''t really know what it means. I''m just reflecting on languages I''ve known, how they''ve affected me, and what I took away from it.\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis weeks summary was curated from ~373 threads (that I''m still working through) by 154 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n----\npost 3 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(840,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n\n[@Logan Brunkhorst ](@lWaeNJRPeyAsyE8fwllLQHAe3AkZbb5bEGPUAAIBVz0=.ed25519) shares [an image of kids keeping busy](%Jcy2uM78JpOA3b2QW2yQmCMWti+cP+fny8/0q9TD/mY=.sha256)\n\n![keeping busy ](&L+AGi/+1/oXSyGz55D1If3vkGOOE613YyXUGqTFIxI4=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@polylith](@0nakXtVIodBfdHwRQLVb64p54jTWS+DFHRqg58ky4CI=.ed25519) shared  [a picture of their dog Tucker](%k4Dfe1SV0vldMq2RYFL84MEkSknPAu+yuj+Xa+nStpo=.sha256) in the light at the end of day.\n\n![A photo of Tucker, who is a brown and white dog, standing amid dunegrass and patches of snow atop a sand dune, wearing a safety orange bandana. The sun is setting over the water in the background.](&oobQVpEmhR4H8EDmNTtuZTxHaAd0KmbYjUcCbk1M5RU=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@dangerousbeans](@TXKFQehlyoSn8UJAIVP/k2BjFINC591MlBC2e2d24mA=.ed25519) shared [another picture of Alchemist](%eqU9voixw3EBkx5DsgY8RJaXffWy+Wugg8PEQJ4r72c=.sha256)\n\n> Stahhppp - A portrait of anchoring struggles, 2020\n\n\n![Alchemist at anchor and chaos on deck](&dZ2gOLS0zKOJCU+dilMWGNuSh8/hiHIUNYKcFr2KSkk=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@mia gooper ](@w6CroJjf0ovg4qqF+uN29sqSztYmMITeD93jaMo0YQ4=.ed25519) shared [an interesting doodle](%/AUF7k1jLUE2IdnzIjfq+NVih9IRjHtAMaKHpct4N5M=.sha256) about brainstorming:\n\n![brainstorm vs brain storm](&iCJ5vkR7FlsYNoc6/lJGAiFVjmHQdzUcYPSJXtRogl4=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Daan p20 ](@tUMwMvb+roaOJAyohpGUxgqYo4E7HfBlY0NkUzALqjY=.ed25519) shared [a glipmse of how you fuel your vehicle in Bali](%b0vjiFQC2mne3eHSrOAZjyvVUxMqcLWSJ2rN4rHsaEE=.sha256)\n\n![two manual fuel pumps, with the fuel visible in a glass cylinder above each one. one fuel is green and one is more blue. both pumps are operated by hand cranks.](&2TwRi+8LYQlQTy9l9wO9IMsviM40xz72DYRreDwoCwA=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Masukomi ](@jRBZhQmc6pe6E105mbl9g/5iqfYeCygVtVwE4QJFFBY=.ed25519) (me) shared a cute fluffy cat. \n\n![a cat curled in a ball on top of an artificial tree ](&n9D82CAbAEUzASwTJ78MJTgXg2QHlR5Vy5/j7LRLhpg=.sha256)\n\nSSB needs more cute pet pictures. They power the internet. \n\n----\n[@punkmonk](@EaYYQo5nAQRabB9nxAn5i2uiIZ665b90Qk2U/WHNVE8=.ed25519) shared [a slice of Lancaster County](%syjgahT22d/bIF7JnIqIjxNqC8rrM+hwNwXBlxQFdEM=.sha256) including pictures of solar power, a spring house, chicken coops, goats, dogs and more.\n\n![two goats look at a photographer. One stands in the snow. The other looks out from a wooden shelter](&gqy5DBzppDr6p/chpVUUvbtSngrgM+oJ0XMJ5kV7rTM=.sha256).\n\n\n----\n[@rjkip](@ctLmxhUiEPou/jxfKyGxs+nVh6XcM6uCCg0ldePkLGc=.ed25519) shares pictures from the opposite hemisphere: trails, sheep, birds, bicyclists, andmore.\n\n![a recently shorn sheep in tall brown grass looks at the photographer](&AglL9ZJhkSE7pldU4sm+nOF9qEiLbe2PJtqawBn5Gmk=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@](@a/g1UYTznmhfE1OQrU1/0sT3YM4TuYNxc6EtfFP1iao=.ed25519) shares [a tale of an old granite quarry and learning to climb](%sOTC/xAUbdLK7Wsum1D1v4wfwha3yW5cQ4DBqUP51og=.sha256). \n\n![two people walking into a quarry filled in with dirt, and covered with graffiti](&YujDniIYBuNkjaQkUPCPVsZFSGknH06QXW2KHGtlS2I=.sha256)\n\n\n\npost 1 of 4\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(850,replace('## Solarpunk \n[@Luandro](@2RNGJafZtMHzd76gyvqH6EJiK7kBnXeak5mBWzoO/iU=.ed25519) shares they''ve been making towards managing their community watershed and asked for a little money to help build the prototype. You beautiful people stepped up and helped out. \n\n![comurede_modulos.jpg](&RyaXnu/DFdv/Oi5Rj3TZpHViZ+XI0PNOfELHl3+ioIs=.sha256)\n\n\nAs an aside, it''s saddening how much of the $$ got eaten by crypto fees.  The idea of cryptocurrency is great, but I feel like we just haven''t found an implementation that actually works better than "real" money for most applications. :(\n\n## Community\n[@haileycoop](@QdKPBH4vZne0DqD+v1mVJgeeOg8y3RxWuomT7pvIfEA=.ed25519) says \n\n> After I mentioned to a US friend about our air quality situation here in Australia, she came back with a ton of ideas about what people could do within limited means to protect their lungs and their overall health.\n> \n> Ive also started pulling in other stuff Im seeing, including stuff that some other folks have been sharing about air purifiers and the right app to use.\n\n[Click through](@QdKPBH4vZne0DqD+v1mVJgeeOg8y3RxWuomT7pvIfEA=.ed25519) to their thread for a link to the Google Doc.\n\n----\n\n[@martin ](@pJsYrTaEjm5XW5Qe0W9JW2c+RpYNqJHPMZ0qGFFYXfI=.ed25519) says \n\n> Yesterday at #lca2020, [I spoke about what makes decentralisation hard, what we can do about that](%9yVpmGY6d5zqcuGiWI2mFuM45BnQX7s/LsC/6jLKSTI=.sha256), and a plan to save the Web, which has stark similarities with what @andrestaltz has been writing about (although I came up with it all by myself).\n\nThe video is up if you''re interested. \n\n----\n[@Richard D. Bartlett](@3r4+IyB5NVl2in6QOZHIu9oSrZud+NuVgl2GX3x2WG8=.ed25519) says \n\n\n> We just wrapped up the filming work for our new online course \n\nIt''s called [Patterns for Decentralised Organisation](%HvDkaIecJG941oON6Ju1ftH3nDxRz4r0+StyS9URy0Q=.sha256)\n\n\n![richard d bartlett being filmed for their new online course](&ojTKlSc4qV02GC0WjT9psuyNxctRmKGu3Nr0WhkLMR8=.sha256)\n\n\n\n----\n[@mnin](@SXVoA/7CuMRS5IDTNsO8HU2PvCIVq8HKUUx/k+idDiQ=.ed25519) shared [an image](%XvyMQXz2LjUmJtc6crjP9GrAEofjXVRHoLRBEqEy46g=.sha256) showing the scale of the Australian bushfires relative to recent large fires.\n\n![bar graph showing the relative size of the 2019 amazon fires, the 2018 California fires, and the 2019-220 Australian bush fire](&O7hjdV1339I10LUO9JnXnfB+SQQNL2DBzOmhFnCmi8Y=.sha256).\n\n----\npost 2 of 4\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(856,replace('[@KawaiiPunk](@LVL4qjvmws3Cxavfi4iCQI6dSOqWqOyq5/5CHImILA8=.ed25519) shared a post about [Growth at the rate of trust](%96fE4lECuncfo8cMQHBWU0WpAx+cIq7A8NHFSzbxLTM=.sha256)\n\n> I am a little worried about our network getting too large...\n> I think private groups may be the single most important feature that is coming down the line. I am basically connecting and replicating with a lot of peers that I dont know or trust. Im not actually so up for that. It adds a constant low level of stress that someone may share something bad or they may be a malicious actor on the network...\n> I really want to share more personal stuff on here about stuff like mental health, gender and ADHD but the current model doesnt seem safe...\n\nThey go on to talk about Google+ style circles and provide a rough sketch of how that could fit in to SSB.\n\n----\n[@andrestaltz_phone](@+UMKhpbzXAII+2/7ZlsgkJwIsxdfeFi36Z5Rk1gCfY0=.ed25519) shared "[The many stages of climate anxiety](%j6pU2gUwhJ82HylvtoBKKckVYqMY86CRtRbnQ4OtJbc=.sha256)" \n\n----\n\n[@mnin](@SXVoA/7CuMRS5IDTNsO8HU2PvCIVq8HKUUx/k+idDiQ=.ed25519) shares that \n\n> In preparation for #scuttlecamp2 a bunch of us are really keen to start picking up some Portuguese! :)\n> \n> Id thought Id [use this thread to begin](%eQP5HHrbULlv0v3Xq2PY6QJBwoGA1ixaQkWXPsQM3Mo=.sha256) some basic introductions of ourselves in Portuguese and share resources. No pressure or fancy pants needed, but also go ahead if you want to show us what youve got :) Just reply in text and/or audio-files of you speaking to join in the fun.\n\n\n\n## Software\n\n[@mix](@ye+QM09iPcDJD6YvQYjoQc7sLF/IFhmNbEqgdzQo3lQ=.ed25519) announced [a really nice upgrade to the Profile Overview page](%2okHT7oIb3f3AWTUGVkwTL6enG7/s75k8iZ0PfU1ugw=.sha256) in hau.\n\n![profile overview page in ahua](&VBqr/5tEm69dgWIVeXkjBsvpGGs1BLoA/DuEoPaHyJQ=.sha256)\n\nYou can learn more about [hau here](https://ahau.io/)\n\n----\n[@Powersource](@Vz6v3xKpzViiTM/GAe+hKkACZSqrErQQZgv4iqQxEn8=.ed25519) has [released SSB First Aid Kit 1.3](%ftHCQ/2PvWjys7KKH2oO7PwMMj+aAXFXn7/pryultJI=.sha256)\n\n> A user-friendly app for diagnosing and fixing problems with your Scuttlebutt installation\n\n\n![SSB First Aid Kit v1.3](&MdDNTMvdoWL7gkZpjK5zzNVdUt/pr3/UPXOcTsWybvg=.sha256)\n\n> Pretty happy where the app is at now. No major missing stuff. Which is nice since the second funding block is just about to end. There are some features I can think of to add but this might be a good point to let people play with it and see where its lacking and could help more, rather than just to put random new features into it.\n\n----\nOn a related note [@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) has begun working on [the restore identity process](%IlbaHuKDPXFQjtDUzl8BKkiPZeEruQB/UdbkKlL8iUk=.sha256) in the SSB Backup utility.\n\n![restore identity screenshot](&FRdWnF/4NEr/MJt3ZvyPWQMwgQ2yvne1CM7rgYAuK7c=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@cblgh](@C6fAmdXgqTDbmZGAohUaYuyKdz3m6GBoLLtml3fUn+o=.ed25519) has "... created an open collective to help fund at least recurring costs [of Cabal development]" \n\nThere [post is here](%QKG/1CVxb5XnW/a4Lr50J+/4rWMP553WlPvSCDG0QTA=.sha256) and If you like the idea of an easy to use, free, decentraliced chat system that can eventually replace Slack you should consider going to [their open collective page](https://opencollective.com/cabal-club) and sponsoring them.\n\nRight now I think [Cabal](https://cabal.chat/) is our best chance at a chatty future not controled by big corporations. \n\nI love that the GUI client is already very user friendly. It''s not perfect, and needs some more moderation features before most folks could use it at work, BUT I''d love to see this get funded enough to support real development progress.\n\npost 3 of 4\n','\n',char(10)));
