REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(888,replace('[@scott](@0nakXtVIodBfdHwRQLVb64p54jTWS+DFHRqg58ky4CI=.ed25519) has released [another Polylith newsletter](%oY1qkc6IW3war9zneziHTfkJXR3+fe6v1yCaQavX4rE=.sha256). \n\n> Hello friends. Here we are at the end of this inaugural twelve-month cycle of letters. We arrive, as ever and by puzzling graces, where we began: under countless strata of snow by turns waning and waxing, pleasantly lost amid a kaleidoscope of tracks, standing atop the great mineral body.\n\n## Community\n\n[@Aljoscha](@zurF8X68ArfRM71dF3mKh36W0xDM8QmOnAS5bYOq8hA=.ed25519) created [SSB Event in Basel - The Official Infothread](%fc9bcQHZiiyntJC6G9IPkI6LHUytEmQeQZvGm9mgyis=.sha256)\n\n\n> In this post, you will find all the information you might need regarding the Basel SSB event in one place. Also check out the event website or the handy flyer.\n\n![P2P SSB Event in Basel Header](&ByyZhYA0u5JQa/1fTezb4XJTL4HBmsGE47zGLnartFM=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n\n[@Richard D. Bartlett](@3r4+IyB5NVl2in6QOZHIu9oSrZud+NuVgl2GX3x2WG8=.ed25519)\n\n> I published the latest story in my Microsolidarity series, explaining how to start a new mutual aid community (a Congregation). That chapter was exclusively focussed on the initiation process: where do you start?\n\n![Scaffolding for a new congregation](&+0RNgrTZi80qQXzDfAcVTXRMKy5jKypRj3dUzo7tyZI=.sha256)\n\n[Details in their post](%TTnDBeIzGU6j69mnUs2Z24cJkp/ojoRJSCRwOIi8t2A=.sha256)\n\n\n## Community & Software Intersection\n[@Luandro](@2RNGJafZtMHzd76gyvqH6EJiK7kBnXeak5mBWzoO/iU=.ed25519) shared a story of [how a handful of Scuttlebutt people got together and used SSB to connect remote villages in hash desert conditions](%Uh6Qk/9ncyKFJWJXDOeLSU1CLIagXc+ANyT999Ol5dw=.sha256). It didn''t work as intended, but there''s hope for it still.\n\n![san women app cropped](&tWh14aRBmwiz0aHUtW6NOvtomsZyU3n3S6O/jTL85LQ=.sha256)\n\nIn a related followup post they [wonder aloud what we can do](%ysNpZQb8WlraaTJYwRGIdwQUTSgWQ6fUETFDzPB2Eo0=.sha256) to make SSB usable on low-end Android devices. \n\n\n----\n\n[@Hamiller](@LZSw/izhW0O1VA1ptApOEQovM2U1//8ThdJNsfDqePQ=.ed25519) [shares](%clRWH7oUl6uNNcmQrL4kqfr7fHW63cofAzcOwE1iuk4=.sha256) a [Wired article](https://www.wired.com/story/phone-addiction-formula/)\n\n> Push messages, manipulative menu navigation, red bubbles that scream: There are new messages! - who came up with all this? The historical view is often missing in the heated debate about the permanent distraction caused by our smartphones. Wired set out in 2018 to find the trail, and the trail leads to Stanford University.\n\n----\n[@Hamiller](@LZSw/izhW0O1VA1ptApOEQovM2U1//8ThdJNsfDqePQ=.ed25519) shares [some thoughts from Cory Doctorow](%dw15U8YH33Jq2enpPs+Zmr92pPUS7gvREo1dQp2/E8Q=.sha256) about a future where the technology we carry is used to help sense and share information on the world around us, not intstead of just sharing information about _us_. \n\n----\n\npost 2 of 4\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(898,replace('[@Emmi Bevensee](@5fX6QTmue/udf7tLwW25vQ63wZSENrksghBt6vfL4/I=.ed25519) helped create [The Social Media Analysis Toolkit](%0bgCPWPsfIC+lrL8kt5WYreDjBtFA17uDO016dOcPTA=.sha256)\n\n> The Social Media Analysis Toolkit (SMAT) was designed to help activists, journalists, researchers, and other social good orgs to analyze and visualize larger trends on a variety of social platforms. Our intention is to provide quick and easy tools that help you tell a story about something like hate or disinformation happening at a large scale and rapidly online. But theyre also rigorous enough for academia. This is our crew doing some research with similar tools.\n\nClick through to learn more and checkout the graphs. \n\n\n## Software\n\n[@Rabble](@THUzexG1y6kWofwiN8Lix/jNH/P6roYdlCDgpAn2HSc=.ed25519) shared [some updates on the Planetary iOS Scuttlebutt Client](%T9rxQjww7cu4h4KeqvwDwKJamgS4v2f3jCMnbda854s=.sha256) and the company they''re building to create it.\n\n----\n[@arj](@6CAxOI3f+LUOVrbAl0IemqiS7ATpQvr9Mdw9LC4+Uv0=.ed25519) says \n[Its time for another update on the ssb-browser front](%pc3IVvokQreZF1a0q448THRccPcuBv5PHhuO6sBUTIA=.sha256) and then [proceeds to give us one](%pc3IVvokQreZF1a0q448THRccPcuBv5PHhuO6sBUTIA=.sha256). \n\n![ssb-browser screenshot](&PbryfIEh5YsKjut3Qse7GLShTecBtoHADLk99X59SBc=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@KawaiiPunk](@LVL4qjvmws3Cxavfi4iCQI6dSOqWqOyq5/5CHImILA8=.ed25519), and others, have posted about how Oasis is the next generation of SSB client, the successor to Patchwork.\n\nChristian Bundy has made spectacular progress on this, but there''s still a ways to go, and our future shouldn''t be resting in the hands of one person. If you''re a JavaScript developer, looking to help with the future of Scuttlebutt I''d strongly recommend you check out the [Oasis Repository](https://github.com/fraction/oasis) and help out in whatever way you can. Maybe take on one of the existing tickets, or write a little documentation for it. \n\n\n![Oasis screenshot](&XVXSIrw9GpmbPJZbErRlAvZhCEnZ+myh63yHKA56xfQ=.sha256)\n\nPlease know that I''m not saying this to diminish any of the great work on Patchbay, Patchfox or any of the other clients, or suggest that they''re not worth pitching in on if they excite you.\n\n----\n[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) shared [some eight ideas for future SSB software](%nbCypNv4VBvSyFCFjLCSez2H0xHf3YLuT1/CWhhX2b4=.sha256) that some of you might find interesting enough to take a crack at. \n\n\n----\n\n[@m455](@uysyXWRXsRD8N13ux57niW/CjZRoDVlilFRi9wpI6BQ=.ed25519) [shared a quick link](%W8mUaCX5iLzLjTm3Eq+pCRqvgokFA4POMx9P/eZ1f3k=.sha256) to a Federated Chat app called [Delta Chat](https://delta.chat/en/) that is built on top of email. If you know someone''s email address you can chat with them, even if they don''t have the client installed. \n\n\n## Geeky\n[@zyk.ratbox](@+Ld8QDcDS4Jnezi48yrpZvwC1tDBiCGpxTfyp6rw920=.ed25519) shared their ["mighty and terrible" "ratbox"](*%Bej9aKn7YDMoMBT953s+ucybEWzp3wgDNJl9KJmak/s=.sha256)\n\n![a laptop(ish) computer with too many wires a couple exposed circuit boards](&cA42siEDagVsDBhW60AQcUPoCUU51Nev5g+wbDGj4jg=.sha256)\n\n\n### Summary Data\nThis weeks summary was curated from ~646 threads by ~225 authors (a little overlap with stuff before the last issue) by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\npost 3 of ~4~ 3\n','\n',char(10)));
