REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(919,replace('## Community Software Intersection\n[@elavoie](@IgYpd+tCtXnlE2tYX/8rR2AGt+P8svC98WH3MdYAa8Y=.ed25519) shared some [more thoughts about the proposed SSB-Coin](%6mByr6BrJflzFM5gCQj5tAwDcYNgiFeZMR41LGj4PzE=.sha256), including a number of practical ways it could be used.\nI''m really torn about this. On the one hand what they''re proposing is _very_ different from all the cryptocurrency BS out there. On the other hand cryptocurrency has become _seriously_ tainted by scams, unregulated market manipulation, and all sorts of other BS. \n\nSo, I _love_ the community aspect and just basic idea of tokens that, ath their heart are just representations of favors. I also fear that having _any_ "coin" associated with SSB will affect the future prospects of SSB as a social network by proxy.\n\n----\n[@cinnamon](@fBS90Djngwl/SlCh/20G7piSC064Qz2hBBxbfnbyM+Y=.ed25519) mentioned the [social problems with the word "block" in SSB](%RhRAuS9kkBhJeaUoKlGGoD6yimM4KY3zm0MJAGylTnI=.sha256) and a small discussion emerged on how to improve it. I believe the general consensus is "yeah, Cinnamon''s right, there''s a problem" but it''s not clear what the best solution is.\n\n----\n[@gwil](@PEqxT8YRvrkf2fyjAgTl8pmdo8aR4KVsKLyh0b5JyOE=.ed25519) posted about how "[Timelines Are Awful, Even If Theyre Decentralised](%4UHRF/xbCaeyk/Jgw92LBWXrfGm9SCo3YIfAVXwtNzw=.sha256)" \n\n> Social networks are made of posts, and users need a way to read them. But the popular timeline interface is designed to benefit the organisation that serves it, not the user who reads it.\n\nThey break down why, and suggest a couple improvements.\n\n\n## Software \n[@andrestaltz](@QlCTpvY7p9ty2yOFrv1WU1AE88aoQc4Y7wYal7PFc+w=.ed25519) released [the 0.20002.4 version of Manyverse](%Sptmraltrgkcq/WP72LGb8gHltncs17taPds254YUBc=.sha256) for Android and iOS. It''s got a bunch of bug fixes and general improvements, but the more notable things are that it now supports private messaging, and has a new layout.\n\n![animated gif of manyverse private messages](&8B5KwCaFThwgFhKADRC08KVqAMpfAcitykn34+jn/VU=.sha256)\n\nThey also shared [a fun little SSB tip](%BupswexGU5BogqOYr05RbRFR9PWjZnT8EsgWSeYzJ28=.sha256). \n\n> if you assign a name that starts with "dead" or "deprecated", they will be ignored in the suggestions dropdown.\n----\n\n[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519) [notes that](%P/Fb+aHzqEASsFMV0fkJohNfVUTqkLFnXVISbimOfaY=.sha256)\n\n> ...if anyone wants to dip their toes into SSB development, Oasis has lots of [good first issues](https://github.com/fraction/oasis/issues) that only require that you know the basics of GitHub. Some require basic HTML, CSS, or JS knowledge, but all of them are easy and bite-sized and Id love to support anyone working on them.\n\n----\n[@KemoNine](@2JMza/WpInn3c0N2bw4QfRRLhrb2h17eNBKpDshBk1o=.ed25519) has shared [instructions on how to install patchfoo as a Docker container](%ELS+7x5JjDJTT+8YN4YcesmEN2BzNHB44JzI7fXJlR8=.sha256). Patchfoo is a...\n\n> Plain SSB web UI. Uses HTML forms instead of client-side JS. Designed for use on low-power and low-resource computers.\n\n----\n[@adz](@3u2quSQ8qX1fTx4HQKthYPDavQI4Wm88kThExFXemYo=.ed25519) has created "Beep beep!" \n\n> ...a naive [p2p proof-of-concept system which can be both federated or fully decentralized](%3cZzSLQBeF97sYIkPjFMqhE7sSLF5cy5KyKW3THtX+o=.sha256), something in-between #ssb and maybe #activitypub.\n\n![Beep beep network](&GdAgrRVAC2AmQRvUUfPJMQtWZrgIFk4WEdJUC0TfYU8=.sha256)\n\nCheck out their post for more details.\n\npost 2 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(929,replace('[@nichoth](@RPFLJtoWjcQyYC51lEUxm4brAyE6Okln8LGeh4Z7sVw=.ed25519) has been continuing their work on "eventual gram" an ssb-based photo sharing. They''re updating us with development diary posts [like this one](%/PKLgEKQqNi1S3XIw3JagcdsgKOR9wRb9j2RXNzj1bg=.sha256).\n\n## Geeky\n[@mixmix](@ye+QM09iPcDJD6YvQYjoQc7sLF/IFhmNbEqgdzQo3lQ=.ed25519) has created [is-my-ssb-valid](%cOBKIX7oyDF4x9yMFDNWcUjV0hGvJrEiRisA54//vAI=.sha256) which can "Build message validators for scuttlebut using JSON schema."\n\n----\n[@punkmonk](@EaYYQo5nAQRabB9nxAn5i2uiIZ665b90Qk2U/WHNVE8=.ed25519) has been [exploring the nodejs cluster module](%4S5TVYfrx4GAqeGpYYWc1fvSoEO9UyS/7UfI17kw8v0=.sha256) and shared  their results.\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis weeks summary was curated from 387 threads by 148 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\npost 3 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(945,replace('I keep thinking about wanting to do more with SSB. About the great community here, and the future we can build. About how it allows us to do great things like [blog from the middle of the ocean](%RbzGUXS4jiZHToZN9xPHBRAOs08VZjLgfyoz1KklmvQ=.sha256) and one thing really struck me tonight.\n\nIt doesn''t matter if SSB becomes "popular". We never have to worry about some company making enough off of it to keep the infrastructure alive. All we have to do is believe in it, and have some developers willing to maintain the tools to use it. \n\nWe do need some folks generous enough to run pubs for us, but that''s not too much to ask especially from a community of devoted users, and it''s just going to get cheaper and easier as time goes by.\n\nThat''s pretty awesome. \n\nThere are _very_ few places online that can say that. ','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(949,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n[@rjkip](@ctLmxhUiEPou/jxfKyGxs+nVh6XcM6uCCg0ldePkLGc=.ed25519) shared [some gorgeous photes](%/XEKhOq8hD5M4W5wraR0RewzatbvG3J7NtG3fVLNNb4=.sha256) from a sunrise at Godley Head in New Zealand.\n\n![ocean meats mountains at Godley Head in New Zealand](&YkLVYCQQd0j9rrMnI1dwguQMb7dnf5Hw2NGnBjqoCQo=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Isabela](@Xe+wuSGAaEdwgyI/ql2WVgPG64Mqf8tVHU0VXne9Ki8=.ed25519) shared some cerrado seeds along with [information on what they are, what they''re used for, etc.](%DmLltmlMMHVWc9WHgLzz+wJTd13QKaPDDUIbnsvoJLI=.sha256)\n\n![a hand holding cerrado seeds](&3bWxOEv9B1PaDetqhwvKLLasKAWN7C93iASS5qMq05U=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Dominic](@EMovhfIrFk4NihAKnRNhrfRaqIhBv1Wj8pTxJNgvCCY=.ed25519) shared a [strange vegetable unknown to most people outside of New Zealand](%JdYW2INlWW5BcSub3caOr4mNmUul4Hw+m0ul7egjsFc=.sha256)\n\n![a kumara on a cutting board](&GuHvsLdFXhjO+Fy8luxUinl5jm8hFr8BwkFPTiYt5aI=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n\nIn case others hadn''t picked up on this: \n\n[@Richard D. Bartlett](@3r4+IyB5NVl2in6QOZHIu9oSrZud+NuVgl2GX3x2WG8=.ed25519) [says](%i+lGd65NeYoVHrUFE/bdanvaWj7HKmC6X+Y8siZwXTo=.sha256): \n\n> I just realised why there is so much crab imagery on scuttlebutt! Wow language is funny, obvious, obscure:\n>\n> gossip -> scuttlebutt -> scuttling -> how crabs move\n\n----\n\n[@Danie](@0Tv5f/opjv/m1ONAKl6S79HWbHdLaCtt/emdXl2MCO0=.ed25519) posted [an example of how ham radio volunteers frequently fill in the communication gaps](%MRZdnRrVJaxnD+G9OoyCRC1zFhgSLNdPhRjFWfo3btw=.sha256) where groups like fire, ambulance, and police don''t have the equipment, or experience. \n\n----\n\n\n[@Beni Grind (mobile)](@GZ7EOhJ3V0xsqy1fNH1CKobsKRRDTAbjl5Jtbp9005Y=.ed25519) continues to [live the one wheel lifestyle](%UgXM4Q6p971jaEhwWIt+xTFrbGm1iYPB9GJJUZnNyC4=.sha256)\n\n![unicycling to work](&NVl9CuSsiPv43w+t0qiQQyjMEen9qX54VOE99IuREWk=.sha256)\n\n> If I walk to the office it takes me roughly 6 minutes. On the unicycle its closer to 10.\n\n\n\n\n## Solarpunk\n\n[@mudflap-Dell-laptop](@w3i0o1aAJimCoOWsvMVCPUl9dKNXIBlgtE/FUh5OQ2k=.ed25519) is building a log cabin in Alabama USA.\n\n![shafts of sunlight hit the inside of an unfinished log cabin wall](&IE+JURfK8WfRvaD3K5+8YcAQ+C0yd6XSGPVODOkGMFk=.sha256)\n\n\n\n## Community\n\n[@emile](@2YVYXQclEJHVzCON5dsLRwf65b2S6HnvxpGS8/LwjwY=.ed25519) asked [who still has a twitter, facebook, and / or linkedin account](%CzAVpa2siu8A6OxdMOcb13wTWYaRbP9OtQq1NYtlrUw=.sha256)\n\nFolks are responding with which they have, and their thoughts on why. The latter is interesting. \n\n\n----\n[@Dylorb](@0ERFW4smS9/m4jQIDD1TNqa1tnh1H2bHnVPjw/Lfv0s=.ed25519) shares a [US Government grant for work on or around P2P communication](%zdlU7ISMRKfocDrcbEwMn0GXO4vbLFrbAFgiQlqD+ps=.sha256) technologies.\n\npost 1 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(960,replace('## Software\n[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519) released Oasis 2.13.1. \n\n* Follow, unfollow, block, unblock\n* More networking info and actions (including offline mode)\n* Way faster private message rendering\n* Works with Patchwork running in background (!)\n* Sidebar navigation with cute emoji\n* Very very basic internationalization (need help translating!)\n* Removed strangers from main feed\n* Add Extended and Topics views\n* Add public viewer mode\n* Fix 8 trillion bugs\n\nIf you''re familiar with running `npm` commands I _highly_ recommend you check it out. It is _very_ usable, and very nice looking. It doesn''t have _all_ the features yet, but the ones it has are :thumbsup:\n\n[@cinnamon](@fBS90Djngwl/SlCh/20G7piSC064Qz2hBBxbfnbyM+Y=.ed25519) shared [a screenshot](%u+Mnq1AFB2w7BV3F27jfi2EcZiyPc7YCnK1mEf+9Z9U=.sha256), and noted that the background color was the result of the color palette they''d chosen. \n\n![oasis.jpg](&OVCfC6AhysTM+1DFuaWPZoCK6DIYKlqTkndCu3SvVcY=.sha256)\n\nI''m really enjoying the built-in color choices. :) \n\n\n\nThen [@josh](@HaYp1REDTDv9Su7XIz8WNDyCIbv5/TkbUJpTdJuQuwI=.ed25519) [shoved it in an Electron wrapper](%1pDgo29fURD+lY/WxbKPdQZG0oHwD0Hao8xV4T222M8=.sha256) to make it a desktop app.\n\n----\n\n[@graham](@LEkAGbzqsXLzBxLEPhkNluDHbPnkU6PXGyqwjqY10Tk=.ed25519) [shared a link and info](%j0DiHbHkdlm3gtn1xmf+ipJ3m4XpYXAiPSz/mbiUh0s=.sha256) about [Anytype](https://anytype.io/)\n\n> Anytype is a next generation software that breaks\ndown barriers between applications, gives back\nprivacy and data ownership to users.\n\nIt appears to be a collection of locally managed apps that share data with peers over IPFS. Apps manage "Pages", Tasks, Files, Contacts, Bookmarks, and Music. It''s still pre-release though so, there''s not much that can be said about it.\n\n## Geeky Software\n\nI [announced private comments](%eY5MWy7c8Ocj5k5Rt5RwxrEVbxFU7QppAUhqwJ33UFQ=.sha256). It allows you to leave private comments on specific lines of a codebase that are not stored _in the codebase_, and disappear when they become obsolete.\n\nThere''s a vim plugin for it, and instructions on how to create one for your favorite editor.\n\n## Geeky\n[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) shares [some of their thoughts on the current version of Patchwork](%wq4Wxx8fbhCiStU9WQ1Wzf3s9qLAs5Xc0hNZW4ioezk=.sha256) as they move from Svelte to Mithril. Separately they discussed the [new build system and scaffold](%o5YA89gWtZaUx9ijo2kHVF25zJL9AmSqMMXiBEJH+Bo=.sha256)\n\nAlso, [an interesting observation about Patchwork as compared to Oasis](%/P3lphrjBvhUy68HOjLnP7g7RZqjatgHZp5nLKS7BtQ=.sha256).\n\n> Oasis is what if the JS was all in the backend.\n> Patchfox is what if the JS was all in the frontend.\n\n----\n[@gwil](@PEqxT8YRvrkf2fyjAgTl8pmdo8aR4KVsKLyh0b5JyOE=.ed25519) is continuing to put out "draft UI Patterns" for social networks. [This one](%GuXX6CGk4sFR/ndczoeM+APoVufOOA4KRq7oG9lQv+A=.sha256) describes "organisational primitives for message-based social networks" including "Pins" and "A place for posts to retire"\n\n----\n[@scott](@0nakXtVIodBfdHwRQLVb64p54jTWS+DFHRqg58ky4CI=.ed25519) has been talking about their work on [creating a DAT version of scuttlebutt.nz](%OR2THatxlW+ZYTXU5DDGoinkT8D8MUpEA4iFJo9lHAY=.sha256)\n\n\npost 2 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
