REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1003,replace('[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) shared [a bunch of photos from the event itself](%zKGFjlHn+j42CObalWCfERDtczUxwSzSEIAt5g7aWa8=.sha2569).\n\n![a talk at P2P Basel](&XiOtjswL8VCAGUA4IC0b9Rfag1lMV0sGR5FWU7ehCcc=.sha256)\n\n\n\n\n## Software Community Intersection\n[@zelf](@3ZeNUiYQZisGC6PLf3R+u2s5avtxLsXC66xuK41e6Zk=.ed25519) posted some high-level [information/thoughts about privacy](%gNJjsZb+jxc032+uZunkj8HyGDO7LFQXHpD+rndvN0s=.sha256) that came out of the brainpower that came together at P2P Basel.\n\nThis is definitely worth a read if you''re interested in how privacy can / will play out in the future of SSB. It is _not_ a geeky post.\n\n\n----\n\n[@Daan](@MRiJ+CvDnD9ZjqunY1oy6tsk0IdbMDC4Q3tTC8riS3s=.ed25519) talked about [the idea of "Passes"](%bYZx4SpKerJGtg3bI5u+pbk+sZZfXG+WxxPxkjRvnro=.sha256) to allow specific posts to be viewable on the web.\n\n> Currently, the ssb-viewer instances and publicly hosted oasis installations are not very useful for bridging people into the scuttleverse because many messages will simply not be displayed. This is for good reasons: many people dont want their ssb content to be indexed and searchable by google and the others, so we switched to an opt-in system some time ago. Anyone who does not explicitly set `publicWebHosting` to `true` in their profile will simply not show up on these viewers. But currently its not easy to opt in, and even if it were, many people probably wouldnt. But we would like to be able to show some content to people we know, wich is very different from making everything public.\n\nIt''s a great proposal. I''d love to see it implemented. It would provide tremendous value. However, I can''t help but think that it''s been over a year since web hosting became opt-in and only Patchbay has an easy "opt-in" mechanism. As far as I know, no other client gives you an easy way to do this, and very few SSB people even understand that it''s an option.\n\n\n----\n[@keks](@YXkE3TikkY4GFMX3lzXUllRkNTbj5E+604AkaO1xbz8=.ed25519) wrote about [Making it Easier to Join Scuttlebutt](%y/4kpkhnsdVJddS0+mgSR+MLEGxnMz7p3+p/pILrg2g=.sha256)\n\n\n## Software\n[@SoapDog](@gaQw6z30GpfsW9k8V5ED4pHrg8zmrqku24zTSAINhRg=.ed25519) [announced the 2020.2.1 release of Patchfox](%iAuYhV5rAs+t/+gyWVilPOTSnmnEl9SJdj6bZlSnRRA=.sha256) (the "Quantum Spaghetti Release")\n\n![new message format in patchfox](&V884FhkI2rzPU2k5T27xrsGIV5aP13lXmjB4tj2oNzg=.sha256)\n\nwhich includes the new "Zine" app. \n\n![screenshot of the zine app within Patchfox showing a panel](&RMUmQ/Wp0dVD2wySEgTBlJ+A2yWdMd1w8d9FXz8BFKw=.sha256)\n\nYou can find the Zine App if you click on Launcher in the Patchfox menu.\n\n----\n[@mixmix](@ye+QM09iPcDJD6YvQYjoQc7sLF/IFhmNbEqgdzQo3lQ=.ed25519) shared [a screenshot from Ahua Mobile](%KE6AisR4a6nhN4TVTLJGv2yDKmyBfT9kkBnVRSiuvCM=.sha256).\n\n![ahau mobile](&4eqyLsAnUwbkap6cO2mKGYdA4rmsr3qLJ/b21PFOZDg=.sha256)\n\n\n\npost 2 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1010,replace('## Geeky\n[@Fred](@9BbJwPDjcyIqrOUPNn0nJZBduWdIrpMk3Cjz5MP361s=.ed25519) did [something cool sounding that I don''t entirely understand](%VBdzK7VxM30eTo/E8xwKze4i0PmOIOcdpI50wnHpU3M=.sha256).\n\n> I made a testing network composed of 5 #raspberrypi (2 Zero / 3B+ / 4B) + my laptop (x64) spread in different locations adding/getting data from ipfs common swarm I could have good speed (ipns/ipfs replication), once bootstrap (Pub!) refresh ipns (every minute actualy), I had access to my mutable data really quick ;) Now, I am experimenting it further.\n> \n> I could extend my ipfs swams by friendly exchanging the ipfs swarm.key through ssb private messages (instead exchanging swarm.key through ssh)!!\n\n\n\n----\n\n[@mark](@2uAvsruiAF9rFC20OUZWc/Da+6q1HqY0GQjwmyVUZ4w=.ed25519) reviewed [the Heap Sort algorithm](%hPnow2EohTsi7eJqBgeLb23Upu7f++3FfICIDckjhHI=.sha256), how it works, and whot you''d need to do to implement it. \n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis weeks summary was curated from 391 threads by 139 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\npost 3 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1015,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n[@Thomas Renkert](@5e3FkSr1OEVb2TEMAYJYIgfT4KC9xpdLdIeDwjZQip4=.ed25519) shared [a Costa Rican sunset](%mF6VLVNBQFqFii+749y/9+UXU/DtJJXNy2NdUzD8Jww=.sha256). \n\n![Costa Rica jungle sunset](&1jlRlJyEFlXwlyJO1wNRSBy205jedWvRa4pA03VYZwY=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n\n[@Beni Grind](@i/gfWqlqxBq9JkYhWIT0whiczxDTySFr9KXVwZgVavw=.ed25519) went to another extreme and shared [this image from skitouring near their home base](%Qyi2Ce7L6sZVgdTRz4dWSZCp1PG/nJzTKJv6TiHt4Ao=.sha256)\n\n![image.png](&K1qDzt+3uoext4uNwCmqvl+2L7sr0TffNJLmpIaRo4c=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@umhi](@7x+lsDrIbLkiub2LVN3YHMYZOGY1ZvaJBcxax9qD854=.ed25519) has taken to choosing an image and then building a "mix tape" around it. \n\n![ww.jpg](&wyw+YO3gIazz4Ib4v7tpf83hIgkW+b6PoqvA04gzgec=.sha256)\n\nThe mix tape for that image is [here on mixcloud.com](https://www.mixcloud.com/umhi/120723-ibm1/)\n\n\n----\n[@Joey Hess](@BCM6DHYJvWzwWi1lFl2tjDXjaqyZAEmJH5ZONSpXhtc=.ed25519) left [this image without comment](%nlPZR2dI/johPXqkj4cnYl53C6fhmNcwQndApteMGwg=.sha256). No words are needed.\n\n![children wearing home made face protection from caronavirus](&z2RPHJr6TSZqmr/ITpiVxm6L6NF5WUphL76rwmikef8=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@mixmix](@ye+QM09iPcDJD6YvQYjoQc7sLF/IFhmNbEqgdzQo3lQ=.ed25519) shared this lovely shot of [mother and child on a "secret path"](%g92VD0t8CNZ7PDIBRBUJ1wSeVMep0qEa1mGAaWpbJYw=.sha256)\n\n![secret path](&YhKdLUANpEXWdLVusUzV/gR2FyZrWaxDwpat+vxJ1M0=.sha256)\n\n----\n\n[@Gergely Polonkai (Notebook)](@YBJ62mnZ2Tx5AIplcbg8JSrZ7jq8ef07pRDm4RXl/fg=.ed25519) shared this [picture of the moon shining through an Acacia tree](%Ys7Zlct/zRaZMfg9bPXDkUoDqPB+fxfqCiEhripeazE=.sha256).\n\n![Grayscale photo of the moon shining through the branches of an acacia tree](&7/yp1++kQX06x/W/3pUFv3BWw4wMzwPIPP49sydQu3k=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@Samuel Chase](@B1ZOjF6edoKiPRtbiCnXPXqSw/4AezJCSN/u9OG+w3M=.ed25519) shared [a trip to Dangs District, Gujarat India](%9Qi+cx0FGi7iyg8Sd7et6B1tlZCORbCthftRZfdSwQ0=.sha256)\n\n> After last years enlightening trip to Bihar, my expectations for this\ntrip were high. However, upon learning that it is going to be a road\ntrip in a Tempo Traveller, I was apprehensive to the idea, and as it\nturns out, they were well-founded.\n\nChurches, rustic food, singing, bells, cows, and more...\n\n![a cow tied to a rustic post observes the camera](&V97CfFtbdQ/DI/MH2rCw8ct5Vw8I3kPhZGrWB4eKRpI=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@](@oPmpTQOH5OwVEU02RyfDj1qJUYDMj+Rt8oy1bYq/8hw=.ed25519) [went to a cat caf](%SUbW8yrdQGB4cn1ZiVCd5t+4ulhZLx2RIow7sn57edw=.sha256) and shared pictures.\n\n![two cats](&x7Do9WqJ22Bd1+gHMvs1PZK4ljJJF6CNtoCB3+/mHhc=.sha256)\n\npost 1 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
