REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1027,replace('[@Fbio Emilio Costa  (Patchwork-Requeriment Room)](@UaDd69LROKdpgNokDjdyxgxmXH0J/HD1eK7KEb98/+g=.ed25519)\nshares some insight into the thinking of British expats living in Spain, as the come to understand the reality of their Post-Brexit world. It''s an Aljazeera article, but the original is no longer available. :/\n\n\n\n## Solarpunk\n\n[@KawaiiPunk](@LVL4qjvmws3Cxavfi4iCQI6dSOqWqOyq5/5CHImILA8=.ed25519) shares a tale of drama in Sunbeam.city.\n\n> Essentially, the Sunbeam City co-op has been in a difficult spot for a long time, with original founder of the project leaving, we had difficulties assembling a team of volunteers in order to carry out moderation and admin duties. Nevertheless the instance kept on growing and eventually a new team was formed by trusted members of the community.\n> \n> After several incidents where moderation processes were lacking and after receiving critique from comrades in our surrounding communities, we decided to enter into a process of reform surrounding our structure and purpose.\n\nIt didn''t go very well and many users are abandoning ship, and trying to find homes on alternate Fediverse Servers.\n\n----\nSeparately [@KawaiiPunk](%MHi8MeDLOTlpQ4OvA9YnSn7HL3MGfpAKKo4NnI6VDRo=.sha256) shared a post entitled "[Solarpunk: To walkaway or to stay and fight?](%MHi8MeDLOTlpQ4OvA9YnSn7HL3MGfpAKKo4NnI6VDRo=.sha256)"\n\n----\n[@Isabela](@Xe+wuSGAaEdwgyI/ql2WVgPG64Mqf8tVHU0VXne9Ki8=.ed25519) shared this [picture of Luandro](%FVGfaHCFL4Cb2WxG57F8cg/EBwxqsrtHVzDL96B7INo=.sha256). As far as I can tell [@Luandro](@2RNGJafZtMHzd76gyvqH6EJiK7kBnXeak5mBWzoO/iU=.ed25519) is the living archetype of "Solarpunk".\n\n\n![luandro is solarpunk](&+YjoM64mkB5X1MDM/NqIDHUq5EDiV9D3Kah/BftDxQk=.sha256)\n\n## Community\n\n[@cel](@f/6sQ6d2CMxRUhLpspgGIulDxDCwYD7DzFzPNr7u5AU=.ed25519) has [SSB stickers for you.](%5boB1JPEk6JX27eL3a00D8PCzNHrJFGY9HocCQKPWlE=.sha256)\n\n![ssb stickers](&A9se6F6XJl8W7afqNPTpsmlzRMlGUoJmQhgD2I1O0yY=.sha256)\n\n\n\n## Software\n[@Rabble](@THUzexG1y6kWofwiN8Lix/jNH/P6roYdlCDgpAn2HSc=.ed25519) announced that [Planetary has switched to the main Scuttlebutt network](%BJEGR8gr3RGcVbyV62dtRsMUHQ8KPjmyR4bQsfzCiT8=.sha256)\n\nPreviously it was just a bunch of us testing it on a private network.\n\n![planetary screenshot](&BRFZxkoJbZYqCATGotptvEXsCAYx4BnuqFngkHtA5m0=.sha256)\n\niOS users can [sign up for the test-flight beta](https://testflight.apple.com/join/M9hPo1gA). From personal experience I''d suggest you _only_ do this if you''re OK with beta software and willing to file bug reports. I don''t think it''s quite ready for general use. I''ve yet to get a single post to download since the switch, but I assume it''s working for others.\n\n----\n[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) has [managed to get Mentions working well in Patchfox](%wfaROeKo9lyZ9yLQOyAMT32XcLdsnpisoa0ptQpKJKs=.sha256) using  [zurb/tribute: ES6 Native @mentions](https://github.com/zurb/tributez)\n\n![mentions autocomplete in patchfox](&MjxDqdjLD5Nm220KqxJkORaoBs9Hfrixo1kI72sxVTg=.sha256)\n\n[as well as custom urls](%fe7x7HZOiL/GcUptdPs84LH7PGmL3n3NPr6y0eNKVY4=.sha256)\n\n![custom urls working in patchfox gif](&vVA+S91PtHiMFJuOCrC6Pf6KP7X6XVRYb7yBk00rZ14=.sha256)\n\n----\n\npost 2 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1035,replace('[@Sam Macbeth](@u5DuaZVblS3ythuu9OnwRujwHitXlJDOkzEJKgep7M0=.ed25519) notes that [native DAT support has landed in the Cliqz browser](%npfn1DThelXoHIvEFXuGZRAUTrkzWOAGVbe3Sg/ybok=.sha256). You have to turn it on in the settings though.\n\n![dat configuration in cliqz](&fUlWZ07p6j5QvKFpLodoZaxC27oyrLMxY9T9ZG4e7WI=.sha256)\n\n\n## Geeky \n[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) is starting to post some useful geek videos on YouTube in English and Portuguese. \n\n> The content will mostly circle around web, IoT, game development and programming languages stuff.\n\n[There are more details in their post](%J7a1n0SVY2EYm32FtaIh07343WIKhffhO1eFyHdU+fU=.sha256)\n\n![Firefox Add-ons Dev 001.png](&MHT7tF4M0uFnM/i2QwYHOeOy7krH7/zXydtvmi8d6AE=.sha256)\n\n----\n\n[@N Navigator](@z2M8msI2EUubNHnrEJncglDIy2/SUd+36jCyJnfeiHk=.ed25519) is trying to do [SSB Verification from scratch in Ruby](%FCstPHg32VU7oyS2ABZ+UvpZuy46MnIWnLA0NgdIVoo=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519)\ntalks "[...about how we work together, and which pain points Ive experienced working with free and open source software.](%/w5BKSLbSOvZZbpfAToCHZXKj28F6fK21x6RG9Zxak4=.sha256)."\n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis weeks summary was curated from 397 threads by 136 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\npost 3 of 3\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1042,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n[@Riley](@MGtu3A8ogT0HmD55UyYgb47UAu4h8H+w/XxPDg2NWfg=.ed25519) caught [a beautiful sunset](%sFU5qSHCsTdjwxYwTY6KU1P9KhgUGX7kHs3jr0IBFng=.sha256) while walking their dogs. \n\n![a sunset in Melbourne with smooth gradient skies behind a couple skylights and reflective brick covered ground](&jLzU+rxKbsuPdPklY6oElKo3TbONsfEzsxfj0hNmklA=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Daan](@MRiJ+CvDnD9ZjqunY1oy6tsk0IdbMDC4Q3tTC8riS3s=.ed25519) shares some pictures from a deserted [St Laurent of Grenoble](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grenoble_Archaeological_Museum)\n\n![a young woman running over a near-deserted bridge. in the background, quartier St Laurent of Grenoble, with the notable Muse Dauphinois letters at the top of the frame.](&WWCZRbUahqI3Wh1JkxMGSTJp1dfZoKGd3yyxRmkOAV0=.sha256)\n\nThey also reminded us of the value of ["Faerie Rings"](%F005mHU21JN3l5w2uEUWd421lAjBZn7pM8B6q5ZulUI=.sha256) during these times of isolation. \n\n----\n[@Rabble](@THUzexG1y6kWofwiN8Lix/jNH/P6roYdlCDgpAn2HSc=.ed25519) watched folks in their neighborhood driving by, filling bars, and restaurants, and [made them a reminder](%haMWixI8E1//BGYdP1d23qm7nHOyXKQTorHl1xa7L6w=.sha256). \n\n![stay at home sign on a corner lawn in Portland Oregon USA](&2lUcCCmWE450lC34cNwsWD0cMmYIG7sy3XVbfcAzVh0=.sha256)\n\nMeanwhile, they started to connect up all their neighbors so that they could help each other out. \n\n----\n[@Rick](@JfQJYnT2o6lbwIfzNcH4GaR+fymvtXSjdfxrKwrc8SY=.ed25519) shares this picture. \n\n![many people pose for a picture at a party with balloons and music](&tKG8pvzN/SQv1qlRtABlbj4uJDlbhWeZ0RrbAIM4omI=.sha256)\n\nA lot of people are having a hard time, suddenly isolated from all their contacts. It''s good to be reminded that they''re all still there. That we''ll see them again.\n\nIf you''re feeling disconnected, maybe print out a picture of your friends and / or family. Maybe make one a background on your computer.\n\n----\nWhile the world fights a virus [@dangerousbeans](@TXKFQehlyoSn8UJAIVP/k2BjFINC591MlBC2e2d24mA=.ed25519) has been fighting bacteria. \n\n> [@Alchemist](@na1AJv1iWOflQOwsQ4srJJhYynkYawXiWDwM0ln4DgY=.ed25519) began to harbor new, angry life deep in the salty, oily depths of its bilge\n\nThey attacked it with Green Tea and Turmeric. \n\n\n![green tea bags and turmeric cover mechanical devices in a ship''s bilge](&Sml8tOiy9Im+liQsJ+nKoACVaIqMmShp6g+Eu7GWOhY=.sha256)\n\n\n\npost 1 of 2\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1048,replace('## Solarpunk\n[@elavoie](@IgYpd+tCtXnlE2tYX/8rR2AGt+P8svC98WH3MdYAa8Y=.ed25519) shared a post about [artifically generating thermals](%jke9h9PsxkIkEoRrhxHJRA07NyB1Dn9qMya47mnEMj8=.sha256), and links to someone doing it on a house-cooling scale. \n\n![thermal-generator-animated.gif](&4KLdwv8/SSwftNZpahTVvC817yFlbHsFVZF5kbSUOjo=.sha256)\n\n## Community\n[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) discusses the dangers of [purity spirals](%BYQXwYoxU1d+X/YF2KpnAe8F9wLTb11zT/Awd6wwXKE=.sha256).\n\nI think that right now there''s going to be a lot of "us" vs "them" and we have to be on the lookout for behaviors like this.\n\n----\n[@jiangplus](@t5iZ/IQAYnYsGzQdpTKvbLpZnlmUML408BrjsvlwRew=.ed25519) asks \n\n> [How are you affected by CoVID19?](%ttxF3Uf+2OzovC9Dg3QrWzVINWpnpTvlVNwNukrfIX0=.sha256)\n\n\n\n## Software\n[@KawaiiPunk](@LVL4qjvmws3Cxavfi4iCQI6dSOqWqOyq5/5CHImILA8=.ed25519) shares \n\n> Chatting to @Neauoire and I asked them why they dont use SSB anymore and they said because [it uses too much bandwidth](%/JBV2eL02b5xHH47Qyq/GneQroE808KYaw7LFWuQLiQ=.sha256) and living on a boat, that is obviously expensive. So I made and issue [against Oasis] for a low bandwidth mode where downloading blobs is disabled.\n\nThen they took it farther and ran it from the command line in Lynx\n\n![Screenshot from 20200319 022120.png](&6CGiCM+K2UguPRHWcEJO73b/fLSdDYTI+kQ1EK4utME=.sha256)\n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis weeks summary was curated from 239 threads by 83 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\npost 2 of 2\n','\n',char(10)));
