REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1078,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n[@Richard D. Bartlett](@3r4+IyB5NVl2in6QOZHIu9oSrZud+NuVgl2GX3x2WG8=.ed25519) is []looking stylish in their new mask](%1MyUI2VzHOeFXd6xXXOLkwSGossmjNnrs1bo9uwMCC4=.sha256). I just posted about these.  There''s a lot of misinformation out there saying they''re not effective. On average masks like this will get you a six fold reduction in infection. They''ll also protect the people around you in case you are a carrier and don''t know it. [In my post](%1MyUI2VzHOeFXd6xXXOLkwSGossmjNnrs1bo9uwMCC4=.sha256) I share links to articles covering the history of the mask in 1910 through to present day including links to reliable sources and studies of their efficacy. Even one from the CDC from long before Covid-19 talking about how you can use t-shirt material if you have nothing else. \n\n\n![rich with face mask](&SGdhlfY1HDS70HjXOWo+d2D3ZNPKYaBBbaEkiPcKtyQ=.sha256)\n\nWear your masks outside folks. They''re good for you, and good for everyone around you. Make them if you don''t have them.\n\n----\n[@Verdeoliva](@BAqkyL7wJIavl2p6g1yQ9TYYy/1pKM6vSUyDOzZSJ18=.ed25519) shares [some pictures from Spain](%CmFx6RqoRvCODJFdYkUPJ4WNknjpAguGupA7pfSgCwM=.sha256). The post is in Spanish.\n\n![cherry trees blossoming in dry ground](&G0UKLs1ZGZcxn+iwuHAugxS67dZWS3UlGrN3wLFpIjg=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Kathleen Marie](@GSuGLzJa8t3aJCLvs66Ekn7MXdr3yqCSzsd6z2iUEBY=.ed25519) shares [some other blooming flowers](%eg7iFKtYhq6fJc5E1Zp+bO/TijEg18DumRoNb8qEI6M=.sha256) in their neighborhood. \n\n![flower buds and fresh blooms on a green tree bush thing](&C7y2SxPpPZBkTeMrjzXEVPXEmdZw5KtQWODKkhE0Hic=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Daan](@MRiJ+CvDnD9ZjqunY1oy6tsk0IdbMDC4Q3tTC8riS3s=.ed25519) [shares this foffee](%WaOh+W697bMlcKe+jMP7nvZ/CHoVM3c58COHwN7ciO8=.sha256)\n\n![A foffee composed of string beans, eggplants, bell peppers, zucchini and tomato](&EzM2I6NbKiVs8qpiC8THqWfignUEX3POZzIh2Ui9Rpw=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@lucy](@IWEJQ2SPZUnFYHrDBFJmCZlANoyOQfZ9vXimUNbe48M=.ed25519) is [making music "without a computer"](%/qqtKKIKfdVFP7SM+y6qyicYIitQSmiq1nJwzsG4QU8=.sha256)\n\n![many digital sound generation and manipulation devices on a desk](&eoUhjgWV5hTW76KtR6Fs0AomLf4h0Xgo4CmS9jwqbkE=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@scott](@0nakXtVIodBfdHwRQLVb64p54jTWS+DFHRqg58ky4CI=.ed25519) has released [the thirteenth issue of their newsletter](%4W15IO0o1qgiFqEbt/vITRvOejrV2xMXqYh7cwlWgtI=.sha256). \n\n----\n[@not not charlie](@fFtzTNuTSdOkipPqMItnjwl6QjQda5/zIXNqfgGXS2U=.ed25519) shares [some of their woodworking](%zs8ERqQp8DwpDkrFi7hV0xg4zpoEWC/7fxz5OzrAG/A=.sha256)\n\n![carved banner bas-relief in wood](&KDGaTm7veljgOWb6Ru74GzM1iogJtecYkHead3ngjCs=.sha256)\n\n\n\n## Community\n[@scott](@0nakXtVIodBfdHwRQLVb64p54jTWS+DFHRqg58ky4CI=.ed25519) informs us that Scuttlecamp 2 has, unsurprisingly, [been postponed](%WpCvDVrKhhOjsvBIQutoN8gYePcGNAPyFuQxzlZy7O8=.sha256). \n\n----\n\npost 1 of 2\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1089,replace('[@mnin](@SXVoA/7CuMRS5IDTNsO8HU2PvCIVq8HKUUx/k+idDiQ=.ed25519) says \n\n> These times can be triggering or scary, especially for those with traumas/ptsd/depression/chronic conditions. [Im keen to hear what are routines or things that help you keep grounded, not too overloaded](%NcsK5+/v07m1FE7yJnzcC11yoLV7DRxqf5B64DqQOv8=.sha256), and/or just generally how people are doing in these times. Im learning about Polyvagal theory too which is helpful for me...\n\nSome folks have responded with their thoughts, maybe you have some to share, or maybe you''ll find something that helps you. \n\n## Software \n\n[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) is [working on the ability to import an RSS/Atom feed into SSB](%AD18JKTigPcmM4wAKT1BPPRxMJ6Vnr6blgJMM0n1jT8=.sha256).\n\n> Importing a feed is the first feature implemented and is shipping on the next version. It is not a bulk import, Im not interested in doing that as it would spam SSB. What it does is fetch an RSS/Atom and list all the entries in it for you. From that list you can choose a specific post and click the compose new blog post using this content button and youll be moved into the blog compose view with the content from the chosen post converted from HTML into Markdown and placed in the appropriated fields.\n\n![blog import animated gif](&JsyvvENaAtdY52H6ykwNDD/jaDTlc4goCuiooKGvGGA=.sha256)\n\n\n----\n[@cel-desktop](@lOUVT+Phkvai9a/cCS/RKo+S9hnPAQdVixms/7ldpPA=.ed25519) [shared their progress](%aED9KQVEHHLJUTG6f171ZkYBZ/2wvM92UXX2kncehWs=.sha256) on adding a "public web hosting" checkbox to Patchwork.\n\n![patchwork public Web Hosting](&7R2R/vd5eLTybBE6objBO5qvu7r3kAziqtGvrVyTOzk=.sha256)\n\n----\n\n[@Joey Hess](@BCM6DHYJvWzwWi1lFl2tjDXjaqyZAEmJH5ZONSpXhtc=.ed25519) is [working on a "quarantine timer"](%yYMgbDAU2PDd3cZnaI7GuqD48QaXSMu35Dl9n1fuiOo=.sha256) for timing when the things you''ve brought into your house are safe to touch. Go to the web page. Take a picture. Tell it what material, and it''ll start a countdown until that item is safe to touch. \n\n[Webapp here](https://quarantimer.app/). Check out the thread if you''re interested in helping improve it.\n\n\n----\n[@Ladislas](@SmLddSPxpYkJ/8HH8qDycMEwus+tyojjH+a60beRMdg=.ed25519) shares [a post about how to make a blog with Publii and share it on Dat](%JSkpAHXFJ5rRBcWFZlPGyAfzXFTUQQqjOzG28Qa3bRo=.sha256).\n\n\n### Geeky\n\n[@devNull](@FJxH29WOcGbN0SuoasQo/mAXybo0lrMKbZDjpFlSrYs=.ed25519) has been giving [an SSB workshop in spanish](%uykw1pUbnhMlEEYG4ij4Gg4PumvTkU7XissSvVUlhrA=.sha256)\n\n> So, taking advantage of the social isolation thats happening ... I decided to start an ssb workshop aimed at students that go to my university and my career...\n> The idea is to explore ssb tools from a kinda low level approach, trying to grasp some fundamental concepts as Im also making sense of them.\n>Last friday I streamed an intro/first talk where I introduce the ssb protocol and layout my intentions for the workshop.\n\n----\n[@Fred](@9BbJwPDjcyIqrOUPNn0nJZBduWdIrpMk3Cjz5MP361s=.ed25519) shares "[How to use ScuttleButt as messaging layer between ipfs Nodes](%hGZRh3lYDBgaA3RM2gbrppbBgxgWFlnZaxAic0SZAtY=.sha256)"\n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\nThis weeks summary was curated from 356 threads by 125 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\npost 2 of 2\n','\n',char(10)));
