REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1111,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n\n[@Dan Hassan](@NeB4q4Hy9IiMxs5L08oevEhivxW+/aDu/s/0SkNayi0=.ed25519) shares 15 days of progress learning to braid (plait) their little one''s hair. \n\n![day two of learning to braid sprout''s hair](&s7wKVmvNRtrcW0ccRxFxRKWFjbNBQ+EXCyr3apKYvyA=.sha256)\n\nthat comes _after_ they''ve [creeped downstairs to have some quiet me time in the early morning](%uZeG0q8qB+0fnOPVs0JtJW5rJ0AxpwruK1J+wGY2CjA=.sha256)\n\n![image of coffee in a glass plunger with a copper lid and legs. the plunger is about a quarter full. there is a stoneware hasami mug to the left of the plunger and behind there are some plants and a crystal backset by a window. it is dark outside. in the window you see a reflection of the person taking the photo, me. ](&retu4VZWCqa5/wxarSi11pBv4mdOQSsHJwxhgM3G/nk=.sha256)\n\n-----\n[@andrestaltz](@QlCTpvY7p9ty2yOFrv1WU1AE88aoQc4Y7wYal7PFc+w=.ed25519) has started learning how to [_make_ their own food](%AnKHagTxpuzSIhvRbotswGmFfCKrrEmx9slS3MnQJ5U=.sha256) from scratch.\n\n![sources of nutrients for plants in soil versus hydroponics displayed in e-ink on an angled surface](&DLIcrlSfk2J566MzQA68NIeaC7QCxb7hSkcpAMxuNL4=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Rabble](@0uOwBrHIeiRK7lcvpLwjSFkcS3UHSQb/jyN52zf+J6Y=.ed25519) shares [some photos of the many flowers blooming](%n2qY+ybJuH+NHdxmp+0W6EXv7LeM/jmnd4d2PSvVppo=.sha256) around them.\n\n![purple flowers blooming](&amrG00MKwtfR5+LtF+smKzLRFzKhd11ReOPB4IuVsU4=.sha256)\n\nthey also [roasted peeps](%+deUGSOaq6dN4448yAl6Gpi+tuZoGXqOqTqbIVjWcT8=.sha256) when the store ran out of marshmallows.\n\n![two kids sit outdoors under a blanket with a black dog in their lap. a fire burns in a ring before them](&6hOZni2g6SX8BcxJDTQ9piRRIj3/x6bSfCVKTsrYlYY=.sha256)\n\n## Community\n[@hoz](@RtsOc2h1gqh0fRrjrUTHAkRBu9YyDgsD+EWsfLpykrc=.ed25519) shares just [a look at how seriously Puerto Rico''s governor is taking quarantine](%4mDfPddrzD7mwt7N17nei4ys4s8f+cHOWMwyLnZNpyQ=.sha256). Some would definitely call it "excessive". Speaking as an outsider I can''t help but wonder if draconian measures aren''t _precisely_ the correct move for Puerto Rico. I fear if they had an outbreak they would get _zero_ help from the US government. That being said, it seems very hard on the residents. \n\nIt''s a quick post and definitely worth the read if you, like me, haven''t heard about what''s happening there. \n\n## Software\n[@andrestaltz](@QlCTpvY7p9ty2yOFrv1WU1AE88aoQc4Y7wYal7PFc+w=.ed25519) announced [the release of Manyverse 0.2004.4](%jsIQ9KqvQe/R8YtmVzTK/tbghAJNaPrXgMNRfwIdJhQ=.sha256) \n\nin addition to various fixes and improvements it now offers "emoji reactions instead of likes" which sounds interesting.\n\n![screenshot of emoji reactions in manyverse](&regE9xl9BNil6+4vb3jVWRZsSJyrefQzTNrAn0crbDA=.sha256)\n\npost 1 of 2\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1117,replace('[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519) \nhas [released Oasis 2.15.0](%1249ZIXMBdHh2xVE3NuD2cJBgr2utlwg/B6wttfNmb4=.sha256) which includes [Oasis desktop](https://github.com/fraction/oasis-desktop/releases/tag/v1.1.0) :link: and a "threads view" which should be great for long discussions.\n\nMore importantly you should _upgrade immediately_ as there was a security vulnerability in the prior versions.\n\n> We dont have any reason to believe that this flaw was exploited in the wild, but we need to get everyone upgraded out of an abundance of caution.\n\nAlso, you''ll get a bunch of new features and bug fixes if you upgrade, and that''s always nice.\n\nIf any of you are graphics folks with a little time on your hand, maybe you''d like to help work on an icon for the new desktop client. hint. hint.\n\n----\n[@Daan](@MRiJ+CvDnD9ZjqunY1oy6tsk0IdbMDC4Q3tTC8riS3s=.ed25519) shares [their thoughts on Jitsi](%JyEuDV4brvYX8SEcIHts0zhgUjkyWV+ub+99vco2Zv0=.sha256) and getting their family set up with it.\n\n> Overall, I feel like [Jitsi](https://jitsi.org/) is very quickly becoming my favourite videoconferencing solution, and Ive been using quite a few of those recently, as everyone.\n\nConsidering all the recent problems with Zoom, and the poor quality of Google Hangouts, Jitsi is worth considering. It appears to be relatively easy for someone with basic server experience to install, and Digital Ocean has a [one click installer for Jitsi](https://marketplace.digitalocean.com/apps/jitsi-server). You can ignore the version number it claims to install. The [installation script](https://github.com/pachamaltese/jitsi-droplet/blob/master/scripts/01-packages.sh) :link: will always install the _latest_ stable version, whatever that is. \n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis weeks summary was curated from 378 threads by 128 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\npost 2 of 2\n','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(1122,replace('![the weekly - curated posts from the scuttleverse](&Q9wEqKM6UtKmMpI+W17MuwTSNTQpEtSnLvTFrgVI5EE=.sha256)\n\n# Recent Days in Scuttlebutt\n\n## Totally Random\n\n[@umhi](@7x+lsDrIbLkiub2LVN3YHMYZOGY1ZvaJBcxax9qD854=.ed25519) shared [a bunch of pictures of lovely flowers](%T4VhHsipMgvIsyYdzX3FbDxBxckP9B/cqas9VdK6mRI=.sha256) including this Rip Van Winkle Daffodil.\n\n![rip van winkle daffodil](&ZSZaW8tN2qpogD+XzJyt5sy8/NAYmC6dOb0rrYoN1tE=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Beni Grind](@i/gfWqlqxBq9JkYhWIT0whiczxDTySFr9KXVwZgVavw=.ed25519) took their unicycle [down a pretty dirt trail](%5UVVSkNwkIy1THWAM9C0n/960bZgXMdoWpYbzTOPhJs=.sha256). \n\n![a unicycle hangs from a wooden fence. a rocky dirt path stretches out through green pastures to a mountainous distance](&3l5c+C+9ylrTo+8YYrg1Vhpk9p/tGd209tgbNwZfzvk=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@Rabble](@0uOwBrHIeiRK7lcvpLwjSFkcS3UHSQb/jyN52zf+J6Y=.ed25519) shared a picture of the unipiper demonstrating significant personal protective measures.\n\n![the unipiper rides a unicycle while playing a flaming bagpipe in a gas mask and plastic suit.](&eww1wlcE/M8o7ovMaIgPZMDjQszXlUcwYkbvfPE8GjI=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@hoodownr](@YND2Cb9uk3ZdFyzXpaXDH5HZ9udu+qjg4MhNcynK2RE=.ed25519) drew [a surprised man in a sound booth](%WfblU/+n2QQtITQ8MWL0SFnYMoY/u7KLjb0I+pMLkew=.sha256)\n\n![herbert''s song drawing by hoodownr](&DTW79YXTrwT+TgKUKvL/jjY++OgdcDZyGI2YArRLNhI=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@not not charlie](@fFtzTNuTSdOkipPqMItnjwl6QjQda5/zIXNqfgGXS2U=.ed25519)\n [sharpened their own saw](%HQdUBxdbj0tnPwOHnmIF6A1yNaMPK+TmtU+2YcsT6QA=.sha256). \n\n![a saw in a vice](&HKRV1rPq6effwihLaRdo14p4BS4wL4/BoBjKHWS0abw=.sha256)\n\n----\n[@David Gmez](@XO687hcrkcQg2S+huhLOYK2WYmBgaVXbiNF2FNpdq3g=.ed25519) shared [adorable dog pictures](%rv2YJcJp6zJUrMkFAXW3ixwQTwCftQBu1LFiT682s0E=.sha256) in a sad story about the power of diabetes.\n\n![small dog Running towards photographer over brown grass](&k8eLyFPNUtEAtl8r92lJooVDMihdMSWAli8H6vAjyhI=.sha256)\n\n\n\n\n## Software \n[@SoapDog (SPX)](@0xkjAty6RSr5uhbAvi0rbVR2g9Bz+89qiKth48ECQBE=.ed25519) has announced [Project Moon Hermit](%/v7WBnJiNuvATx9X08da/cMzgH1TFo1lVp/eStdT5Q0=.sha256)\n\n![project moon hermit](&JL4n8pLaqievH1eCfSp5+arC6N329JRb5hTp1TpMCEo=.sha256)\n\n\n> It is a new SSB client of sorts. It is not exactly a client but a version of Lua 5.3 that contains an embedded SSB client inside it. It was built by picking #sbotc by @cel and grafting #lua into it.\n\n\nIt''s still very early stages and there''s lots of geeky stuff in the post for those who are curious.\n\n\n[@kas](@RuNxm8SRujPcJx6GjtTQHp6hprAFv5voEkcvoAkB8Pk=.ed25519) shares ["Phetch" a command line gopher client](%rB8LZn7Qoe1OlFWCbOto1gEmFA5+9OkLuLzXX1b9bEM=.sha256). \n\n![phetch-start.png](&W1goktmim+bIaFZWLW+B3ezGxYKEIG1pnt5wG1wct3w=.sha256)\n\n\n\n------------\n### Summary Data\n\nThis weeks summary was curated from 403 threads by 135 authors by [@masukomi](@LzTjF5eAVC6xprPMGeNzqEP/EEBIGpM6hDaaY10hrz8=.ed25519), **with the support of my lovely patrons**. If you''d like to help continue this creation you can [become a patron on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/the_weekly).\n\n\n\n','\n',char(10)));
