REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3186,replace('# 2019-11-03\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Ethiopian clashes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Ethiopian_clashes)\n    *   The death toll of recent clashes in the [Oromia Region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oromia_Region) of [Ethiopia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopia) rises to 86. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ethiopia-politics/ethiopia-pm-abiy-says-death-toll-from-recent-protests-rises-to-86-idUSKBN1XD0F6)\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   Four people are injured at a mall as a knife-wielding man attacks a crowd in Hong Kong. The suspect, a [pro-Beijing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pro-Beijing_camp_(Hong_Kong)) [Mandarin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandarin_Chinese) speaker, is subdued and arrested by police. [(BBC News)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-50281914)\n*   [Taliban insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban_insurgency)\n    *   At least nine Afghan security forces are killed in clashes with [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) forces in northeastern [Afghanistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan). [(WION)](https://www.wionews.com/south-asia/nine-afghan-security-officers-killed-in-taliban-ambush-259707)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Saudi Vision 2030](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Vision_2030)\n    *   [Saudi Aramco](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Aramco) announces it will go public on the [Riyadh stock exchange](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tadawul), with [shares](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Share_(finance)) totalling up to two percent of the firm''s worth made available at its [IPO](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Initial_public_offering) launch. Valued at [US$](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_dollar)1.2 trillion, the company is being partially privatized to reduce the [kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia)''s [economic dependence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Economy_of_Saudi_Arabia) on oil. [(BBC News)](https://www.bbc.com/news/business-50070823)\n*   [McDonald''s](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McDonald%27s) CEO [Steve Easterbrook](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Easterbrook) is fired for having a relationship with an employee. Current company president [Chris Kempczinski](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Kempczinski) immediately assumes his position. [(BBC News)](https://www.bbc.com/news/business-50283720)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   Thirty-three people are injured, four critically, when a [FlixBus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FlixBus) overturns at an exit near [Amiens](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amiens), [France](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France). [(BBC News)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50283112)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Venezuelan presidential crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Venezuelan_presidential_crisis)\n    *   Following similar measures by [Argentina](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argentina) last month, the government of [El Salvador](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El_Salvador) expels diplomats of the government of [Venezuela](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Venezuela) led by [Nicols Maduro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicol%C3%A1s_Maduro). [(BBC News)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-50279917)\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   Protestors storm the [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) consulate in [Karbala](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karbala), where they set fires around the building and replaced the [Iranian flag](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flag_of_Iran) with an [Iraqi one](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flag_of_Iraq). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/iraqi-protesters-attack-iran-consulate-karbala-191103232545555.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_3','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3187,replace('# 2019-11-05\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Yemeni Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemeni_Civil_War_(2015%E2%80%93present)), [Yemeni peace process](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemeni_peace_process)\n    *   [Yemen](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemen) and the [Southern Transitional Council](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_Transitional_Council) sign a power-sharing deal in [Riyadh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riyadh), [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia), to put an end to infighting between the two groups in [Aden](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aden). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/peace-deal-announced-yemeni-government-separatists-191105145143441.html)\n*   [Mexican Drug War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexican_Drug_War)\n    *   [2019 Sonora massacre](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Sonora_massacre)\n        *   [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) offers [Mexico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico) [military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Armed_Forces) support to help defeat [drug cartels](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_cartel), should his counterpart [Andrs Manuel Lpez Obrador](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9s_Manuel_L%C3%B3pez_Obrador) request help, after nine [American Mexican](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Mexican) [Mormon fundamentalists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_of_the_Firstborn_(LeBaron_order)), including six children, are killed in an ambush by suspected cartel members in [Sonora](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonora), northern Mexico. [(_The Independent_)](https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/trump-mexico-war-us-army-troops-drug-cartels-twitter-a9185881.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [LGBT rights in the Cook Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_rights_in_the_Cook_Islands)\n    *   The [Cook Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cook_Islands) announces it will retain its ban on [homosexual](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homosexuality) [practises by men](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gay_sexual_practices) and that it will be [extended to women](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesbian_sexual_practices) as well. Homosexuals face up to seven years of imprisonment on the islands. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/402530/cook-islands-retains-ban-on-homosexuality)\n*   [Crime in Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crime_in_Italy)\n    *   Three [firefighters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Firefighter) are killed while two others and a [policeman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_Italy) are injured after an explosion at an abandoned farm building in [Quargnento](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quargnento), [Piedmont](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Piedmont), [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy). The explosion was caused by two bombs placed by unknown people, and his suspected that the target of the attack were the owners of the building. [(_Il Messaggero_)](https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/alessandria_esplosione_cascina_casa_morti_vigili_fuoco_oggi_5_novembre_2019-4842506.html)\n*   [Murder of Ana Krigel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murder_of_Ana_Kri%C3%A9gel)\n    *   An [Irish](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Irish_people) judge sentences two 15-year-old boys to jail for the 2018 murder of 14-year-old Ana Krigel in suburban [Dublin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dublin). The boys were 13-years-old at the time they murdered her and are the youngest people convicted of murder in [Ireland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_Ireland). They have not been named due to their age. One boy was sentenced to [life in detention](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_imprisonment) to be reviewed after twelve yearshe was also sentenced to eight years for [sexual assault](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_assault) to run concurrently with the murder sentence. The other boy was sentenced to 15 years in prison, but his sentence will be reviewed after eight years instead of twelve. Her parents said that "justice has been served for Ana", but about the sentences that "forever is not long enough". [(RTE)](https://www.rte.ie/news/ireland/2019/1105/1088699-kriegel-sentencing/) [(RTE2)](https://www.rte.ie/news/courts/2019/1105/1088828-ana-kriegel/)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Impeachment inquiry against Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_against_Donald_Trump)\n    *   [Gordon Sondland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gordon_Sondland), the [United States Ambassador to the European Union](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Ambassador_to_the_European_Union), reverses his previous testimony, admitting to a _[quid pro quo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quid_pro_quo)_ in the withholding of military aid for [Ukraine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine). [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/05/us/politics/impeachment-trump.html)\n*   [2019 Virginia elections](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Virginia_elections), [2019 Kentucky gubernatorial election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Kentucky_gubernatorial_election)\n    *   Democrats win majorities in both houses of the [Virginia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia) [General Assembly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia_General_Assembly) ([Senate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Senate_of_Virginia) and [House](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia_House_of_Delegates)), resulting in Democratic [trifecta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_trifecta) control of the [governorship](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Governor_of_Virginia) and General Assembly for the first time since 1993. Democratic [Kentucky Attorney General](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attorney_General_of_Kentucky) [Andy Beshear](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andy_Beshear) defeats Republican incumbent [Matt Bevin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matt_Bevin) to win the [governorship](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Governor_of_Kentucky) of Kentucky. [(Vox)](https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2019/11/5/20944109/virginia-elections-legislature-results-democrats) [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/polls-open-in-virginia-balance-of-power-in-state-government-is-at-stake/2019/11/05/bdb57972-ff5b-11e9-8501-2a7123a38c58_story.html) [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2019/11/05/politics/virginia-election-democrats-control/index.html)\n*   [Elections in New York (state)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elections_in_New_York_(state))\n    *   [New York City](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_City) becomes the largest city in the United States to adopt [ranked-choice voting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranked-choice_voting). [(Vox)](https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2019/11/5/20948376/new-york-election-results-ranked-choice-voting) [(_The Hill_)](https://thehill.com/homenews/state-watch/469167-new-york-city-to-adopt-ranked-choice-voting)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_5','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3188,replace('# 2019-11-07\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A [Cirrus SR22](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cirrus_SR22) crashes into a house in [Upland, California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Upland,_California), killing the pilot. [(_Los Angeles Times_)](https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2019-11-07/aircraft-crashes-into-home-in-upland-sparking-fire-officials-say)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [United States withdrawal from the Paris Agreement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_withdrawal_from_the_Paris_Agreement)\n    *   [Tuvaluan Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Tuvalu) [Kausea Natano](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kausea_Natano) bemoans the [United States withdrawal from the Paris Agreement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_withdrawal_from_the_Paris_Agreement), saying it will undermine U.S. credibility in the [Pacific](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Ocean) region. [(Radio New Zealand)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/402721/us-will-lose-pacific-influence-over-paris-decision-forum)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [LGBT rights in Malaysia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_rights_in_Malaysia)\n    *   Five [Malaysian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaysians) men are sentenced to six months in jail, fined, and caned for "attempting gay sex". [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-malaysia-lgbt/malaysia-sentences-five-men-to-jail-caning-and-fines-for-gay-sex-idUSKBN1XH197)\n*   The [International Criminal Court](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Criminal_Court) sentences [Bosco Ntaganda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bosco_Ntaganda) to 30 years in prison for war crimes as leader of the [National Congress for the Defence of the People](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Congress_for_the_Defence_of_the_People) which operated in the [Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/icc-set-sentence-congolese-rebel-chief-bosco-ntaganda-191107065841913.html)\n*   [2019 Bolivian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_protests)\n    *   The mayor of [Vinto](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vinto), Patricia Arce of the ruling [MAS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Movement_for_Socialism_(Bolivia)) party, is attacked by opposition protesters who dragged her through the streets barefoot, covered her in red paint and forcibly cut her hair. [(BBC News)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-50332167)\n    *   Limbert Guzman, a 20-year-old student, is killed following clashes between supporters and opponents of [Bolivian President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Bolivia) [Evo Morales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evo_Morales). [(Voice of America)](https://www.voanews.com/americas/bolivia-clashes-third-person-killed-disputed-election)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Mauritian general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Mauritian_general_election)\n    *   Citizens of [Mauritius](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mauritius) cast their vote in the country''s latest [parliamentary election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elections_in_Mauritius). [(Foreign Brief)](https://www.foreignbrief.com/daily-news/indian-ocean-island-nation-of-mauritius-heads-to-the-polls-for-parliamentary-election/)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_7','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3189,replace('# 2019-11-08\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A 5.9-magnitude earthquake strikes 60 km (35 miles) from [Hashtrud](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hashtrud), [East Azerbaijan Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Azerbaijan_Province), in northwestern [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran), killing at least six and injuring more than 300. The [United States Geological Survey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Geological_Survey) warns that "significant casualties are likely and the disaster is potentially widespread". [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/deadly-magnitude-59-earthquake-hits-northwestern-iran-191108011507464.html)\n*   An explosion in a mine in [Teutschenthal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teutschenthal), [Saxony-Anhalt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saxony-Anhalt), [Germany](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany), injures two workers and traps around 30 underground in a secure area. All are rescued several hours later. [(Deutsche Welle)](https://www.dw.com/en/germany-workers-trapped-underground-after-mine-explosion/a-51165862)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   A [federal judge](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_judge) orders the immediate release of former [Brazilian President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Brazil) [Luiz Incio Lula da Silva](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luiz_In%C3%A1cio_Lula_da_Silva). [(Reuters)](https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-brazil-corruption-court-lula/brazil-judge-orders-ex-president-lula-released-from-prison-idUKKBN1XI2AE)\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   A student from Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (HKUST), named Chow Tsz-lok, died after suffering brain damage following a fall during anti-government protests. [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/08/hong-kong-protests-student-who-fell-from-parking-lot-during-demonstrations-dies) [(The New York Times)](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/07/world/asia/hong-kong-protest-student-dies.html)\n*   [Impeachment inquiry against Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_against_Donald_Trump)\n    *   During her testimony before [U.S. House](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_of_Representatives) investigators last month in the [impeachment inquiry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_against_Donald_Trump) into [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump), [Fiona Hill](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiona_Hill_(presidential_advisor)), President Trump''s former top adviser on [Russia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia) and [Europe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Europe), said that she received death threats, "hateful calls", and was the subject of false "[conspiracy theories](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conspiracy_theory)" as part of a targeted harassment campaign she claims was implemented after she agreed to cooperate with the inquiry on impeachment, according to a deposition transcript. [(NBC News)](https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/trump-impeachment-inquiry/former-trump-adviser-who-testified-ukraine-pressure-campaign-said-she-n1078726)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey)''s [Interior Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_the_Interior_(Turkey)) [Sleyman Soylu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S%C3%BCleyman_Soylu) announces that his country will begin repatriating [ISIL](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant) prisoners on Monday. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-security-turkey-islamic-state/turkey-says-will-begin-repatriation-of-islamic-state-prisoners-on-monday-anadolu-idUSKBN1XI1G3)\n*   Under pressure of sanctions by [ECOWAS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECOWAS), newly appointed [Prime Minister of Guinea-Bissau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Guinea-Bissau) [Faustino Imbali](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faustino_Imbali) resigns. [(Yahoo News)](https://news.yahoo.com/guinea-bissau-newly-appointed-pm-210456853.html)\n*   [2019 Bolivian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_protests)\n    *   Several dozen policemen were seen joining the protests against Evo Morales'' government in at least three cities. Bolivia''s defence minister stated that no "military measures" would be taken against the policemen, but added that he would "get" the disobedient officers. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bolivia-election/bolivian-police-seen-joining-scattered-anti-morales-protests-idUSKBN1XI20M) [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/09/bolivian-police-mutiny-in-opposition-to-evo-morales)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_8','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3190,replace('# 2019-11-09\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Chilean protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Chilean_protests)\n    *   Overnight, protesters forcibly storm the [Argentine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argentina) [embassy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embassy) in [Santiago](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santiago) and [set it on fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arson) because of the [Argentine government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argentine_government)''s support for [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Chile) [Sebastin Piera](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sebasti%C3%A1n_Pi%C3%B1era). Ambassador [Jos Octavio Bordn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jos%C3%A9_Octavio_Bord%C3%B3n) is unharmed and now considering moving the embassy. [(MDZol in Spanish)](https://www.mdzol.com/mundo/bordon-fue-muy-duro-ingresaron-rompiendo-todos-los-vidrios-20191109-51612.html)\n*   [2019 Bolivian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_protests)\n    *   [Police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_Bolivia) guards outside Bolivia''s presidential palace abandoned their posts and join the protest against [Evo Morales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evo_Morales). [(Associated Press)](https://apnews.com/336592adf2524dc3a582a95ec9372f5f) [(Fox News)](https://www.foxnews.com/world/police-join-protesters-abandon-their-posts-outside-bolivias-presidential-palace)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [Bushfires in Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bushfires_in_Australia)\n    *   The bodies of three people killed by bushfires in [Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia) are found  two near [Glen Innes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glen_Innes,_New_South_Wales), and one at [Johns River](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johns_River,_New_South_Wales)  as fires that have destroyed at least 150 houses continue to burn in eastern [New South Wales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_South_Wales) and [Queensland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queensland). [(_The Sydney Morning Herald_)](https://www.smh.com.au/national/nsw/nsw-bushfires-live-firefighters-to-assess-damage-amid-unprecedented-emergency-20191109-p538ye.html)\n*   Half a million people are evacuated from the [Bangladesh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladesh) coastal area in preparation for the landfall of [Cyclone Bulbul](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclone_Bulbul). [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2019/11/09/asia/cyclone-bulbul-bangladesh-eastern-india-intl/)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Ayodhya dispute](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ayodhya_dispute)\n    *   The [Supreme Court of India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supreme_Court_of_India) rules in favor of [Hindus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hindus) over a place of worship that has been the center of disputes between them and the [Muslim community](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islam_in_India) in the country. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-india-religion-temple-explainer/indian-court-rules-in-favor-of-hindus-in-explosive-row-with-muslims-idUSKBN1XJ01Z)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [President of Sierra Leone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Sierra_Leone) [Julius Maada Bio](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julius_Maada_Bio) calls for urgent action on [Guinea-Bissau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guinea-Bissau) to "avoid a [civil war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civil_war)". He makes the statement before the Chairman of [ECOWAS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECOWAS), [Nigerien](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger) [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Niger) [Mahamadou Issoufou](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahamadou_Issoufou). [(The Patriotic Vanguard)](http://www.thepatrioticvanguard.com/sierra-leone-s-president-julius-maada-bio-calls-for-urgent-action-on-guinea-bissau)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_9','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3191,replace('# 2019-11-14\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Ford](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ford) announces that its new electric [SUV](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SUV) will be known as the [Mustang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mustang) Mach-E. The "Mustang" model name, previously employed by Ford''s muscle cars, could be an important asset for the new venture. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ford-motor-electric-mustang/ford-to-use-mustang-name-for-electric-suv-idUSKBN1XO1HT?il=0)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A vehicle collision in [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran)''s southeastern [Sistan and Baluchestan Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sistan_and_Baluchestan_Province) kills at least 28 people, all [Afghan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan) nationals. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-50422965)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Saugus High School shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saugus_High_School_shooting)\n    *   A [school shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/School_shooting) at [Saugus High School](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saugus_High_School_(California)) in [Santa Clarita, California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Clarita,_California), United States, injures [five](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_shooting) students, two fatally. The 16-year-old gunman, identified as Nathaniel Berhow, shoots himself but survives. [(New York Post)](https://nypost.com/2019/11/14/police-responding-to-report-of-school-shooting-in-california/)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   Chief Superintendent of Police of [Hong Kong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong) Tse Chun-chung says protesters'' acts are "another step closer to [terrorism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism)". [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-protests/hong-kong-students-arm-themselves-for-showdown-as-police-take-breather-idUSKBN1XO06C)\n*   [JapanSouth Korea relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93South_Korea_relations)\n    *   [South Korean government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korean_government) officials announce that [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) and the United States are interested in renewing the [GSOMIA](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93South_Korea_General_Security_of_Military_Information_Agreement) pact between Japan and [South Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea) to maintain bilateral cooperation between the two nations in defense issues. [(Yonhap Korean Agency)](https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20191114003351325?section=national/diplomacy)\n*   [2019 Bolivian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_protests), [2019 Bolivian political crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_political_crisis)\n    *   Bolivian police used [tear gas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tear_gas) to break up a peaceful pro-Morales counter-protest in La Paz. Following this, it blocked about a dozen pro-Morales senators from entering the nation''s legislature, upon which pro-Morales demonstrators responded with cries of "[dictatorship](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dictatorship)" and by throwing stones at the riot policemen. [(The New York Times)](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/13/world/americas/bolivia-morales-news.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_14','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3192,replace('# 2019-11-15\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   The [Iranian government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_the_Islamic_Republic_of_Iran) announces that, effective immediately, [petrol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gasoline) will be rationed to 60 litres per month, and prices will increase 50%. Fuel beyond the limit will cost double. Iranians take to the street to oppose the price hikes, which result from [American sanctions in response to Iran''s nuclear program](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_sanctions_against_Iran). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/ajimpact/petrol-rationing-price-hikes-iranians-surprise-191115155053008.html) [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/15/world/middleeast/iran-gasoline-prices-rations.html)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [North Korean abductions of Japanese citizens](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Korean_abductions_of_Japanese_citizens), [JapanNorth Korea relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93North_Korea_relations)\n    *   [Sakie Yokota](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yokota_family), the mother of a [Japanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_people) girl abducted by [North Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Korea) 42 years ago at the age of 13, appeals directly to [Kim Jong-un](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Jong-un) to release her and all Japanese abductees. She also decries the lack of [Japanese government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_government) action on the issue. [(NHK)](https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20191115_17/)\n*   [JapanSouth Korea relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93South_Korea_relations), [JapanUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93United_States_relations), [South KoreaUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea%E2%80%93United_States_relations)\n    *   Japan, [South Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea) and the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) agree to boost multilateral military cooperation and defense issues. [(Yonhap Korean Agency)](https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20191115004300325)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   A 70-year-old bystander dies after being hit by a brick in clashes between local residents and brick-throwing [protesters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protester). [Police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong_Police_Force) investigate the act as [murder](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murder). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-50428704) [(_South China Morning Post_)](https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3037927/hong-kong-protests-police-treat-death-70-year-old-cleaner)\n    *   [Pro-Beijing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pro-Beijing) Hong Kong Justice Secretary [Teresa Cheng](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teresa_Cheng_(politician)) is "assaulted by a crowd" and "sustains an injury" in [London](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London). China''s Foreign Ministry condemns the protesters. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-protests-diplomacy/china-strongly-condemns-attack-on-hong-kong-government-official-in-london-idUSKBN1XP0BM?il=0) [(_South China Morning Post_)](https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3037830/hong-kong-justice-secretary-teresa-cheng-injured-london-while)\n*   [2019 Chilean protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Chilean_protests)\n    *   An agreement is signed by most of the political parties supporting a referendum in April 2020 regarding the draft of a new constitution through a [constituent convention](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constituent_assembly). This will be the first time the [Constitution of Chile](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitution_of_Chile) is written with popular participation. [(Cooperativa)](https://www.cooperativa.cl/noticias/pais/manifestaciones/historico-los-chilenos-definiran-en-plebiscito-si-hay-nueva/2019-11-15/012059.html)\n*   [Criminal charges brought in the Special Counsel investigation (20172019)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Criminal_charges_brought_in_the_Special_Counsel_investigation_(2017%E2%80%932019))\n    *   A federal jury convicts [Roger Stone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roger_Stone) of lying to the [United States Congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Congress) and tampering with a witness about his efforts to learn about the anti-secrecy group [WikiLeaks](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WikiLeaks)''s release of [hacked Democratic emails](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2016_Democratic_National_Committee_email_leak) in the [2016 U.S. presidential election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2016_United_States_elections). [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/public-safety/roger-stone-jury-weighs-evidence-and-a-defense-move-to-make-case-about-mueller/2019/11/15/554fff5a-06ff-11ea-8292-c46ee8cb3dce_story.html)\n*   [2019 Bolivian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_protests)\n    *   Security forces open fire on protesters in [Cochabamba](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cochabamba), killing at least five. [(CBC)](https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/bolivia-protests-deaths-1.5362104)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_15','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3193,replace('# 2019-11-17\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   Clashes erupt on the campus of [Hong Kong Polytechnic University](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong_Polytechnic_University). Police use [tear gas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tear_gas) and [water cannons](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Water_cannon). Protesters fire [bows and arrows](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bow_and_arrow) and [petrol bombs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petrol_bomb), and [set fires](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arson). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-protests/hong-kong-campus-protesters-fire-bows-and-arrows-set-fires-idUSKBN1XQ0OJ?il=0)\n    *   [Democracy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democracy) activist [Joshua Wong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joshua_Wong) urges Germany to stop military assistance to [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China). [(_Outlook_)](https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/hong-kong-activist-urges-germany-to-halt-chinese-army-training/1664857)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A [gas explosion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gas_explosion) in [Chittagong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chittagong), [Bangladesh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladesh), kills at least seven people and injures eight. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bangladesh-blast/at-least-seven-killed-in-gas-explosion-in-bangladesh-idUSKBN1XR06K)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   In response to a [measles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Measles) outbreak, [Samoa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samoa) declares a [state of emergency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_of_emergency), closes all schools and urges all persons under 17 to avoid public gatherings. [(ABC News)](https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-11-17/samoa-declares-state-of-emergency-over-measles-outbreak/11711576)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [201819 Korean peace process](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018%E2%80%9319_Korean_peace_process)\n    *   [U.S.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) [Defense Secretary](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Secretary_of_Defense) [Mark Esper](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Esper) and [South Korean](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea) [Minister of National Defense](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_National_Defense_(South_Korea)) [Jeong Kyeong-doo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeong_Kyeong-doo) announce that their countries will postpone their annual joint [military air exercises](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military_exercise) to help facilitate the peace process. [(_San Francisco Chronicle_)](https://www.sfchronicle.com/news/us/article/US-S-Korea-postpone-joint-exercise-criticized-by-14841116.php)\n*   [JapanUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93United_States_relations), [JapanNorth Korea relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93North_Korea_relations)\n    *   Japanese [Defence Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defence_Minister) [Tar Kno](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tar%C5%8D_K%C5%8Dno) tells his United States and South Korea counterparts that "no one could be optimistic about North Korea" after "they launched over 20 missiles so far this year". [(Yahoo! News)](https://news.yahoo.com/japan-tells-u-no-one-070921616.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Fresno party shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fresno_party_shooting)\n    *   [At least ten](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_shooting) people are shot, with four killed, at a backyard party in [Fresno, California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fresno,_California). [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2019/11/18/us/fresno-mass-shooting-football-party/index.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Belarusian parliamentary election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Belarusian_parliamentary_election)\n    *   Voters in [Belarus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belarus) head to the polls in the country''s latest parliamentary election. The election is closely watched by the [Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization_for_Security_and_Co-operation_in_Europe) due to the country''s poor [human rights record](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights_in_Belarus). [(Deutsche Welle)](https://www.dw.com/en/belarus-holds-parliamentary-polls-as-lukashenko-balances-russia-and-the-west/a-51282093)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_17','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3194,replace('# 2019-11-21\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Bolivian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_protests)\n    *   [Bolivian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_Bolivia) [riot police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riot_police) fire [tear gas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tear_gas) to break up a [funeral procession](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funeral_procession) that had turned into massive anti-[government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Bolivia) protest. [(France 24)](https://www.france24.com/en/20191121-police-break-up-bolivia-funeral-protest-as-congress-meets-on-elections) [(International Business Times)](https://www.ibtimes.com/police-break-bolivia-funeral-protest-congress-meets-elections-2871174) [(Reuters)](https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-bolivia-politics/supporters-of-bolivias-morales-march-with-coffins-of-dead-protesters-idUKKBN1XV1P5)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   Two [USAF](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Air_Force) airmen are killed when [two planes collide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mid-air_collision) at [Vance Air Force Base](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vance_Air_Force_Base) in [Enid, Oklahoma](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enid,_Oklahoma), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States). [(Associated Press)](https://www.abc12.com/content/news/Vance-Air-Force-Base-Okla-says-2-aircraft-involved-in-mishap-565283912.html)\n*   An explosion at a [fireworks](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fireworks) factory in the town of [Barcellona Pozzo di Gotto](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barcellona_Pozzo_di_Gotto), [Sicily](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sicily), [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy), kills five people and injures two others. [(Sky News)](https://news.sky.com/story/five-people-killed-in-explosion-at-fireworks-factory-in-sicily-11866146)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Cross-Strait relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross-Strait_relations)\n    *   After the [running mate for the presidency of Taiwan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Taiwan_presidential_election) for [Tsai Ing-wen](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsai_Ing-wen), [William Lai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Lai), says he supports [Taiwanese independence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taiwanese_independence), [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) condemns the move as a "disaster" which crosses a red line China is not willing to accept. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-taiwan-election/china-says-taiwan-courting-disaster-after-pre-election-comment-on-independence-idUSKBN1XV0LU)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   The [Hong Kong High Court](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong_High_Court) denies the lift of a travel ban imposed on [pro-democracy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pro-democracy) activist [Joshua Wong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joshua_Wong), who was scheduled to travel to the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom) to receive a [human rights](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights) award from the two houses of the [British Parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Parliament). The judge cites the risk of absconding and says he can remain in the city to help restore peace. [(_The Independent_)](http://theindependent.sg/hk-court-forbids-joshua-wong-from-traveling-to-london-to-receive-human-rights-award-from-british-parliament/)\n*   [2019 Chilean protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Chilean_protests)\n    *   [Amnesty International](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amnesty_International) releases a report regarding [human rights violations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights_violations) committed by the [Carabineros](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carabineros_de_Chile) and the [Armed Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chilean_Armed_Forces) against peaceful protesters. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-chile-protests-amnesty-idUSKBN1XV1J1?taid=5dd6b27cbd53880001eb7034)\n*   [Investigations involving Benjamin Netanyahu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Investigations_involving_Benjamin_Netanyahu)\n    *   [Prime Minister of Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Israel) [Benjamin Netanyahu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benjamin_Netanyahu) is officially indicted by [Attorney General](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attorney_General_of_Israel) [Avichai Mandelblit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avichai_Mandelblit) for bribery, fraud, and breach of trust. Netanyahu protests the allegations as being part of a political "[witch-hunt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witch-hunt)" against him. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/21/israeli-prime-minister-benjamin-netanyahu-indicted-for-bribery-and)\n*   [2019 Iranian fuel protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iranian_fuel_protests)\n    *   The [Supreme National Security Council](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supreme_National_Security_Council) gradually restores the internet to some [provinces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Provinces_of_Iran) and parts of [Tehran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tehran), after [shutting it off](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_outage) nationwide five days ago to counteract protests. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/iran-loosens-internet-restrictions-protest-shutdown-191121195539005.html)\n*   Nine [Extinction Rebellion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extinction_Rebellion) protesters are arrested for storming U.S. House of Representatives Speaker [Nancy Pelosi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nancy_Pelosi)s office. [(_Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/climate-environment/2019/11/21/nine-climate-activists-arrested-after-storming-nancy-pelosis-office/)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Vanuatu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vanuatu) backtracks on a controversial law that would have allowed immigration authorities to [racially profile](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Racial_profiling) and closely follow people from the [Middle East](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_East). [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/403853/vanuatu-backtracks-on-special-profiling-immigration-policy)\n*   [2019 Colombian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Colombian_protests)\n    *   Thousands of protestors take to the streets in [Colombia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombia) demanding the resignation of [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Colombia) [Ivn Duque Mrquez](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iv%C3%A1n_Duque_M%C3%A1rquez). The protests were instigated over controversial tax and labor reforms proposed by [Congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congress_of_Colombia), murders of indigenous leaders, and the governments failure to implement the [FARC](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Revolutionary_Armed_Forces_of_Colombia) [peace deal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombian_peace_process). [(_Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/with-nationwide-strike-colombia-joins-south-americas-season-of-protest/2019/11/21/2d3adf0e-0bef-11ea-8054-289aef6e38a3_story.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_21','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3195,replace('# 2019-11-22\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [ChinaUnited States trade war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China%E2%80%93United_States_trade_war)\n    *   The U.S. [Federal Communications Commission](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Communications_Commission) (FCC) unanimously votes to label Chinese telecommunications giants [Huawei](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huawei) and [ZTE](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ZTE) as national security risks, thereby disqualifying them from the [Universal Service Fund](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Universal_Service_Fund). In a separate vote, the FCC mandates that [national wireless carriers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_United_States_wireless_communications_service_providers) remove both companies'' products from their existing networks. The companies have 30 days to appeal. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-china-huawei-tech/fcc-votes-5-0-to-bar-chinas-huawei-zte-from-government-subsidy-program-idUSKBN1XW1TC)\n*   [2019 JapanSouth Korea trade dispute](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Japan%E2%80%93South_Korea_trade_dispute)\n    *   [South Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea) halts its [World Trade Organization](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Trade_Organization) complaint concerning [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan)''s tightened export controls of key chemicals South Korea uses for [computer chips](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_chip) and displays. [(Voice of America)](https://www.voanews.com/east-asia-pacific/south-korea-reverses-course-will-still-share-intel-japan)\n*   [Amazon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_(company)) files a lawsuit against the [United States Department of Defense](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense) for awarding a [US$](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._dollar)10 billion [cloud computing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_computing) contract to [Microsoft](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft). The company had previously accused the Department of bias in their decision, given CEO [Jeff Bezos](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeff_Bezos) has been a vocal critic of [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-amazon-com-pentagon-microsoft/amazon-files-lawsuit-contesting-pentagons-10-billion-cloud-contract-to-microsoft-idUSKBN1XX00M?il=0)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [Samoa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samoa) confirms that 20 persons, mostly children, have died of [measles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Measles), and 11 more are in critical condition. Authorities recorded 1,644 cases since the outbreak began last month. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/403902/samoa-measles-death-toll-hits-20-eleven-children-critical)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Chagos Archipelago sovereignty dispute](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chagos_Archipelago_sovereignty_dispute)\n    *   The [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom) misses a [United Nations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations) deadline to return control of the disputed [Chagos Archipelago](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chagos_Archipelago) to [Mauritius](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mauritius), prompting the [government of Mauritius](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Mauritius) to call the UK an "illegal [colonial occupier](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colonialism)". [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-50511847)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Murder of Grace Millane](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murder_of_Grace_Millane)\n    *   After a three-week trial, a 27-year-old New Zealand man is found guilty of murdering 22-year-old British tourist Grace Millane in [Auckland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Auckland) in December 2018. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-essex-50512163)\n*   Former [Paraguayan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paraguay) [Congresswoman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congress_of_Paraguay) Cynthia Tarrag is arrested alongside her husband at [Newark Liberty International Airport](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newark_Liberty_International_Airport) in [Newark, New Jersey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newark,_New_Jersey) and charged with [money laundering](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Money_laundering), following an undercover operation from [FBI](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation) agents who purported to be drug traffickers. According to court documents, in addition to money laudering, Tarrag offered to [traffic drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illegal_drug_trade) herself from Paraguay. [(_ABC Color_)](https://www.abc.com.py/tv/abc-noticias/2019/11/22/detienen-a-cynthia-tarrago-en-eeuu/) [(_ltima Hora_)](https://www.ultimahora.com/detienen-cynthia-tarrago-eeuu-blanqueo-dinero-n2856211.html) [(_The Philadelphia Inquirer_)](https://www.inquirer.com/business/money-laundering-cocaine-marijuana-paraguay-newark-cynthia-tarrago-diaz-raimundo-va-fbu-20191122.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2021 German federal election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next_German_federal_election)\n    *   [Annegret Kramp-Karrenbauer](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annegret_Kramp-Karrenbauer), who replaced [German Chancellor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chancellor_of_Germany) [Angela Merkel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angela_Merkel) as leader of the [Christian Democratic Union](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christian_Democratic_Union_of_Germany), threatens to stand down as a chancellor candidate if her [centre-right](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centre-right) party continues to disagree over support. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-50520902) [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/22/merkel-successor-annegret-kramp-karrenbauer-back-her-or-sack-her) [(_The Telegraph_)](https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/11/22/mini-merkel-faces-critics-back-sack-challenge/)\n*   [2019 Bolivian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_protests), [2019 Bolivian political crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bolivian_political_crisis)\n    *   [Bolivia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolivia)''s new [interior minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interior_minister), Arturo Murillo, files a criminal complaint against former [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Bolivia) [Evo Morales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evo_Morales) for alleged [sedition](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sedition) and [terrorism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/22/bolivia-evo-morales-terrorism-sedition-interim-government) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bolivia-politics/bolivias-interim-government-charges-morales-with-sedition-and-terrorism-idUSKBN1XW26Y)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_22','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3196,replace('# 2019-11-23\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [November 2019 Syria bombings](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/November_2019_Syria_bombings)\n    *   A [car bomb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Car_bomb) detonates in [Tell Abyad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tell_Abyad), [Raqqa Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raqqa_Governorate), killing ten people and wounding 25 others. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-security/car-bomb-kills-at-least-10-people-near-syrias-border-with-turkey-idUSKBN1XX0BS?il=0)\n*   [2019 Colombian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Colombian_protests)\n    *   Three [Colombian police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Police_of_Colombia) are killed and seven wounded by a [car bomb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Car_bomb) in [Santander de Quilichao](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santander_de_Quilichao), [Cauca](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cauca_Department) province. [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/23/colombian-protests-flare-again-as-looting-erupts-in-bogota)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [Tonga](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tonga) and [Fiji](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiji) declare a [state of emergency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_of_emergency) as part of an ongoing [measles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Measles) outbreak. Conditions worsen in [Samoa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samoa) where the death toll continues to rise and schools remain closed. There are 1,797 confirmed cases as of Saturday, with 153 detected on Friday alone. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-50528834)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [2019 Iranian fuel protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iranian_fuel_protests)\n    *   [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) [Vice President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vice_President_of_Iran) [Eshaq Jahangiri](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eshaq_Jahangiri) warns regional states of dire consequences, claiming the protests are directly linked to the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States), [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia), and [Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-gasoline-protests/iran-warns-regional-states-of-consequences-if-they-stoked-unrest-idUSKBN1XX07O)\n*   [IranIraq relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Iraq_relations)\n    *   The [border between](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran-Iraq_border) Iran and [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq) reopens, after being closed for a week due to mass protests in their [respective](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iranian_fuel_protests) [countries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-iran-border/iraq-iran-border-crossing-reopens-after-week-long-closure-statement-idUSKBN1XX0BB?il=0)\n*   [ChinaUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China%E2%80%93United_States_relations)\n    *   [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) [Foreign Affairs Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foreign_Minister_of_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China) [Wang Yi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wang_Yi_(politician)) accuses the United States of being the "world''s biggest destabilizing factor" and of "smear\[ing\] China everywhere" at the [G20](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G20) meeting in [Nagoya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nagoya). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-usa-trade/china-attacks-u-s-at-g20-as-the-worlds-biggest-source-of-instability-idUSKBN1XX09P?il=0)\n*   [Pope Francis travels to Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_pastoral_visits_of_Pope_Francis)\n    *   During his 23 November to 26 November journey to [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan), [Pope Francis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pope_Francis) visits [Tokyo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokyo), [Nagasaki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nagasaki) and [Hiroshima](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hiroshima). The only pope to previously visit Japan was Pope John Paul II in 2326 February 1981. [(Holy See Press Office)](https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/en/bollettino/pubblico/2019/10/28/191028a.html) [(Vatican News)](https://www.vaticannews.va/en/vatican-city/news/2019-11/pope-john-paul-ii-visit-japan-1981.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Bougainvillean independence referendum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Bougainvillean_independence_referendum)\n    *   People in the [Autonomous Region of Bougainville](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autonomous_Region_of_Bougainville) vote to choose between more [autonomy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autonomy) within [Papua New Guinea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Papua_New_Guinea) or outright [independence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independence). However, the [Papua New Guinea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Papua_New_Guinea) central government will have the final say on accepting independence. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/403929/expectations-high-as-bougainville-referendum-gets-underway)\n*   [2019 referendum on the creation of a Sidama region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_referendum_on_the_creation_of_a_Sidama_region)\n    *   The [Ethiopian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopia) [electoral board](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Election_Board_of_Ethiopia) announces that the [referendum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Referendum) to grant autonomy to the [Sidama Zone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidama_Zone) passed with 98.5% of the vote. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ethiopia-politics/ethiopias-sidama-vote-overwhelmingly-to-form-autonomous-region-idUSKBN1XX0GR?il=0)\n*   [Climate change policy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change_policy_of_the_United_States), [Harvard-Yale football game](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harvard-Yale_football_game)\n    *   A non-violent protest was held at the [Yale Bowl](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yale_Bowl) during the annual [Harvard](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harvard)\-[Yale](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yale) [football](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_football) game at halftime. The apparently scheduled protest included both Yale and Harvard students. The students were protesting the colleges'' usage of endowments from [fossil fuel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fossil_fuel) companies. The game was delayed for about an hour. There were some arrests. [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2019/11/23/us/harvard-yale-climate-protest-trnd/index.html) [(_The New York Times_}](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/23/us/harvard-yale-game-protest.html)\n\n## Sports\n\n*   [2019 Copa Libertadores](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Copa_Libertadores)\n    *   The premier [association football](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Association_football) club competition of South America concludes with [Brazilian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil) club [Flamengo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clube_de_Regatas_do_Flamengo) beating titleholders [River Plate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Club_Atl%C3%A9tico_River_Plate) 2-1 in [Lima](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lima)''s [Monumental Stadium](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Estadio_Monumental_%22U%22). It is their first title since 1981 and second overall. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50532892)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_23','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3197,replace('# 2019-11-25\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   Protestors storm the [MONUSCO](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MONUSCO) headquarters in [Beni](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beni,_Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo), [Democratic Republic of the Congo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo), and set [UN](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations) vehicles on fire in anger at the [peacekeepers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations_peacekeeping)'' failure to stop the [Allied Democratic Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Democratic_Forces) [insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Democratic_Forces_insurgency). Congolese security forces fire at the crowd to disperse them, killing at least two. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/killed-rebel-attack-dr-congo-city-beni-191125105346272.html)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Transport for London](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transport_for_London) announces it will not grant a new license to operate to [Uber](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uber), citing safety failures. The company will appeal. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/business-50544283)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [2019 Mnaka helicopter crash](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_M%C3%A9naka_helicopter_crash)\n    *   Thirteen [French soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_soldier) are killed in helicopter crash during an operation against [jihadists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jihadists) in [Mali](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mali). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-50557511?ns_linkname=news_central&ns_mchannel=social&ns_campaign=bbc_breaking&ns_source=twitter)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [Fijian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiji) Health Minister [Ifereimi Waqainabete](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ifereimi_Waqainabete) warns that [police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_Fiji) will be deployed to areas under [quarantine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quarantine) if people continue not to respect the order to stay at home if they have [measles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Measles), amid an ongoing outbreak of the illness in various [Pacific island](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_island) nations. [(_Fiji Times_)](https://www.fijitimes.com/ministry-sounds-warning-as-measles-cases-rise/) [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/404072/authorities-in-fiji-urge-public-to-respect-quarantine)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [IranIsrael relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Israel_relations), [IranSaudi Arabia relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Saudi_Arabia_relations), [IranUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93United_States_relations), [2019 Iranian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iranian_protests)\n    *   Head of the [Revolutionary Guards](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Revolutionary_Guards) [Hossein Salami](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hossein_Salami) delivers a televised speech toward [Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel), [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia), the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) and those who are protesting against the government in which he says "We will destroy you" if they cross Iran''s red line. [(_Haaretz_)](https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/iran/iran-warns-israel-u-s-saudi-arabia-cross-red-lines-and-we-will-destroy-you-1.8176159) [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/irans-guard-threatens-us-allies-over-protests/2019/11/25/87ebdb90-0f89-11ea-924c-b34d09bbc948_story.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Essex lorry deaths](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Essex_lorry_deaths)\n    *   The driver of the lorry in which 39 Vietnamese migrants were found dead in [Grays](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grays), [Essex](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Essex), [England](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England), pleads guilty to conspiring to assist [unlawful immigration](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unlawful_immigration). [(_The Independent_)](https://independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/essex-lorry-deaths-maurice-robinson-mo-guilty-trafficking-immigration-latest-a9216561.html)\n*   [Catholic Church sexual abuse cases in Argentina](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catholic_Church_sexual_abuse_cases_by_country#Argentina)\n    *   Two [Roman Catholic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman_Catholic) priests are sentenced to more than 40 years in prison for [sexually assaulting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexually_assault) deaf children at a church school in [Mendoza Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mendoza_Province), Argentina; the school''s gardener also receives an 18-year sentence. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-50549918) [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/25/roman-catholic-priests-argentina-sentenced-45-years-child-abuse-school-deaf)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   [Tim Berners-Lee](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tim_Berners-Lee), creator of the [World Wide Web](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Wide_Web), launches a [World Wide Web Foundation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Wide_Web_Foundation) scheme _[Contract for the Web](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contract_for_the_Web)_. [(CNBC)](https://www.cnbc.com/2019/11/25/tim-berners-lee-launches-contract-for-the-web-to-fix-the-internet.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_25','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3198,replace('# 2019-11-29\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 The Hague stabbing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_The_Hague_stabbing)\n    *   [Police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_the_Netherlands) report that three young people have been wounded in a stabbing on a shopping street in [The Hague](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hague), [Netherlands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netherlands). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-netherlands-stabbing/dutch-police-several-wounded-in-stabbing-in-the-hague-idUSKBN1Y329Y)\n*   [2019 London Bridge attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_London_Bridge_attack)\n    *   A [mass stabbing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_stabbing) at [London Bridge](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London_Bridge) results in two [civilians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian) killed and three others injured. The attacker, [Usman Khan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Usman_Khan_(militant)), wearing a fake [explosive belt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Explosive_belt), is shot dead by [police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metropolitan_Police) on the bridge. The attack is confirmed as [terror](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_the_United_Kingdom)\-related. Khan was a former prisoner convicted of terrorism offences, and had links to [Islamist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_extremism) terror groups. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50610215)\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   After a surprise visit by [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._President) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump), the [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) say they are ready to restart [peace talks](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_peace_process) and reach a [ceasefire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ceasefire). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-afghanistan-taliban/after-trumps-kabul-visit-taliban-says-ready-to-resume-peace-talks-idUSKBN1Y30GR)\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   Protests continue across [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq) with a death toll of seven protesters by unsourced reports. Other reports by hospital sources state the death toll is over 20 due to [Iraqi forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi_Armed_Forces) opening fire in [Nasiriya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nasiriya). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/protesters-shot-dead-violence-continues-iraq-191129193729541.html) [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50600495)\n*   [Yemeni Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemeni_Civil_War_(2015%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Houthi militants](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houthi_movement) say that they shot down a [Saudi Arabian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia) [helicopter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helicopter), killing both pilots. Saudi Arabia has not confirmed the incident. [(Sputnik)](https://sputniknews.com/middleeast/201911291077435287-houthi-forces-claim-theyve-shot-down-a-saudi-helicopter/)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [2019 Samoa measles outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Samoa_measles_outbreak)\n    *   It is expected that there will be 70 deaths from the illness, and at least 6,500 people will be infected by the highly infectious disease. [(NZ Hearld)](https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12289525)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   The [government of Sudan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Sudan) repeals all laws restricting women''s freedom of dress, movement, association, work and study, and dissolves the former ruling party. [Sudanese Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_heads_of_government_of_Sudan) [Abdalla Hamdok](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdalla_Hamdok) praises women on [social media](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_media) and says that the laws were an instrument of exploitation, humiliation, violation, aggression on the rights of citizens. [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/29/sudan-dissolves-ex-ruling-party-and-repeals-morality-law)\n*   A [national](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suriname) court rules [President of Suriname](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Suriname) [Dsi Bouterse](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D%C3%A9si_Bouterse) guilty of murder. The case adresses the execution of 15 government critics in 1982, following the [1980 Sergeants'' Coup](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1980_Surinamese_coup_d%27%C3%A9tat) led by Bouterse. Six other former military officers are also declared guilty. [(Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/30/suriname-president-guilty-of-over-1982-executions)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   [Prime Minister of Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Iraq) [Adel Abdul Mahdi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adel_Abdul_Mahdi) announces plans to offer his resignation to the [country](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq)''s [parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Representatives_of_Iraq) as a reaction to the ongoing protest movement. [(DW)](https://www.dw.com/en/iraq-prime-minister-adel-abdul-mahdi-says-he-will-resign/a-51469003)\n*   [Prime Minister of Malta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Malta) [Joseph Muscat](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Muscat) intends to step down following controversy over an ongoing investigation about the murder of [investigative journalist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Investigative_journalism) [Daphne Caruana Galizia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daphne_Caruana_Galizia) two years ago. [(DW)](https://www.dw.com/en/maltas-prime-minister-joseph-muscat-to-resign/a-51471942)\n*   Former [Japanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Japan) [Yasuhiro Nakasone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yasuhiro_Nakasone) dies at the [age of 101](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centenarian). [(NHK WORLD News)](https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20191129_37/amp.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_29','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3199,replace('# 2019-11-30\n\n## Armed conflict and attacks\n\n*   [ADF Insurgency in the Democratic Republic of The Congo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Democratic_Forces_insurgency)\n    *   Twelve [civilians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian) are killed in an attack by militants. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/11/drc-army-killed-top-adf-leader-civilian-toll-rises-191130081713060.html)\n    *   Two alleged rebels are [lynched](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lynched) by civilians who suspected that the two were involved in the deaths of dozens of [civilians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian) since November 5. [(Straits Times)](https://www.straitstimes.com/world/africa/crowd-in-dr-congo-lynches-two-suspected-militants-as-un-envoy-visits)\n    *   The [DR Congo armed forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armed_Forces_of_the_Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo) say that they have killed a top militant, Mouhamed Mkubwa Islam, who is one of three leaders of the [insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Insurgency). [(CGNT)](https://africa.cgtn.com/2019/11/30/dr-congo-army-says-it-has-killed-top-rebel-leader/)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   Nine people are killed and another three are injured in a plane crash in [Sioux Falls, South Dakota](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sioux_Falls,_South_Dakota), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States). [(_USA Today_)](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2019/11/30/plane-crash-south-dakota-kills-nine-people-ntsb-says/4343688002/)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [JapanNorth Korea relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93North_Korea_relations)\n    *   In an insult-laden statement, [North Korean media](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Media_of_North_Korea) warn [Japanese Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Japan) [Shinz Abe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shinz%C5%8D_Abe) that he "may see a real [ballistic missile](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ballistic_missile) in the near future." [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-northkorea-japan/north-korea-warns-japans-abe-may-soon-see-real-ballistic-missile-launch-idUSKBN1Y32GB)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Samoa measles epidemic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Samoa_measles_outbreak)\n    *   The [Prime Minister of Samoa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Samoa), [Tuilaepa Sailele Malielegaoi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuilaepa_Sailele_Malielegaoi), says that he will propose a law which would penalize parents who [refuse to](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anti-vaccination) [vaccinate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccinate) their children, amid an ongoing [epidemic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epidemic) that has killed 44 people, mostly children under the age of four. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/404533/samoa-govt-allocates-more-funds-for-measles-epidemic)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   Protests against poor living conditions break out in the central town of [Jilma](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jilma), [Tunisia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tunisia) after a man [set himself on fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-immolation) for the same reason on Friday. Police use [tear gas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tear_gas) to disperse the protestors. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-tunisia-protests/tunisians-protest-in-southern-town-after-man-sets-himself-alight-idUSKBN1Y40O7?il=0)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_November_30','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3200,replace('# 2019-12-01\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Villa Unin shootout](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Villa_Uni%C3%B3n_shootout)\n    *   A [shootout](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shootout) between [police officers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Police_(Mexico)) and [cartel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_cartel#Mexico) gunmen in [Villa Unin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Villa_Uni%C3%B3n,_Coahuila), [Coahuila](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coahuila), [Mexico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico), leaves at least 21 people dead. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mexico-violence/shootouts-in-northern-mexican-town-kill-21-fueling-debate-on-cartels-idUSKBN1Y515O)\n*   [Insurgency in the Maghreb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Insurgency_in_the_Maghreb_(2002%E2%80%93present))\n    *   Gunmen open fire on a church in [Burkina Faso](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burkina_Faso) killing fourteen Christians and wounding dozens of others. The attack took place in a village of [Foutouri](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foutouri_(department)). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-burkina-security/at-least-14-killed-in-attack-on-burkina-faso-church-idUSKBN1Y51C6)\n*   [Anglophone Crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anglophone_Crisis)\n    *   A [Camair-Co](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camair-Co) plane is fired upon while attempting to land at [Bamenda Airport](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bamenda_Airport), but the pilot manages to safely land the plane with no casualties reported. [(RT)](https://www.rt.com/newsline/474792-passenger-plane-attacked-cameroon/)\n*   [Syrian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Civil_War)\n    *   [Rami Abdul Rahman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rami_Abdul_Rahman) says clashes in [Idlib](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib) between [Islamists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamist) and the [Syrian Arab Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Arab_Army) kill around 70. Around 36 [Syrian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria) soldiers were killed in the two day clash. [(France 24)](https://www.france24.com/en/20191201-clashes-syrian-government-forces-militant-groups-leave-nearly-70-dead-idlib-jihadists-opposition)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   Nineteen people die when a bus skids off a bridge in [Zabaykalsky Krai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zabaykalsky_Krai) in the [Russian Far East](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Far_East), and falls onto a frozen river. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-russia-accident-bus/nineteen-people-killed-in-bus-crash-in-russias-far-east-local-government-idUSKBN1Y50V8)\n*   Twenty-four people are killed and 18 injured when a bus plunges into a [ravine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ravine) in [Tunisia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tunisia). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/bus-crash-northern-tunisia-kills-20-191201142400774.html)\n*   Three people are killed in a plane crash in [San Antonio](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Antonio), [Texas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texas), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States). [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/01/us/san-antonio-plane-crash/index.html)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [2019 Samoa measles outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Samoa_measles_outbreak)\n    *   Three children in one family are among those killed by the outbreak. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/nov/30/there-are-no-words-samoa-buries-its-children-as-measles-outbreak-worsens)\n*   [World AIDS Day](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_AIDS_Day)\n    *   The observance is marked by [UNAIDS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint_United_Nations_Programme_on_HIV/AIDS) and worldwide, as the [AIDS Quilt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NAMES_Project_AIDS_Memorial_Quilt) returns to [San Francisco](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Francisco). [(_The Independent_)](https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/world-aids-day-theme-when-is-it-what-hiv-status-health-awareness-campaign-a8652271.html) [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/29/health/AIDS-drugs-children.html) [(Wikispore)](https://wikispore.wmflabs.org//wiki/Event:World_AIDS_Day_2019)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [2019 New Orleans shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_New_Orleans_shooting)\n    *   Ten people are injured, two critically, in a [mass shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_shooting) in [New Orleans](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Orleans), [Louisiana](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louisiana). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2019/dec/01/new-orleans-shooting-french-quarter)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   The [Council of Representatives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Representatives_of_Iraq) accepts [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Iraq) [Adil Abdul-Mahdi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adil_Abdul-Mahdi)''s resignation. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/iraq-pm-offer-quit-country-191201092331173.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_1','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3201,replace('# 2019-12-03\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Google](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google) co-founders [Larry Page](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larry_Page) and [Sergey Brin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sergey_Brin) announce they are stepping down as CEO and president respectively from the company. [Sundar Pichai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sundar_Pichai) will become the new CEO of Google and its parent company [Alphabet Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphabet_Inc.) effective immediately. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/Business/google-founders-larry-page-sergey-brin-stepping-company/story?id=67472607)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   An [explosion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Explosion) at a ceramic factory in the [Sudanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudan) capital, [Khartoum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khartoum), kills at least 16 people and leaves dozens injured, according to the [Sudanese Professionals Association](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudanese_Professionals_Association). [(Gulf News)](https://gulfnews.com/world/mena/pictures-explosion-at-sudan-factory-kills-16-1.68230159)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [2019 Samoa measles outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Samoa_measles_outbreak)\n    *   The government makes it illegal to make non-essential domestic travel on the roads while [vaccination](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination) units cross the country with 40,000 still to be vaccinated. Also, the opposition calls for an inquiry into the low vaccination rates which began after a mistake by two nurses last year which resulted in the deaths of two children. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/404775/samoa-measles-epidemic-non-essential-road-travel-banned)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [2019 London summit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_London_summit)\n    *   World leaders from members of [NATO](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NATO) gather for their annual summit in [Watford](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Watford), [Hertfordshire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hertfordshire), [England](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England). [(_Time_)](https://time.com/5741250/nato-summit-2019/)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Pakistani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistanis) [business tycoon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business_tycoon) [Malik Riaz](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malik_Riaz) agrees to surrender [](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pound_sterling)190 million in cash and assets to the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom)''s [National Crime Agency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Crime_Agency), including his [Grade II listed](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Listed_building)\-[London](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London) home in [One Hyde Park](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Hyde_Park). The NCA accuse the tycoon of acquiring his wealth and property through crime. [(Sky News)](https://news.sky.com/story/pakistani-property-tycoon-malik-riaz-hussain-agrees-to-hand-over-190m-to-uk-authorities-11877161)\n*   The [Federal Supreme Court of Switzerland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Supreme_Court_of_Switzerland) upholds a 2018 ruling that the [Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liberation_Tigers_of_Tamil_Eelam) is not a [criminal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crime_in_Sri_Lanka) group. Even though it carried out [terrorist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_Sri_Lanka) attacks, the [Tamil](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tamils) Tigers'' primary objective in the [Sri Lankan Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sri_Lankan_Civil_War) was, according to the court, to be recognised as an independent ethnic community. [(swissinfo.com)](https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/law---order_tamil-tigers-acquitted-in-switzerland/45409056)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Politics of Finland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politics_of_Finland)\n    *   [Antti Rinne](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antti_Rinne) resigns as the [Prime Minister of Finland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Finland) after losing the support of [coalition](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coalition_government) partner [Centre Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centre_Party_(Finland)) over Rinne''s handling of [industrial strikes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strike_action). The [Rinne Cabinet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rinne_Cabinet) will continue as a [caretaker government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caretaker_government) until a new [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Finland) can be formed. [(Reuters)](https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-finland-government/finlands-pm-resigns-after-losing-trust-of-coalition-partner-idUKKBN1Y70PO)\n*   [2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Democratic_Party_presidential_primaries)\n    *   [California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California) [Senator](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Senate) [Kamala Harris](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kamala_Harris) drops out of the presidential race, citing a lack of funds for [her campaign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kamala_Harris_2020_presidential_campaign). [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2019/12/03/784443227/kamala-harris-drops-out-of-presidential-race)\n*   [Impeachment inquiry into Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_into_Donald_Trump)\n    *   The [U.S. House Intelligence Committee](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_Permanent_Select_Committee_on_Intelligence) releases a 330-page report of its impeachment inquiry saying there is "overwhelming" evidence of misconduct and obstruction of Congress by [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump). It is sent to the [U.S. House Judiciary Committee](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_Committee_on_the_Judiciary) for review. [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/03/politics/house-intelligence-committee-report/index.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_3','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3202,replace('# 2019-12-04\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Japanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_people) [doctor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physician) [Tetsu Nakamura](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetsu_Nakamura_(physician)) and five [Afghans](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghans) are killed in [Jalalabad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalalabad), [Nangarhar Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nangarhar_Province), [Afghanistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan) when militants [open fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_shooting) on their car while they were travelling to monitor a project. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-50654985) [(Euronews)](https://www.euronews.com/2019/12/04/japanese-doctor-killed-attack-mourned-one-afghanistan-s-greatest-friends-n1095301)\n*   [Syrian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Civil_War), [IranIsrael proxy conflict](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Israel_proxy_conflict)\n    *   An [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) [Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_Revolutionary_Guard_Corps) weapons depot in [Abu Kamal District](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abu_Kamal_District), [Deir ez-Zor Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deir_ez-Zor_Governorate), [Syria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria), is hit by an [airstrike](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airstrike). Arab media say [Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel) is behind the attack. The [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) denies any involvement. [(Ynet)](https://www.ynetnews.com/article/B1v3mKS6H) [(Haaretz)](https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/iran/iranian-weapons-warehouse-struck-in-northern-syria-report-says-1.8223997)\n*   In [Madrid](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madrid), [Spain](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spain), a man throws a hand [grenade](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grenade) at a [migrant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immigration_to_Spain) [unaccompanied minor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unaccompanied_minor) centre, although it did not explode. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/04/grenade-thrown-at-migrant-childrens-centre-in-madrid)\n*   Eighteen [Indian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_people) [sailors](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Navy) are [abducted](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kidnapping) near the [Nigerian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigeria) coast. [(The Hindu)](https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/18-indians-on-board-hong-kong-vessel-kidnapped-off-nigerian-coast-ship-tracking-agency/article30172117.ece)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [Gadhimai festival](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gadhimai_festival)\n    *   Thousands of [animals are sacrificed](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animal_sacrifice) by [beheading](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decapitation) at the [Hindu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hinduism) [Gadhimai Temple](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gadhimai_Temple) in southern [Nepal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nepal). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nepal-religion/thousands-of-animals-sacrificed-in-nepal-hindu-ritual-amid-outcry-idUSKBN1Y81R6)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A boat carrying refugees capsized near [Nouadhibou](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nouadhibou), off the coast of [Mauritania](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mauritania), in one of the deadliest [maritime disasters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maritime_disasters) this year, leaving 58 people dead and many more who tried to swim to shore in need of treatment. The boat had departed [Gambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gambia) on 27 November 2019. It was heading towards the [Canary Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canary_Islands) when it approached the Mauritanian coast to get fuel and food. The boat had been carrying between 150-180 people when it capsized, most of them aged between 20 and 30. [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/05/dozens-killed-as-migrant-boat-sinks-off-mauritania-coast)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [2019 Samoa measles outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Samoa_measles_outbreak)\n    *   Amid the imposed curfew, the [Samoan government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samoan_government) asks unvaccinated families to display a red flag or red cloth in front of their homes to warn others and to aid mass [vaccination](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination) efforts as the death toll hits 60 and confirmed cases surpass 4,000. [(Deutsche Welle)](https://www.dw.com/en/samoan-measles-epidemic-unvaccinated-advised-to-display-red-flags-in-front-of-their-homes/a-51520869)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [JapanUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93United_States_relations)\n    *   The [National Diet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Diet) of [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) ratifies a [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States)Japan [trade deal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trade_deal). Under the deal, Japan will reduce its tariffs on U.S. beef and pork; in return, Japan will receive reductions in tariffs on certain manufactured goods. [(Financial Times)](https://www.ft.com/content/01240552-166d-11ea-9ee4-11f260415385)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Crime in Hawaii](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crime_in_Hawaii)\n    *   The [U.S. military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Armed_Forces) says a [sailor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Navy) shot and killed two people at [Joint Base Pearl HarborHickam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint_Base_Pearl_Harbor%E2%80%93Hickam), [Hawaii](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawaii), before killing himself. [(UPI)](https://www.upi.com/Top_News/US/2019/12/04/3-killed-including-gunman-in-Pearl-Harbor-shipyard-shooting/5351575510428/)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Impeachment inquiry against Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_against_Donald_Trump)\n    *   The [U.S. House Judiciary Committee](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_Committee_on_the_Judiciary) begins its hearings into the [impeachment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_in_the_United_States) inquiry of [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump). [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/04/us/politics/impeachment-hearings.html)\n\n*   _[Nunes v. CNN](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nunes_v._CNN)_\n    *   U.S. Rep. [Devin Nunes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Devin_Nunes) files a [US$](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/US$)435 million defamation lawsuit against [CNN](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CNN). [(_USA Today_)](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/04/devin-nunes-files-435-million-defamation-lawsuit-against-cnn/2606359001/)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_4','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3203,replace('# 2019-12-05\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   Chinese telecommunications giant [Huawei](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huawei) sues the U.S. [Federal Communications Commission](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Federal_Communications_Commission) over the latter''s ban on carriers from using money from the [Universal Service Fund](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Universal_Service_Fund) to buy equipment from Huawei and [ZTE](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ZTE). [(Tech Crunch)](https://techcrunch.com/2019/12/04/huawei-sues-fcc-over-unconstitutional-ban-the-use-of-federal-subsidies-to-buy-its-equipment/)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   Three [Minnesota National Guard](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minnesota_National_Guard) members are killed when a [Sikorsky UH-60 Black Hawk](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sikorsky_UH-60_Black_Hawk) helicopter crashes near [St. Cloud](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._Cloud,_Minnesota). [(AOL News)](https://www.aol.com/article/news/2019/12/05/3-national-guard-members-dead-in-black-hawk-helicopter-crash-in-minnesota/23875024/)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Indonesian police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indonesian_police) arrest more than 34 people over "charges of [treason](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treason)" for attempting to raise the outlawed [Morning Star flag](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morning_Star_flag), which represents the independence movement of [West Papua Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Papua_Province). [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/404931/dozens-face-treason-charges-for-flag-activities-in-papua)\n*   Former [Brazilian Presidents](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Brazil) [Dilma Rousseff](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dilma_Rousseff) and [Luiz Incio Lula da Silva](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luiz_In%C3%A1cio_Lula_da_Silva) are acquitted by a judge of alleged illegal financing for the [Workers'' Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Workers%27_Party_(Brazil)). [(_El Mundo_)](https://www.elmundo.es/internacional/2019/12/05/5de84c61fc6c838c458b459c.html)\n*   [Accounting fraud](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accounting_fraud)\n    *   The [U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Securities_and_Exchange_Commission) charges Neil Cole, former CEO of [Iconix Brand Group](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iconix_Brand_Group), with accounting fraud. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/iconix-brand-grp-fraud/iconix-brand-former-ceo-charged-with-accounting-fraud-idUSL4N28F3RV)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Impeachment inquiry against Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_against_Donald_Trump)\n    *   [U.S. House Speaker](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives) [Nancy Pelosi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nancy_Pelosi) announces the [U.S. House of Representatives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_of_Representatives) will begin to draft articles of [impeachment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_in_the_United_States) against [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) before the [Christmas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christmas) recess. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/05/us/politics/pelosi-impeachment.html)\n\n*   [2019 French Pension Reform Plan Strike](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_French_Pension_Reform_Plan_Strike)\n    *   A national strike begins in [France](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France) over [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_France) [Emmanuel Macron](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emmanuel_Macron)''s pension reform plan. [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2019/12/05/785018695/national-strike-in-france-shuts-down-cities-over-macrons-pension-reform-plans)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_5','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3204,replace('# 2019-12-06\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   Gunmen in vehicles open fire on protesters in [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad) killing over 19 and injuring around 70 others. Three of the dead were [Iraqi police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi_Police). The victims were either stabbed or shot. [(AP)](https://apnews.com/2d15fae86ea3e86dcf417f1d26a3461b) [(Telegraph)](https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/12/06/gunmen-cars-kill-least-15-injure-scores-baghdad-protests/) [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2019/12/killed-central-baghdad-assailants-fire-live-rounds-191206190824237.html)\n*   [Terrorism in Kenya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_Kenya)\n    *   At least ten people including seven [Kenyan police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenya_Police) are killed when armed gunmen ambush a bus in Kotulo, [Kenya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenya). Police suspect the Somalian Islamist group [Al-Shabaab](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Shabaab_(militant_group)) is behind the attack. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-kenya-attack/at-least-eight-killed-in-kenya-in-suspected-islamist-militant-attack-idUSKBN1YA27Z) [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/10-killed-kenya-bus-attack-claimed-al-shabab-191207082718077.html)\n*   [Naval Air Station Pensacola shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naval_Air_Station_Pensacola_shooting)\n    *   A shooter kills three people and injures eight more at [Naval Air Station Pensacola](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naval_Air_Station_Pensacola), [Florida](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florida), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States), before being shot and killed by police. [(_Pensacola News Journal_)](https://www.pnj.com/story/news/2019/12/06/breaking-active-shooter-reported-base-nas-pensacola/4351773002/)\n*   [Allied Democratic Forces insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Democratic_Forces_insurgency)\n    *   Islamists kill 17 civilians in two attacks in eastern [Democratic Republic of the Congo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-congo-security/islamist-rebels-kill-at-least-17-in-eastern-congo-local-official-idUSKBN1YA1YJ)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A collision between a [U.S. Navy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Navy) boat and a [U.S. Coast Guard](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Coast_Guard) boat in [Kodiak, Alaska](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kodiak,_Alaska)''s [Womens Bay](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Womens_Bay,_Alaska) injures nine, one critically. [(_Stars & Stripes_)](https://www.stripes.com/news/coast-guard/coast-guard-navy-boats-collide-in-alaska-nine-injured-1.610036)\n*   A gas explosion and consecutive fire in an apartment building in [Preov](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pre%C5%A1ov), Slovakia killed at least seven people and injured dozens. [(_Deutsche Welle_)](https://www.dw.com/en/slovakia-7-die-in-gas-explosion-dozens-injured/a-51559162) [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2019/12/07/world/europe/ap-eu-slovakia-gas-explosion.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [2019 Samoa measles outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Samoa_measles_outbreak)\n    *   [Samoan Police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_Samoa) arrest Edwin Tamasese, an [anti-vaccination](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccine_hesitancy) campaigner, for incitement against a [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Samoa) order. [(ABC Australia)](https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-12-06/anti-vaxxer-charged-samoa-amid-nationwide-immunisation-drive/11772714)\n*   The [United States District Court for the Central District of California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_District_Court_for_the_Central_District_of_California) unanimously votes to throw out a [US$](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._dollar)190 million [defamation suit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defamation) against entrepreneur [Elon Musk](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elon_Musk) by [Tham Luang cave rescuer](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tham_Luang_cave_rescue) Vernon Unsworth. The lawsuit, considered to be the first major suit by a private individual over comments made on [Twitter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twitter), was filed over Musk calling him a [pedo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pedophilia) guy in a Tweet after Unsworth criticized his role in the rescue. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-musk-lawsuit/tesla-boss-elon-musk-wins-defamation-trial-over-his-pedo-guy-tweet-idUSKBN1YA13U?il=0)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_6','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3205,replace('# 2019-12-07\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   A drone attacks the home of prominent [Shia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shia_Islam) cleric [Muqtada al-Sadr](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muqtada_al-Sadr), leaving no casualties and causing minimal damage. The attack follows a shooting against protestors in [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad) yesterday. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-protests-baghdad/rocket-hits-iraqi-clerics-home-following-deadly-baghdad-attack-idUSKBN1YB09W)\n*   [Afghan peace process](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_peace_process)\n    *   The [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) announce that the peace talks with the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) resumed "from where they stopped" in September. [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2019/12/07/politics/us-taliban-peace-talks-resume-doha-qatar/index.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [201819 Southern Africa drought](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018%E2%80%9319_Southern_Africa_drought)\n    *   An unprecedented [drought](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drought) in [Zimbabwe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zimbabwe), which is considered the worst in a century, causes the [Victoria Falls](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Victoria_Falls) [waterfall](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Waterfall) on the [Zambezi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zambezi) river to almost completely cease flowing. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/07/victoria-falls-dries-to-a-trickle-after-worst-drought-in-a-century)\n*   A woman is killed and 18 other people injured when a bus crashes with a truck in [Milan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milan), [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy). [(Ansa)](http://www.ansa.it/lombardia/notizie/2019/12/07/scontro-bus-camion-rifiuti-feriti_b566a1a7-0fe6-4eeb-b062-052f928302e6.html)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [IranUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93United_States_relations)\n    *   In an act of cooperation that is rare in recent years, [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) releases [Princeton](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Princeton_University) PhD candidate [Wang Xiyue](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xiyue_Wang) while the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) releases [stem cell](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stem_cell) researcher Massoud Soleimani in a [prisoner exchange](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prisoner_exchange). Both [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) and [Iranian Foreign Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Iran)) [Mohammad Javad Zarif](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohammad_Javad_Zarif) thank the [Swiss](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Switzerland) government for facilitating the swap. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-usa-prisoners/united-states-and-iran-swap-prisoners-in-rare-act-of-cooperation-idUSKBN1YB08X)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Rohingya genocide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohingya_genocide)\n    *   [Myanmar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myanmar)''s [Aung San Suu Kyi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aung_San_Suu_Kyi) travels to [The Hague](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hague) where she is expected to face [genocide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genocide) charges against her government for the alleged crimes committed against the [Rohingya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohingya) [Muslim](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islam_in_Myanmar) minority, in what is described as one of the most-high profile international legal cases in a generation. [_(Telegraph)_](https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/12/07/aung-san-suu-kyi-fight-genocide-charges-hague/)\n*   Two [indigenous](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indigenous_peoples_in_Brazil) leaders from the [Guajajara](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guajajara) tribe are shot dead in a [drive-by shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drive-by_shooting) on a federal highway in [Brazil](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil)''s [Maranho](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maranh%C3%A3o) state. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/08/amazon-indigenous-leaders-killed-in-brazil-drive-by-shooting)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_7','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3206,replace('# 2019-12-08\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Saudi Arabian-led intervention in Yemen](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabian-led_intervention_in_Yemen), [Yemeni Crisis (2011present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemeni_Crisis_(2011%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Sudanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudan) [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Sudan) [Abdalla Hamdok](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdalla_Hamdok) says the [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Sudan) has reduced the number of [Sudanese Armed Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudanese_Armed_Forces) troops in [Yemen](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemen) from 15,000 to 5,000, saying the conflict "can no longer be solved militarily". [(Reuters)](https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-sudan-politics/sudan-says-it-has-reduced-troops-in-yemen-to-5000-idUKKBN1YC0HX?il=0)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [2019 Delhi factory fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Delhi_factory_fire)\n    *   Forty-three workers are killed in a fire in a factory in [Delhi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delhi), [India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India). [(BBC)](https://bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-50703659)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Women''s rights in Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Women%27s_rights_in_Saudi_Arabia)\n    *   The [Ministry of Municipal and Rural Affairs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Municipal_and_Rural_Affairs_(Saudi_Arabia)) of [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia) announces that [gender-segregated](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sex_segregation) entrances are no longer mandatory for restaurants. This change is not considered compulsory however, and there are no announcements for similar changes to other public institutions. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/saudi-arabia-ends-gender-segregated-entrances-restaurants-191208171725619.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   After a massive march in the city, [Civil Human Rights Front](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civil_Human_Rights_Front) leader and [Rainbow of Hong Kong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rainbow_of_Hong_Kong) activist [Jimmy Sham](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimmy_Sham) says "it is the last chance for [Carrie Lam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carrie_Lam) to listen to the people". [(_Economic Times India_)](https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/hong-kong-protesters-mark-half-a-year-of-protest-with-mammoth-rally/articleshow/72430246.cms)\n*   [2019 Sammarinese general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Sammarinese_general_election)\n    *   Citizens of [San Marino](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Marino) are called to the polls in the first round to elect the 60 members of the [Grand and General Council](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_and_General_Council). [(_Il Resto del Carlino_)](https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/rimini/politica/elezioni-san-marino-2019-1.4927174)\n*   [Politics of Finland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politics_of_Finland)\n    *   The [Social Democratic Party of Finland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_Democratic_Party_of_Finland) selects [Minister of Transport and Communications](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minister_of_Transport_and_Communications_(Finland)) [Sanna Marin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sanna_Marin) for [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Finland), following the resignation of [Antti Rinne](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antti_Rinne). If confirmed, she will become Finland''s youngest ever Prime Minister and the world''s youngest serving Prime Minister at age 34. [(Reuters)](https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-finland-government-pm/finlands-social-democrats-name-marin-to-be-youngest-ever-prime-minister-idUKKBN1YC0JQ)\n*   [2019 Lebanese protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Lebanese_protests)\n    *   Businessman Samir Khatib withdraws his candidacy for the [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Lebanon) position after failing to secure enough votes from the [Sunni Muslim](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanese_Sunni_Muslims) bloc last week. This leaves the ousted [Saad Hariri](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saad_Hariri) as the only potential candidate. Massive protests are formed outside the [Parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parliament_of_Lebanon) building in response to Hariris possible return. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/lebanon-hariri-emerges-pm-candidate-khatib-withdraws-191208192459108.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_8','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3207,replace('# 2019-12-10\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Somali Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somali_Civil_War_(2009%E2%80%93present))\n    *   Near the [Villa Somalia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Villa_Somalia) [presidential palace](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Presidential_palace) in [Mogadishu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mogadishu), five [al-Shabaab](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Shabaab_(militant_group)) gunmen attack a SYL hotel. The attack and subsequent shootout kills three civilians, two [soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somalia_Armed_Forces) and all the attackers. [(CBS17)](https://www.cbs17.com/news/armed-men-attack-presidential-residence-in-somalias-capital/)\n*   [2019 Jersey City shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Jersey_City_shooting)\n    *   Heavy gunfire is exchanged between [police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Jersey_State_Police) and two shooters in [Jersey City](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jersey_City), [New Jersey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Jersey). Six people are killed: A police officer, the shooters, and three people inside a [kosher](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kosher_foods) [supermarket](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supermarket), which the shooters [barricaded](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barricade) themselves in. Police describe the shooting as an "[ambush](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ambush)". [(_The Independent_)](https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/jersey-city-shooting-today-active-shooter-police-officer-nj-mlk-drive-new-york-a9241241.html) [(NBC New York)](https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/active-shooter-situation-in-jersey-city-sources-say/2238983/)\n*   [Iranian involvement in the Syrian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iranian_involvement_in_the_Syrian_Civil_War)\n    *   Satellite images spot a tunnel system being dug at [Imam Ali military base](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imam_Ali_military_base) in eastern [Syria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria), which is controlled by the [Iranian military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armed_Forces_of_the_Islamic_Republic_of_Iran); Western intelligence believe the tunnels are being constructed to house their missiles. [(Fox News)](https://www.foxnews.com/world/iran-underground-tunnel-missile-storage)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [MyanmarUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myanmar%E2%80%93United_States_relations)\n    *   The [United States Department of the Treasury](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_the_Treasury) blacklists four top [Burmese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myanmar) [military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tatmadaw) leaders, including [Commander-in-Chief](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commander-in-Chief_of_Defence_Services) [Min Aung Hlaing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Min_Aung_Hlaing), for their role in the [persecution of Rohingya Muslims](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persecution_of_Muslims_in_Myanmar) and other minorities. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-myanmar-sanctions/u-s-blacklists-head-of-myanmar-military-for-alleged-rights-abuses-against-rohingya-idUSKBN1YE1XU?il=0)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Ostrava hospital attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ostrava_hospital_attack)\n    *   In [Ostrava](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ostrava), [Czech Republic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Czech_Republic), a man [opens fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_shooting) in a hospital''s waiting room, killing six people before fleeing, then shooting himself dead. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-czech-shooting/gunman-kills-six-in-czech-hospital-before-shooting-himself-idUSKBN1YE0P4)\n\n*   _[Rohingya genocide case](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohingya_genocide_case)_\n    *   At the [International Court of Justice](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Court_of_Justice), [The Gambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Gambia) presents charges against the government of [Myanmar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myanmar) and its leader [Aung San Suu Kyi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aung_San_Suu_Kyi), who traveled to appear in the court. According to the prosecution, the Burmese government is responsible for mass rapes, widespread arson and killings of Rohingya children, among other crimes. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-rohingya-world-court/as-suu-kyi-looks-on-gambia-details-mass-rapes-killings-in-myanmar-idUSKBN1YE0HL?il=0)\n*   [2017 Saint Petersburg Metro bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2017_Saint_Petersburg_Metro_bombing)\n    *   A military court sentences 10 people to jail terms ranging between 19 and 28 years. The person who is said to have trained the [suicide bomber](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicide_bomber) gets prison for life. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-50729108)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Impeachment inquiry against Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_against_Donald_Trump)\n    *   [Democrats](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Party_(United_States)) in the [United States House of Representatives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_of_Representatives) unveil two [articles of impeachment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Articles_of_impeachment) against [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump): [abuse of power](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abuse_of_power) and [obstruction](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obstruction_of_justice) of [Congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Congress). [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/politics/live-news/impeachment-inquiry-12-10-2019/index.html)\n*   [Alberto Fernndez](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alberto_Fern%C3%A1ndez) takes the oath of office as [President of Argentina](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Argentina) while [Cristina Fernndez de Kirchner](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cristina_Fern%C3%A1ndez_de_Kirchner) is sworn in as [Vice President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vice_President_of_Argentina). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.tv/l/P3X2/2019/12/10/argentina-s-president-elect-alberto-fernandez-is-sworn-in)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_10','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3208,replace('# 2019-12-13\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [ChinaUnited States trade war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China%E2%80%93United_States_trade_war)\n    *   Both countries announce an initial deal where new tariffs to be mutually imposed on December 15 would not be implemented. China says it "will buy more high quality of American agricultural products", while the United States says it will halve the existing 15% tariffs. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/business/2019/dec/13/china-confirms-phase-one-trade-deal-us-tariffs)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [2019 Chilean protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Chilean_protests)\n    *   The [Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Office_of_the_United_Nations_High_Commissioner_for_Human_Rights) releases a report regarding the situation in Chile. The report confirms the existence of severe and reiterative human rights violations, including excessive use of force, arbitrary detentions, torture and sexual violence. [(Cooperativa)](https://www.cooperativa.cl/noticias/pais/dd-hh/ddhh-informe-bachelet-consigna-muertes-tortura-y-violencia-sexual/2019-12-13/092349.html)\n*   [Corruption in Ukraine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corruption_in_Ukraine)\n    *   An appeals court in [Ukraine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine) confirms head of the [National Anti-Corruption Bureau of Ukraine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Anti-Corruption_Bureau_of_Ukraine) [Artem Sytnyk](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artem_Sytnyk)''s culpability and sentence for corruption. [(UNIAN)](https://www.unian.info/politics/10794095-elite-leisure-in-rivne-region-court-finds-nabu-head-sytnyk-guilty-of-corruption.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Impeachment inquiry against Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_against_Donald_Trump)\n    *   The [House Judiciary Committee](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_Committee_on_the_Judiciary) votes along party lines to pass two articles for impeachment against [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump). The [House of Representatives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_of_Representatives) is expected to hold two votes, one for each charge, on Wednesday, December 18. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/house-judiciary-committee-set-vote-trump-impeachment-articles/story?id=67706093)\n*   [2019 Algerian presidential election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Algerian_presidential_election)\n    *   [Abdelmadjid Tebboune](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdelmadjid_Tebboune) is elected in the first round. [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2019/12/13/787789940/algeria-elects-a-new-president-in-controversial-election)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_13','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3209,replace('# 2019-12-14\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   An insider attack by seven [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) infiltrators killed 25 [Afghan Armed Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_Armed_Forces) in [Qarabagh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qarabagh_District,_Ghazni), [Ghazni Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghazni_Province), [Afghanistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan). [(VOA News)](https://www.voanews.com/south-central-asia/insider-attack-kills-25-afghan-security-forces)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Light rail in Sydney](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Light_rail_in_Sydney)\n    *   The first section of the [CBD and South East Light Rail](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CBD_and_South_East_Light_Rail) commences operations returning trams down [George Street](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Street,_Sydney) for the first time since the demise of the [former tram network](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trams_in_Sydney). [(_The Sydney Morning Herald_)](https://www.smh.com.au/national/nsw/these-projects-are-like-childbirth-hopes-high-as-sydney-s-light-rail-begins-taking-passengers-20191214-p53jzi.html)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [2019 Samoa measles outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Samoa_measles_outbreak)\n    *   The [government of Samoa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Samoa) extends the [state of emergency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_of_emergency) until December 29 when it was due to end on December 15. There have been 72 deaths and more than 5,100 cases to date. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/405509/samoa-measles-state-of-emergency-extended) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-measles-samoa/samoa-extends-measles-state-of-emergency-nz-to-fund-pacific-vaccination-campaign-idUSKBN1YI05V)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   Former [Sudanese President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudanese_President) [Omar al-Bashir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omar_al-Bashir) is sentenced to two years detention in a reform facility for [corruption](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corruption_in_Sudan). There is heavy military custody of the [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Sudan) buildings and the court as followers of his now dissolved party rally in his support. Defense lawyers say they will appeal the sentence. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-sudan-politics-bashir/former-sudan-president-bashir-sentenced-to-two-years-in-detention-for-corruption-idUSKBN1YI087)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_14','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3210,replace('# 2019-12-15\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Lebanese protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Lebanese_protests)\n    *   Clashes between protestors and security forces at a protest camp in [Beirut](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beirut) leave dozens of people injured. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/dozens-injured-police-clash-protesters-lebanon-191215054752981.html)\n*   [Allied Democratic Forces insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Democratic_Forces_insurgency)\n    *   Twenty-two civilians are killed by Islamist militants in [machete](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machete) attacks in the town of [Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beni,_Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-congo-security/militants-kill-22-in-eastern-congo-despite-claims-of-security-progress-idUSKBN1YJ0KC?il=0) [(DW News)](https://www.dw.com/en/islamist-rebels-kill-dozens-in-dr-congo/a-51684794)\n*   [Citizenship (Amendment) Bill protests in India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Citizenship_(Amendment)_Bill_protests_in_India)\n    *   Violent protests against the [new citizenship bill](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Citizenship_(Amendment)_Act,_2019) break out in [Delhi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delhi), leaving at least six dead. The protestors, numbering in the thousands and containing numerous students, were dispersed by [police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delhi_Police) using [tear gas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tear_gas) and [baton charges](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baton_charge). The police also stormed the campus of [Jamia Millia Islamia University](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jamia_Millia_Islamia) to arrest protestors fleeing the scene while clashing against students. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/india-killed-assam-protests-citizenship-law-191215070715487.html)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [Censorship in China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Censorship_in_China)\n    *   State broadcaster [China Central Television](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Central_Television) pulls a [Premier League](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Premier_League) match between [Arsenal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arsenal_F.C.) and [Manchester City](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchester_City_F.C.) from its schedule after Arsenal [midfielder](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Midfielder) [Mesut zil](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mesut_%C3%96zil) criticized China''s [re-education camps in Xinjang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xinjiang_re-education_camps). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/dec/15/mesut-ozil-china-uighur-muslims-arsenal-manchester-city)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [2019 Davao del Sur earthquake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Davao_del_Sur_earthquake)\n    *   At least seven people are confirmed dead while 37 more are injured after a [magnitude](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moment_magnitude_scale) 6.9 earthquake strikes [Matanao](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matanao,_Davao_del_Sur), [Davao del Sur](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Davao_del_Sur), in the [Philippines](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippines). [(Sputnik)](https://sputniknews.com/asia/201912161077585528-at-least-7-people-killed-as-result-of-earthquake-in-southern-philippines-reports/) [(AP via CBC News)](https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/earthquake-philippines-1.5397035)\n*   At least ten people are killed by a fire at a [fan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fan_(machine)) factory in [Gazipur](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gazipur), [Bangladesh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladesh). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bangladesh-factory-fire/fire-at-bangladesh-factory-kills-10-people-idUSKBN1YJ0IA?il=0)\n*   A bus carrying 32 [Hindu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hinduism) pilgrims veers off a highway in central [Nepal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nepal), killing at least 14 people. [(Channel News Asia)](https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/14-killed-in-nepal-pilgrimage-bus-crash-12185588)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [LibyaTurkey relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya%E2%80%93Turkey_relations), [Libyan Civil War (2014present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Civil_War_(2014%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey) says it is ready to provide [military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_Armed_Forces) support to the [Tripoli](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tripoli)\-based [Government of National Accord](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_National_Accord) (GNA) against [Khalifa Haftar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khalifa_Haftar)''s forces if requested to do so by the GNA. The [Grand National Assembly of Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_National_Assembly_of_Turkey) approves military intervention in [Libya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-turkey-libya-security-erdogan/turkey-ready-to-give-any-military-support-libya-needs-erdogan-idUSKBN1YJ0LB) [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/turkish-lawmakers-sign-libya-military-support-deal-191215114132175.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   [Hong Kong Police Force](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong_Police_Force) clash with protesters at different malls across [Hong Kong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong) amid a visit by [Chief Executive](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chief_Executive_of_Hong_Kong) [Carrie Lam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carrie_Lam) to [Beijing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beijing). Riot police use [pepper spray](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pepper_spray) to disperse crowds as a result. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-protests/hong-kong-mall-protests-flare-with-leader-lam-in-beijing-idUSKBN1YJ09S)\n*   [2019 Chilean protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Chilean_protests)\n    *   In a non-binding referendum organized by the Chilean Association of Municipalities, 91% of the voters support a new Constitution and more than 70% of the voters support a fully elected [constituent assembly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constituent_assembly) to write it. An [official referendum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Chilean_constitutional_referendum) will be realized in April 2020. [(_La Tercera_)](https://www.latercera.com/nacional/noticia/consulta-ciudadana-resultados-preliminares-revelan-846-110-personas-estan-favor-una-nueva-constitucion/940360/)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_15','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3211,replace('# 2019-12-16\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2019 Lebanese protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Lebanese_protests)\n    *   The [Lebanese Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanese_Armed_Forces) clashes with supporters of [Hezbollah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hezbollah) and [Amal Movement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amal_Movement) in [Beirut](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beirut). The [Shiite](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shia_Islam) [Islamists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamism) were attempting to attack an anti-[government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Lebanon) protester camp in [Martyrs'' Square](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martyrs%27_Square,_Beirut). [(Reuters)](https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-lebanon-protests-clashes/lebanese-army-clashes-with-supporters-of-hezbollah-amal-in-beirut-idUKKBN1YK27F?il=0)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Boeing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing) decides to halt production of the [Boeing 737 MAX](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_737_MAX). [(The Economist)](https://www.economist.com/leaders/2019/12/17/boeings-misplaced-strategy)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   The [Supreme Court of the United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States) refuses to hear a case regarding [homeless](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homelessness_in_the_United_States) people sleeping in public parks, and on sidewalks, when no other shelter is available. In allowing the camping, the high court left intact a lower court ruling, calling such bans [cruel and unusual punishment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cruel_and_unusual_punishment). [(USA Today)](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2019/12/16/homeless-supreme-court-living-street-crime/4403793002/)\n*   In rare protests, dozens are arrested in [Kazakhstan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kazakhstan) during [Independence Day](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independence_Day_(Kazakhstan)). Protestors demand political reform and the sidelining of the family of former [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Kazakhstan) [Nursultan Nazarbayev](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nursultan_Nazarbayev). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-kazakhstan-independence-protests/dozens-detained-in-rare-kazakhstan-independence-day-protests-idUSKBN1YK1B1?il=0)\n*   [Cannabis in Zambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cannabis_in_Zambia)\n    *   [Zambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zambia) legalizes the production and export of [cannabis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cannabis_(drug)) for economic and medicinal purposes, but recreational use of the drug remains illegal. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-zambia-cannabis/zambia-approves-cannabis-exports-to-boost-economy-idUSKBN1YK1XU)\n*   The [human rights group](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights_defender) International Rights Advocates formally launches a lawsuit in the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) against [Apple Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple_Inc.), [Alphabet Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphabet_Inc.) ([Google](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google)), [Tesla, Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tesla,_Inc.), [Dell](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dell) and [Microsoft](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft) on behalf of 14 [Congolese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo) families whose children died or were injured in [Copperbelt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copperbelt) mines that supply [cobalt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cobalt) for the firms'' [lithium-ion battery](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lithium-ion_battery) products. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-50812616)\n*   Wanted criminal [Ridouan Taghi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ridouan_Taghi) has been arrested in [Dubai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dubai). He was wanted by the Netherlands for large scale cocaine trafficking and multiple murders. [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/16/dubai-police-arrest-most-wanted-man-netherlands-ridouan-taghi)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 French pension reform strike](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_French_pension_reform_strike)\n    *   On the twelfth day of the strike, [Jean-Paul Delevoye](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean-Paul_Delevoye) resigns. Delevoye, who was in charge of the proposed pension reform, failed to disclose private posts and income in his [asset declaration](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_disclosure_of_public_servants). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/16/france-pensions-chief-jean-paul-delevoye-resigns-as-transport-strike-enters-12th-day)\n\n*   [Impeachment inquiry into Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_into_Donald_Trump)\n    *   The [U.S. House Judiciary Committee](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_Committee_on_the_Judiciary) releases its 658-page report on its inquiry of the [impeachment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_in_the_United_States) of [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump), claiming he committed [obstruction of Congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contempt_of_Congress) and [abuse of power](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abuse_of_power). [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2019/12/16/politics/house-judiciary-committee-impeachment-charges-report/index.html)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   [SpaceX](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SpaceX) successfully launches the [JCSAT-18](/w/index.php?title=JCSAT-18&action=edit&redlink=1) and [Kacific 1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kacific_Broadband_Satellites) [communications satellites](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Communications_satellite) on a [Falcon 9 Block 5](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Falcon_9_Block_5) rocket from [Cape Canaveral Air Force Station](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cape_Canaveral_Air_Force_Station). The satellites will bring [Internet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet) access to isolated islands in the [Pacific Ocean](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_Ocean). [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2019/12/16/tech/spacex-launch-kacific-jcsat-scn/index.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_16','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3212,replace('# 2019-12-17\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   _[Shandong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_aircraft_carrier_Shandong)_, the first fully domestically built Chinese [aircraft carrier](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aircraft_carrier), enters [naval](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/People%27s_Liberation_Army_Navy) service. [(CGTN)](https://news.cgtn.com/news/2019-12-17/Xi-attends-commissioning-of-first-Chinese-built-aircraft-carrier-Mv4uyZPVUk/index.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Musharraf high treason case](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Musharraf_high_treason_case)\n    *   Former [President of Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Pakistan) [Pervez Musharraf](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pervez_Musharraf) is [sentenced to death](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_punishment_in_Pakistan) _[in absentia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trial_in_absentia)_ for [high treason](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High_treason), by a 2-1 majority. He is described as a [dictator](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dictator) who seized power in a [1999 coup](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1999_Pakistani_coup_d%27%C3%A9tat), imposed a [2007 state of emergency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistani_state_of_emergency,_2007) and resigned in 2008 to avoid [impeachment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Movement_to_impeach_Pervez_Musharraf). [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2019/12/17/asia/pervez-musharraf-death-sentence-pakistan-intl-hnk/index.html) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-pakistan-law-musharraf/pakistan-sentences-former-dictator-musharraf-to-death-in-absentia-idUSKBN1YL0MJ)\n*   [2016present purges in Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2016%E2%80%93present_purges_in_Turkey)\n    *   Turkish police arrest 191 people, including a mayor, accused of links with the [Glen movement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G%C3%BClen_movement) (named by Turkey as FET, a terrorist group) and of using [ByLock](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ByLock_(application)), an encrypted messaging application. [(_Daily Sabah_)](https://www.dailysabah.com/investigations/2019/12/17/mayor-190-others-arrested-in-new-wave-of-operations-against-feto)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   [Climate change in Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change_in_Australia)\n    *   A temperature of 47[C](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celsius) (116.6F) is recorded in the remote [outback](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outback) town of [Oodnadatta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oodnadatta), [South Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Australia), marking [Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia)''s hottest day on record with average temperatures of 40.9[C](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celsius), according to the [Bureau of Meteorology](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bureau_of_Meteorology). [(Sky News)](https://news.sky.com/story/australia-has-hottest-day-on-record-as-heatwave-grips-the-country-11889511)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_17','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3213,replace('# 2019-12-18\n\n## Armed conflict and attack\n\n*   [Boko Haram insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boko_Haram_insurgency)\n    *   [Boko Haram](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boko_Haram) militants open fire on civilians, killing 15 and wounding five others in a fishing village in [Chad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chad). 13 others were missing after the attack. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/chad-dozen-killed-boko-haram-attack-191218140312791.html)\n*   Gunmen kill two [police officers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_Pakistan) escorting a [polio](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polio) [vaccination](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination) team in [Lower Dir District](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lower_Dir_District), [Khyber Pakhtunkhwa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khyber_Pakhtunkhwa), [Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan). [(National Post)](https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/gunmen-in-pakistan-kill-two-police-escorting-polio-vaccinators)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [Ilham Tohti](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ilham_Tohti), an [Uyghur](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uyghur_people) [economist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Economist) serving a [life sentence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_sentence) for his criticisms of [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China)s policies in [Xinjiang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xinjiang), is awarded this years [Sakharov Prize](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sakharov_Prize). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/jailed-uighur-economist-ilham-tohti-receive-sakharov-prize-191216064925850.html)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   Pakistan pulls out of an international summit of [Muslim nations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muslim_world) in [Kuala Lumpur](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuala_Lumpur), [Malaysia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaysia), scheduled to start this Thursday. [Foreign Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Pakistan)) [Shah Mahmood Qureshi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shah_Mahmood_Qureshi) said it was done after [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia) and the [United Arab Emirates](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Arab_Emirates) expressed concern that the summit was to establish a rival bloc to the [Organisation of Islamic Cooperation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organisation_of_Islamic_Cooperation). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/pakistan-pulls-malaysia-summit-muslim-nations-191218082917256.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   The [Cabinet of Germany](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cabinet_of_Germany) proposes to ban [conversion therapy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conversion_therapy) for both [transgender](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transgender) and [gay](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gay) people. The proposal was expanded to include people between the ages of 16 and 18. [(Deutsche Welle)](https://www.dw.com/en/germanys-cabinet-approves-ban-on-gay-transgender-conversion-therapy/a-51717750)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Impeachment of Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_of_Donald_Trump)\n    *   The [United States House of Representatives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_of_Representatives) votes largely along party lines to [impeach](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_in_the_United_States) [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) for [abuse of power](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abuse_of_power) and [obstruction of Congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obstruction_of_Congress). Trump becomes the third American president to be impeached by the House, after [Andrew Johnson](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_of_Andrew_Johnson) and [Bill Clinton](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_of_Bill_Clinton). His impeachment proceedings continue on to the [Senate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Senate), which will give them a final verdict and decide whether or not he should be removed from office. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/12/18/us/politics/impeachment-vote.html?action=click&module=Spotlight&pgtype=Homepage)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   [Cosmic Vision](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cosmic_Vision)\n    *   [Arianespace](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arianespace) successfully launches the [European Space Agency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Space_Agency)''s [CHEOPS](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CHEOPS) [space telescope](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_telescope) from [Guiana Space Centre](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guiana_Space_Centre). The European observatory will search for new [exoplanets](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exoplanet) and will be able to study an exoplanet''s composition and internal structure. The launch also included [OPS-SAT](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OPS-SAT), an ESA [CubeSat](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CubeSat). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-50804258)\n\n## Sports\n\n*   [2019 Catalan protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Catalan_protests)\n    *   Despite the boycott attempt by [Democratic Tsunami](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Tsunami), [El Clsico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El_Cl%C3%A1sico) is played in [Camp Nou](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camp_Nou), [Barcelona](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barcelona), with important security measures. [(Ruptly)](https://ruptly.tv/en/events/201912182042-LIVE2242)\n    *   The first clashes between [Mossos d''Esquadra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mossos_d%27Esquadra), [Boixos Nois](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boixos_Nois) and protestors occur outside the stadium, leaving 9 arrested and 70 injured. [(_El Pas_)](https://elpais.com/ccaa/2019/12/18/catalunya/1576691270_224054.html) [(_Marca_)](https://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2019/12/18/5dfa844022601de4518b45bf.html) [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-50845732) [(_El Mundo_)](https://www.elmundo.es/deportes/futbol/primera-division/2019/12/18/5dfaaa6021efa0892f8b4643.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_18','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3214,replace('# 2019-12-20\n\n## Armed conflict and attacks\n\n*   [Syrian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Civil_War)\n    *   Fighting resumes in rebel-held northwestern [Syria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria), as [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Syria) forces capture four villages by making their first large-scale push against rebel groups since the ceasefire that ended the [2019 northwestern Syria offensive](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(April%E2%80%93August_2019)) earlier this year. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/syrian-troops-make-push-rebel-held-northwest-idlib-67856263)\n*   [Citizenship Amendment Act protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Citizenship_Amendment_Act_protests)\n    *   Further clashes between protesters and [police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_India) in the northern [state](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/States_and_union_territories_of_India) of [Uttar Pradesh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uttar_Pradesh) leaves six people dead. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/killed-india-anti-citizenship-law-protests-rumble-191220171811195.html)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) announces it will raise [military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan_Self-Defense_Forces) spending (1.1%) for an eighth consecutive year to a record high as it invests in [ballistic missile](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ballistic_missile) and air defence to counter a perceived threat from [North Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Korea) and [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-japan-economy-budget-defence/japan-government-approves-eighth-straight-defense-spending-hike-to-record-high-idUSKBN1YO05N)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [IsraeliPalestinian conflict](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israeli%E2%80%93Palestinian_conflict)\n    *   [Chief Prosecutor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prosecutor_of_the_International_Criminal_Court) of the [International Criminal Court](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Criminal_Court) [Fatou Bensouda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatou_Bensouda) announces she will launch a full investigation into allegations of [war crimes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_crime) in the [Palestinian territories](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palestinian_territories). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/icc-investigate-alleged-war-crimes-palestinian-territories-191220143949348.html)\n*   [IranJapan relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Japan_relations)\n    *   [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Iran) [Hassan Rouhani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hassan_Rouhani) meets with [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Japan) [Shinz Abe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shinz%C5%8D_Abe) in [Tokyo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokyo) to discuss renewing the [Iranian nuclear deal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint_Comprehensive_Plan_of_Action). Rouhani is the first Iranian president to visit Japan in over 19 years. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/iran-rouhani-visits-japan-nuclear-deal-impasse-191220153826601.html)\n*   [Foreign relations of Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foreign_relations_of_Saudi_Arabia)\n    *   [Twitter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twitter) bans almost 6,000 accounts, alleging that they were "amplifying messages favourable to Saudi authorities" in a [Saudi state](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia)\-backed coordination. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50872118)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   In _Urgenda Foundation v. State of the Netherlands_, the [Supreme Court of the Netherlands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supreme_Court_of_the_Netherlands) upholds a 2015 ruling that "protection from the potentially devastating effects of [climate change](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change)" is a [human right](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights), ordering the [Dutch government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cabinet_of_the_Netherlands) to cut [greenhouse gas emissions](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greenhouse_gas#Direct_greenhouse_gas_emissions) by at least 25% by the end of 2020 compared to 1990 levels. [(climatecasechart.com)](http://climatecasechart.com/non-us-case/urgenda-foundation-v-kingdom-of-the-netherlands/) [(AP)](https://apnews.com/5534fe18ac5352ba43c74c9a64d6a20a)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Brexit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brexit)\n    *   The [House of Commons of the United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_of_Commons_of_the_United_Kingdom) votes 358234 to pass the [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_the_United_Kingdom)''s [Brexit withdrawal agreement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brexit_withdrawal_agreement) for the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom) to leave the [European Union](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union) on 31 January 2020. The bill will now head to the [House of Lords](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_of_Lords) for final approval. The bill also rules out extending trade talks with the EU beyond 31 December 2020, known as the "transition period". [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-50870939)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   [Boeing Orbital Flight Test](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_Orbital_Flight_Test)\n    *   An [Atlas V N22](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlas_V#Variants) rocket successfully launches the first space-faring [Boeing Starliner](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_CST-100_Starliner) spacecraft during the [Boe-OFT](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_Orbital_Flight_Test) mission. However, an issue with the spacecraft''s [mission elapsed time](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mission_elapsed_time) clock immediately after launch causes the premature depletion of the spacecraft''s attitude control fuel, precluding the spacecraft''s planned rendezvous with the [International Space Station](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Space_Station). An early reentry and landing of the spacecraft at the [White Sands Missile Range](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_Sands_Missile_Range) is planned for 22 December. [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2019/12/20/790098677/in-uncrewed-test-boeings-starliner-capsule-fails-to-reach-space-station)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_20','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3215,replace('# 2019-12-21\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Somali Civil War (2009present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somali_Civil_War_(2009%E2%80%93present))\n    *   A [suicide attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicide_attack) by [car bomb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Car_bomb) in [Galkayo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galkayo), [Somalia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somalia), kills at least seven [civilians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian), though the death toll is expected to rise according to military officials. According to a military spokesman, the suicide bomber tried to enter a hotel compound but failed and hit a military pickup. No group has claimed responsibility yet. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-somalia-attack-galkayo/suicide-bomb-outside-somali-hotel-kills-at-least-seven-military-idUSKBN1YP0KT)\n*   [Islamic insurgency in the Maghreb (2002present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_insurgency_in_the_Maghreb_(2002%E2%80%93present)), [Operation Barkhane](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Barkhane)\n    *   During his visit to [West Africa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Africa), [French President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_France) [Emmanuel Macron](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emmanuel_Macron) says that French forces killed 33 [Islamist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamism) militants in central [Mali](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mali) earlier that day. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/21/french-forces-kill-33-islamic-extremists-in-mali-says-macron)\n*   [Libyan Crisis (2011present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Crisis_(2011%E2%80%93present)), [LibyaTurkey relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya%E2%80%93Turkey_relations)\n    *   The [Libyan Coast Guard](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Coast_Guard) loyal to [Field marshal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_marshal_(Libya)) [Khalifa Haftar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khalifa_Haftar) seizes a [Grenada](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grenada)\-flagged ship with a [Turkish](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turks) crew off the coast of [Derna, Libya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Derna,_Libya), according to a spokesman for the [Libyan National Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_National_Army). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-security-turkey/eastern-libyan-forces-seize-ship-with-a-turkish-crew-spokesman-idUSKBN1YP0LW)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Nord Stream 2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nord_Stream_2) says it will finish construction "as soon as possible" after a contractor suspends pipe-laying work due to U.S. sanctions on the Russian gas pipeline to Europe. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-russia-nord-stream-completion/nord-stream-2-to-press-on-with-europe-gas-pipe-despite-u-s-sanctions-idUSKBN1YP061)\n*   [RussiaUkraine relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia%E2%80%93Ukraine_relations)\n    *   [Russia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia) and [Ukraine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine) reach a new five-year agreement on gas transit. [(AP)](https://apnews.com/5025492604b2378ef41e5e040351814c)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A fire at an apartment building in [Las Vegas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Las_Vegas), [Nevada](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nevada), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States), kills six people and injures thirteen others. [(Associated Press)](https://www.abc12.com/content/news/Fire-in-Las-Vegas-apartment-complex-kills-6-injures-13-566405781.html)\n*   A bus collides with a truck near [Gualn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gual%C3%A1n), [Guatemala](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guatemala), killing at least 21 people including seven children, according to the [Guatemalan Public Ministry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministries_of_Guatemala). [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2019/12/21/americas/guatemala-bus-crash/index.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Censorship in Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Censorship_in_Pakistan), [Blasphemy in Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blasphemy_in_Pakistan), [Capital punishment in Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_punishment_in_Pakistan)\n    *   A court in [Multan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multan), [Punjab](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab,_Pakistan), [Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan), sentences [university](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University) [professor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Professor) [Junaid Hafeez](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Junaid_Hafeez) to death for [blasphemy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blasphemy)  verbal and on [Facebook](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facebook). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/pakistani-academic-junaid-hafeez-sentenced-death-blasphemy-191221091139428.html)\n*   The [Royal Canadian Mounted Police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Canadian_Mounted_Police) arrest two suspects after they allegedly made online [death threats](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death_threat) to [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Canada) [Justin Trudeau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Justin_Trudeau). Trudeau had to wear a [bulletproof vest](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulletproof_vest) during a visit to [Mississauga, Ontario](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mississauga,_Ontario), due to the threats made during his electoral campaign. [(Yahoo! News Canada)](https://ca.news.yahoo.com/rcmp-arrests-2-alleged-online-184209881.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_21','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3216,replace('# 2019-12-22\n\n## Armed conflict and attacks\n\n*   [Crisis in Venezuela](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crisis_in_Venezuela)\n    *   Attackers raid a [military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Bolivarian_Armed_Forces_of_Venezuela) facility in the southern state of [Bolvar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bol%C3%ADvar_(state)), killing one soldier and stealing weapons. Authorities say the weapons are recovered and opposition-linked suspects are arrested. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-venezuela-military/southern-venezuela-military-facility-raided-one-soldier-dead-officials-idUSKBN1YQ0M9)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [British](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom) retailer [Tesco](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tesco) suspends operations at a factory in [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) after the _[Sunday Times](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunday_Times)_ newspaper reports that a six-year-old in [London](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London) found a message from [Shanghai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shanghai) prisoners calling for help and urging whoever finds the message to alert a [human rights organisation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights_organisation), with a link to the author of the story, hidden inside a pack of [charity Christmas cards](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charity_Christmas_card). Tesco says that it has a policy against using [prison labour](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prison_labour). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-50883161)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [201920 Australian bushfire season](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Australian_bushfire_season)\n    *   [Fire and Rescue NSW](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fire_and_Rescue_NSW) firefighters gain access to previously cut-off towns and settlements by [bushfires](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bushfires_in_Australia) in [New South Wales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_South_Wales), taking advantage of cooler weather. The small town of [Balmoral](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balmoral,_New_South_Wales_(Southern_Highlands)) is reported as being destroyed with NSW Premier [Gladys Berejiklian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gladys_Berejiklian) saying there''s "not much left" of the town. [(_Daily Telegraph_)](https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/nsw/black-christmas-record-number-of-fireys-battle-terrifying-blazes/news-story/a8c4f2e3fbc15b85b9dc98f237b3605f) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-australia-bushfires/australian-firefighters-access-badly-burned-towns-pm-defends-climate-policies-idUSKBN1YP0MG)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   A riot at a [maximum security](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maximum_security) [prison](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prison) in [El Porvenir, Atlntida](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El_Porvenir,_Atl%C3%A1ntida), [Honduras](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honduras) leaves at least 16 inmates dead, according to Honduran authorities. The riot comes just two days after another riot killed 18 inmates at a prison in the town of [Tela](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tela). [(AP)](https://apnews.com/796606438edfbd2d5a79a7e200aa18f1)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Afghan presidential election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Afghan_presidential_election)\n    *   [Afghanistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan)''s incumbent [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Afghanistan) [Ashraf Ghani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashraf_Ghani) wins a slim majority of the votes in a September 28 election, delayed preliminary results showed after a poll that plunged the country into political crisis and was marred by allegations of fraud. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-afghanistan-election/afghanistans-ghani-wins-slim-majority-of-presidential-vote-in-preliminary-results-idUSKBN1YQ054)\n*   [2019 Croatian presidential election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Croatian_presidential_election)\n    *   Citizens of [Croatia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Croatia) cast their votes in the latest [presidential election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elections_in_Croatia). [(DW)](https://www.dw.com/en/croatians-head-to-presidential-polls-in-tight-race/a-51770348)\n*   [2019 Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Hong_Kong_protests)\n    *   Over a thousand protestors march in the [financial district](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central,_Hong_Kong) of [Hong Kong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong) to show solidarity with [Uyghur](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uyghurs) [Muslims](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islam_in_China) in [Xinjiang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xinjiang). A dozen [police officers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong_Police_Force) clash with the crowd to disperse them. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-protests/clashes-as-police-try-to-clear-hong-kong-protesters-after-uighur-support-rally-idUSKBN1YQ076)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   [Boeing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing)''s unmanned [CST-100 Starliner](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_CST-100_Starliner) crew capsule successfully reenters the atmosphere and lands at [White Sands Missile Range](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_Sands_Missile_Range) in [New Mexico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Mexico), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States), after a failed rendezvous with the [International Space Station](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Space_Station). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/science/2019/dec/22/nasa-boeing-starliner-capsule-lands-safely-new-mexico)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_22','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3217,replace('# 2019-12-24\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) insurgents ambush an [Afghan National Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_National_Army) [checkpoint](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Security_checkpoint), killing 15 members of the security forces. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-afghanistan-attack/taliban-kill-15-in-attack-on-afghan-security-checkpoint-local-officials-idUSKBN1YS0K2)\n*   [Syrian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Civil_War), [Northwestern Syria offensive (November 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(November_2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   The [Syrian Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Army) continues its offensive in southern [Idlib Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib_Governorate) towards the key rebel-held city of [Ma''arrat al-Nu''man](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ma%27arrat_al-Nu%27man), capturing several towns and villages, including [Jarjnaz](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jarjnaz) and [Sarman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarman). Around 30,000 [civilians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian) have fled the area in recent days, according to the [Syrian Observatory for Human Rights](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Observatory_for_Human_Rights). [(Channel News Asia)](https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/syria-regime-forces-surround-turkish-army-post-in-idlib--12207822)\n    *   A war monitor reports that eight peopleincluding five childrenwere killed after a missile struck a school in [Jobas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jobas), [Idlib District](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib_District), used as a shelter for displaced civilians. Opposition activists blame [Russia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/children-killed-syria-missile-hits-school-191224115623082.html)\n*   [Arbinda attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arbinda_attack)\n    *   Thirty-five civilians are dead and six others are injured after [jihadists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jihadists) stormed the town of [Arbinda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arbinda), [Soum Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soum_Province), [Burkina Faso](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burkina_Faso), and its military base, killing seven [soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burkina_Faso_Armed_Forces). Eighty militants were also killed. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-50908880)\n*   [Boko Haram insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boko_Haram_insurgency)\n    *   Gunmen attacked the Christian village of [Chibok](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chibok), killing seven [Christians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christianity). It is believed the attack was targeted for [Christmas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christmas) to send a message. [(VOA News)](https://www.voanews.com/africa/7-killed-nigeria-jihadist-attack-christmas-eve)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A bus plunges into a [ravine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ravine) in [South Sumatra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sumatra), [Indonesia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indonesia), killing at least 25 people. [(Sky News)](https://news.sky.com/story/sumatra-bus-crash-25-killed-after-262ft-ravine-plunge-11894592)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [United StatesZambia relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States%E2%80%93Zambia_relations), [LGBT rights in Zambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_rights_in_Zambia)\n    *   Sources report that the [U.S.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) has recalled its [ambassador to Zambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Ambassador_to_Zambia) after a row over a conviction of men who were sentenced to prison in [Zambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zambia) for consensual [homosexual acts](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gay_sexual_practices). [President of Zambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Zambia) [Edgar Lungu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edgar_Lungu) declared ambassador [Daniel Lewis Foote](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_Lewis_Foote) _[persona non grata](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persona_non_grata)_ because he had criticized the verdict while accusing Zambia of not actively prosecuting misappropriation of [donor aid](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aid). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-50901537)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   The [Council of Representatives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Representatives_of_Iraq) passes a series of electoral laws to placate protestors. The laws will allow voters to [select individuals](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single-member_district) rather than use [party lists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Party-list_proportional_representation), and the candidates will represent [electoral districts](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electoral_district) rather than [provinces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Governorates_of_Iraq). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-protests/iraq-passes-electoral-reforms-but-deadlock-remains-idUSKBN1YS157?il=0)\n*   Thousands of [Ethiopian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopia) [Muslims](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islam_in_Ethiopia) march across the country in response to attacks last Friday that saw four [mosques](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mosque) and multiple Muslim-owned businesses burned in the [Amhara Region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amhara_Region). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/ethiopian-muslims-protest-mosques-burned-191224141944689.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_24','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3218,replace('# 2019-12-25\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) militants say they have [kidnapped](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kidnap) 27 local [peace activists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peace_activist) in [Farah Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Farah_Province) as they were traveling from [Herat Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herat_Province). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-afghanitan-kidnapping/27-local-peace-activists-abducted-in-western-afghanistan-idUSKBN1YT0FB)\n*   [Arbinda attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arbinda_attack)\n    *   In [Burkina Faso](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burkina_Faso), the [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Burkina_Faso) orders 48 hours of [mourning](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mourning) after the [jihadist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jihadist) attack yesterday in [Soum Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soum_Province). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/mourning-burkina-faso-attack-kills-dozens-191225001927810.html)\n    *   A dozen [Burkina Faso soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burkina_Faso_Armed_Forces) are killed in an armed attack in the night by militants responsible for the previous attack. [(DW News)](https://www.dw.com/en/burkina-faso-tense-in-mourning-amid-jihadist-attacks/a-51795594)\n*   Two "wanted [terrorists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_Saudi_Arabia)" are killed in [Dammam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dammam), [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia), after exchanging gunfire with security forces. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-saudi-security/saudi-security-forces-kill-two-terrorists-after-dammam-city-shooting-tv-idUSKBN1YT0KU)\n*   [Israeli Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israeli_Prime_Minister) [Benjamin Netanyahu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benjamin_Netanyahu) is briefly brought to a [bomb shelter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bomb_shelter) during an election rally in [Ashkelon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashkelon), [Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel), after a rocket is fired from the [Gaza Strip](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaza_Strip). The rocket is intercepted with no casualties reported. [(NBCWashington)](https://www.nbcwashington.com/news/national-international/israel-gaza-rocket-intercepted-as-pm-held-election-rally/2192244/) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-israel-palestinians-violence/gaza-rocket-sends-netanyahu-to-shelter-during-campaign-rally-tv-idUSKBN1YT0P6?)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [Notre-Dame de Paris fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Notre-Dame_de_Paris_fire)\n    *   [Notre-Dame](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Notre-Dame_de_Paris) [rector](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rector_(ecclesiastical)) Patrick Chauvet states there is "maybe a 50 percent chance that \[the building\] will be saved" due to deterioration of [scaffolding](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scaffolding) near the vaults, and that renovations will not start until 2021 at the soonest. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/notre-dame-rector-fragile-cathedral-saved-191225163613989.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Japanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Japan) [National Diet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Diet) member [Tsukasa Akimoto](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsukasa_Akimoto) of the ruling [Liberal Democratic Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liberal_Democratic_Party_(Japan)) is arrested for allegedly receiving up to [](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_yen)3 million in bribes from a [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) company interested in setting up a [casino](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casino) in the country. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-japan-casino-corruption/japan-ruling-party-lawmaker-arrested-on-casino-bribery-suspicion-prosecutors-idUSKBN1YT03N?il=0)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   The largest [parlamentary](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_Representatives_of_Iraq) [bloc](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bloc_(politics)), Binaa Bloc, including [Fatah Alliance](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatah_Alliance) and [State of Law Coalition](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_of_Law_Coalition), nominates [Basra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basra_Governorate) governor [Asaad Al Eidani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asaad_Al_Eidani) to succeed [Adil Abdul-Mahdi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adil_Abdul-Mahdi) as [Prime Minister of Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Iraq). Protesters reject the nomination, seeing him as part of the establishment. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/iraq-iran-backed-bloc-nominates-basra-governor-pm-191225124512897.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_25','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3219,replace('# 2019-12-26\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Libyan Civil War (2014present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Civil_War_(2014%E2%80%93present)), [LibyaTurkey relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya%E2%80%93Turkey_relations)\n    *   [Turkish](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey) [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Turkey) [Recep Tayyip Erdoan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo%C4%9Fan) announces he will send [troops](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_Armed_Forces) to [Libya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya) to help the internationally-recognized [Tripoli](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tripoli)\-based [Government of National Accord](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_National_Accord) after they requested support. He plans to submit his motion to the [Grand National Assembly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_National_Assembly_of_Turkey) on January 7 for approval. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/erdogan-announces-plan-send-troops-libya-191226090214331.html)\n*   [Insurgency in the Maghreb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Insurgency_in_the_Maghreb_(2002%E2%80%93present))\n    *   Fourteen [Nigerien soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger_Armed_Forces) are killed by heavily armed militant gunmen who ambushed the convoy in the [Tillabri Region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tillab%C3%A9ri_Region) of [Niger](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger). [(France24)](https://www.france24.com/en/20191226-niger-authorities-say-14-troops-killed-during-ambush-g5-sahel-force-west-africa)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Capital punishment in Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_punishment_in_Japan)\n    *   [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) [executes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hanging#Japan) a foreigner for the first time since the disclosure of details of its sentences began in 2007. He was a [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_people_in_Japan) man convicted of killing a family of four. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-japan-deathpenalty/japan-executes-first-foreigner-in-years-a-chinese-man-who-killed-a-family-idUSKBN1YU07N) [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-50916494)\n*   [Censorship in Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Censorship_in_Turkey)\n    *   The [Constitutional Court of Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitutional_Court_of_Turkey) orders the immediate lifting of the [block of Wikipedia in Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Block_of_Wikipedia_in_Turkey), ruling it a [violation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights#Violations) of the [freedom of expression](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freedom_of_expression). In response to the news, Wikipedia co-founder [Jimmy Wales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimmy_Wales) says, "Welcome back, Turkey!" [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/26/turkish-court-wikipedia-block-lifted)\n*   [2020 Ivorian general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Ivorian_general_election)\n    *   In [Ivory Coast](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ivory_Coast), former rebel leader, prime minister and presidential candidate for next year''s general election, [Guillaume Soro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guillaume_Soro), could face prison for life over an alleged [coup](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coup) plot that involved amassing weapons, says the country''s public prosecutor. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ivorycoast-politics/ivory-coast-says-presidential-candidate-soro-plotted-a-coup-idUSKBN1YU14A?il=0)\n*   A court in [Morocco](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morocco) sentences a man to four years in prison for insulting the [king](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_of_Morocco). Authorities also arrest a [Twitter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twitter) user for criticizing the long prison terms given to those who protest. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-morocco-trial/morocco-jails-one-man-detains-another-over-criticism-of-authorities-on-social-media-idUSKBN1YU16M)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Citizenship Amendment Act protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Citizenship_Amendment_Act_protests)\n    *   [Chief Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chief_Minister) of [Uttar Pradesh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uttar_Pradesh) [Yogi Adityanath](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yogi_Adityanath) threatens to confiscate property from more than 200 people, mostly [Muslims](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islam_in_India), allegedly to pay for damages caused by protesters. The northern [Indian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India) [state](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/States_and_union_territories_of_India) has seen the most violence from the protests, with 18 out of the 25 killings happening there. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/indian-state-warns-law-protesters-confiscate-property-191226111207708.html)\n*   [Freedom of religion in Montenegro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freedom_of_religion_in_Montenegro)\n    *   Hundreds of protesters, mostly consisting of supporters of the pro-[Serbia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serbia) opposition bloc, march in [Podgorica](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Podgorica), [Montenegro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montenegro), to protest a proposed law that would require [religious communities](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Religion_in_Montenegro) to provide proof of property ownership from before the [creation of Yugoslavia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Creation_of_Yugoslavia) in 1918. Protesters claim the law unfairly targets the predominant [Serbian Orthodox Church](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serbian_Orthodox_Church). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-montenegro-protest/serbs-protest-in-montenegro-ahead-of-vote-on-religious-law-idUSKBN1YU0WC?il=0)\n*   [2020 Israeli legislative election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Israeli_legislative_election)\n    *   [Israeli](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel) [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Israel) [Benjamin Netanyahu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benjamin_Netanyahu) survives a primary challenge from former [Education Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Education_(Israel)) [Gideon Sa''ar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gideon_Sa%27ar) with 72% of the vote. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/26/israel-voting-under-way-in-likud-primary-seen-as-threat-to-netanyahu)\n*   [2019 Iraqi protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Iraqi_protests)\n    *   [Iraqi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq) [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Iraq) [Barham Salih](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barham_Salih) rejects the nomination of [Basra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basra_Governorate) governor [Asaad Al Eidani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asaad_Al_Eidani) for [Prime Minister of Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Iraq), stating that protesters will also oppose him due to his connections with [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran)\-backed [parties](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_political_parties_in_Iraq). As the [constitution](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitution_of_Iraq) doesn''t give him the power to officially veto candidates, Salih threatens to resign instead. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/iraq-president-threatens-quit-pm-nominee-191226132315483.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_26','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3220,replace('# 2019-12-28\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Somali Civil War (2009present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somali_Civil_War_(2009%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [December 2019 Mogadishu bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/December_2019_Mogadishu_bombing)\n        *   A [suicide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicide_attack) [truck bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Car_bomb) at a [security checkpoint](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Security_checkpoint) in [Mogadishu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mogadishu) kills at least 79 people and injures 149 others. No group has claimed responsibility. [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2019/12/28/africa/somalia-unrest-bombing-intl/index.html)\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   A [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) attack on an [Afghan military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_National_Army) base in [Sangin District](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sangin_District), [Helmand Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helmand_Province), kills at least 10 Afghan soldiers and injures 4 others. [(VOA)](https://www.voanews.com/south-central-asia/taliban-assault-army-base-kills-10-afghan-soldiers)\n*   [Terrorism in the United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_the_United_States), [Antisemitism in the United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antisemitism_in_the_United_States)\n    *   Five people are injured in a mass stabbing at the home of a [Hasidic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hasidic_Judaism) [rabbi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rabbi), which was hosting [Hanukkah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hanukkah) celebrations, in [Monsey, New York](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monsey,_New_York). The suspect was later apprehended by [the police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_City_Police_Department). [New York](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_(state)) [governor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Governor_of_New_York) [Andrew Cuomo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Cuomo) calls it an "act of domestic terrorism". [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/nypd-adl-monitoring-reports-of-stabbing-at-synagogue/2019/12/28/4eb05460-29f5-11ea-9cc9-e19cfbc87e51_story.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A [North Korean ghost ship](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Korean_ghost_ships) washes up on the shore of [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan)''s [Sado Island](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sado,_Niigata), containing the corpses of five people onboard, suspected to be fishermen. The bodies are described by [Japanese police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_police) as "partially skeletonised", suggesting the boat has been adrift at sea for a long time. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-50934145)\n*   Five people are killed when a plane crashes near a [Walmart](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walmart) supermarket in [Lafayette](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lafayette,_Louisiana), [Louisiana](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louisiana). One occupant survives, while three others on the ground are injured. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-50935208)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Corruption in Vietnam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corruption_in_Vietnam)\n    *   A court in [Vietnam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietnam) sentences former information minister Nguyen Bac Son to [life in prison](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_in_prison) after finding him guilty of accepting $3 million in kickbacks via an overpriced purchase of Audio Visual Global JSC for nearly 8.9 trillion dong ($383.7 million) in late 2015 by [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Vietnam)\-owned company [MobiFone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MobiFone). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-vietnam-corruption/vietnam-court-sentences-ex-minister-to-life-in-mobifone-corruption-scandal-idUSKBN1YW02M?il=0)\n*   [Prostitution in China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prostitution_in_China)\n    *   The [National People''s Congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_People%27s_Congress) abolishes the use of [forced labor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unfree_labour) to punish [sex workers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sex_worker), but states that [prostitution](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prostitution) will remain illegal. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-lawmaking-prostitution/china-scraps-extra-judicial-forced-labor-for-sex-workers-idUSKBN1YW08M?il=0)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Algerian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Algerian_protests)\n    *   [Algerian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algeria) [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Algeria) [Abdelmadjid Tebboune](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdelmadjid_Tebboune) appoints former [University of Algiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Algiers) professor [Abdelaziz Djerrad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdelaziz_Djerrad) to be the new [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Algeria). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-algeria-politics/algeria-names-new-prime-minister-idUSKBN1YW08G?il=0)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_28','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3221,replace('# 2019-12-30\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [December 2019 Mogadishu bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/December_2019_Mogadishu_bombing)\n    *   [Al-Shabaab](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Shabaab_(militant_group)), an ally of [Al-Qaeda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Qaeda), claims responsibility for the attack in [Mogadishu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mogadishu), Somalia, that killed nearly 90 people. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-somalia-blast/al-qaeda-ally-claims-responsibility-for-somalia-blast-that-killed-90-people-idUSKBN1YY16C)\n*   [Allied Democratic Forces insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Democratic_Forces_insurgency)\n    *   [ADF](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Democratic_Forces) militants kill twenty-two people in eastern [Democratic Republic of the Congo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo). They were all hacked with machetes and many also went missing in the attack. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/rebels-hack-civilians-death-eastern-drc-attack-191230182423732.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [201920 Australian bushfire season](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Australian_bushfire_season)\n    *   Thousands of people are reported stranded on a local beach awaiting evacuation near [Mallacoota, Victoria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mallacoota,_Victoria), [Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia), as [bushfires](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bushfires_in_Australia) enter the coastal town. Four people are reported missing. Elsewhere, a volunteer [Fire and Rescue NSW](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fire_and_Rescue_NSW) firefighter died battling a bushfire near the town of [Jingellic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jingellic). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/dec/31/mallacoota-fire-mayhem-armageddon-bushfires-rage-victoria-east-gippsland)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [BoliviaSpain relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolivia%E2%80%93Spain_relations), [BoliviaMexico relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolivia%E2%80%93Mexico_relations)\n    *   In a tit-for-tat move, [Spain](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spain) expels three [Bolivian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolivia) diplomatic staff from [Madrid](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madrid) after interim [Bolivian President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Bolivia) [Jeanine ez](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeanine_%C3%81%C3%B1ez) forced two Spanish diplomats and the [Mexican](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico) ambassador to leave. Their expulsions are related to the Mexican embassy in [La Paz](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/La_Paz)''s decision to shelter at least nine officials connected to [the government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Presidency_of_Evo_Morales) of deposed President [Evo Morales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evo_Morales). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/bolivia-spat-spain-mexico-deepens-morales-allies-191230153945637.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Lulu and Nana controversy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lulu_and_Nana_controversy)\n    *   [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) state news agency [Xinhua](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xinhua_News_Agency) reports that [He Jiankui](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/He_Jiankui), who last year announced the birth of babies with modified [DNA](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DNA), was sentenced to three years imprisonment and a fine of 3 million [yuan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Renminbi), for "[illegal medical practice](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_malpractice)". Two other defendants are given lesser sentences. [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2019/12/30/china/gene-scientist-china-intl-hnk/index.html)\n    *   The court in [Shenzhen](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shenzhen) confirms his claim that a second woman was impregnated, and reveals that three [gene-edited](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genome_editing) babies were born instead of the previously believed two. [(New Scientist)](https://www.newscientist.com/article/2228710-scientist-behind-worlds-first-gene-edited-babies-sentenced-to-prison/)\n*   A [Sudanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudan) court sentences 29 people to be hanged for the killing of a teacher in detention in February during protests that led to the overthrow of former president [Omar al-Bashir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omar_al-Bashir). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-50945224)\n*   A [Yemeni](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemenis) man, suspected to be an [Al-Qaeda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Qaeda) militant, is sentenced to death in [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia) for a November 11 [terror attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terror_attack) against a group of Spanish theatre actors in [Riyadh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riyadh), wounding three of them. An accomplice is sentenced to 12 years of jail. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-50947324)\n*   Former CEO of the [RenaultNissanMitsubishi Alliance](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Renault%E2%80%93Nissan%E2%80%93Mitsubishi_Alliance) [Carlos Ghosn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Ghosn) escapes house arrest in [Tokyo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokyo) and flees to [Lebanon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanon). He was under arrest for money laundering and underreporting his income, though he denies the charges. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-renault-nissan-ghosn-lebanon/ousted-renault-nissan-boss-ghosn-leaves-japan-for-lebanon-idUSKBN1YY1FM)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_30','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3222,replace('# 2019-12-31\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [American-led intervention in Iraq (2014present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American-led_intervention_in_Iraq_(2014%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Angry supporters storm](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attack_on_the_United_States_embassy_in_Baghdad) the [United States embassy in Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embassy_of_the_United_States,_Baghdad), [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq), in response to [the U.S. airstrike on Sunday](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_United_States_bombing_of_Kata%27ib_Hizbollah) against [Kata''ib Hezbollah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kata%27ib_Hezbollah) militants. Iraqi officials say the U.S. ambassador and staff have been evacuated, but the [U.S. Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Army) denies this. The U.S. ambassador is reportedly on holiday. [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._President) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) blames [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) for the attack. [(_The Independent_)](https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/iraq-protests-american-embassy-attack-violence-police-a9265131.html) [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/31/iraq-riots-embassy-expose-america-weaker-fewer-options)\n    *   According to an Iraqi official, demonstrators have prepared a [sit-in](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sit-in) protest in front of the embassy. [(Xinhua)](http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2019-12/31/c_138669405.htm)\n    *   [Protesters in Tahrir Square](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Iraqi_protests) distance themselves from the events around the U.S. embassy. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/12/protesters-embassy-baghdad-gear-sit-191231130210231.html)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Tencent](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tencent), along with [Singaporean](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Singapore) [sovereign wealth fund](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sovereign_wealth_fund) [GIC Private Limited](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GIC_Private_Limited) and the [Qatar Investment Authority](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qatar_Investment_Authority), purchase a 10% stake in the [Universal Music Group](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Universal_Music_Group). The former purchased it to build up [its own music streaming service](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tencent_Music). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-vivendi-universal/tencent-gets-into-global-groove-with-stake-in-vivendis-universal-idUSKBN1YZ0HF)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   An 8 meters (26ft) high fire ignites accidentally next to [Adelaide Oval](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adelaide_Oval) after the 9pm [New Year''s Eve](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Year%27s_Eve) fireworks in [Adelaide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adelaide), [South Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Australia). This comes following major controversy over the [New Year](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Year)''s [firework displays](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Firework_display) across [Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia) in response to [ongoing bushfires](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Australian_bushfire_season). [(News.com.au)](https://www.news.com.au/sport/cricket/big-bash/bbl09-adelaide-strikers-vs-sydney-thunder-live-blog/live-coverage/7f0d7331e1d59f06c536323f5cf6d254)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   A court in [Abidjan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abidjan) sentences [Charles Bl Goud](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Bl%C3%A9_Goud%C3%A9) to 20 years in prison _[in absentia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In_absentia)_ for his role in the [Second Ivorian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Ivorian_Civil_War) that followed the 2010 presidential election, his lawyers say. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ivorycoast-justice/ivory-coast-street-militia-leader-sentenced-to-20-years-for-role-in-civil-war-idUSKBN1YZ0S7)\n*   Former [Bosnian Serb Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Army_of_Republika_Srpska) general Milomir Savi is indicted for his role in planning the [Srebrenica massacre](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Srebrenica_massacre). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bosnia-warcrimes/bosnia-indicts-serb-army-general-over-srebrenica-genocide-idUSKBN1YZ11X?il=0)\n*   Aftermath of the [2019 Fresno shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Fresno_shooting)\n    *   Police arrest six people in connection with a mass shooting last month in [Fresno, California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fresno,_California) that left four people dead and another six injured. [(_USA Today_)](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2019/12/31/fresno-mass-shooting-arrests-deadly-backyard-shooting/2783554001/)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2019_December_31','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3223,replace('# 2020-01-02\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Libyan Civil War (2014present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Civil_War_(2014%E2%80%93present))\n    *   The [Turkish](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey) [Grand National Assembly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_National_Assembly_of_Turkey) votes 325184 to send [troops](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_Armed_Forces) to help the internationally-recognized [Government of National Accord](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_National_Accord) in [Libya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/turkey-parliament-approves-military-deployment-libya-200102113511422.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [2020 New Taipei helicopter crash](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_New_Taipei_helicopter_crash)\n    *   A [UH-60 Black Hawk](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sikorsky_UH-60_Black_Hawk) helicopter carrying 13 people crashes in [New Taipei](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Taipei), [Taiwan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taiwan). Eight people are killed, including the [Chief of the General Staff](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chief_of_the_General_Staff_(Republic_of_China)) [Shen Yi-ming](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shen_Yi-ming), the head of the [Republic of China Armed Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_China_Armed_Forces). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/02/taiwans-military-chief-missing-helicopter-crash)\n*   [201920 Australian bushfire season](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Australian_bushfire_season)\n    *   [New South Wales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_South_Wales) [Premier](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Premier_of_New_South_Wales) [Gladys Berejiklian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gladys_Berejiklian) declares a [state of emergency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_of_emergency) for seven days starting on January 3. [(News.com.au)](https://www.news.com.au/technology/environment/nsw-premier-gladys-berejiklian-declares-state-of-emergency/news-story/8651cf93eb1fe85e3866221ed567a88c)\n    *   An elderly woman dies of suffocation while departing from a [Brisbane](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brisbane), [Queensland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queensland)\-originated [Qantas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qantas) plane at [Canberra Airport](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canberra_Airport). [Canberra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canberra)''s [air quality](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_quality) had been reported as the worst in the world because of heavy smoke from the bushfires in [New South Wales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_South_Wales). [(News.com.au)](https://www.news.com.au/travel/travel-updates/incidents/woman-dies-from-bushfire-smoke-in-canberra-after-exiting-qantas-plane/news-story/280f1c9bb729c5c4f3377f97936b5cda)\n    *   A second person is confirmed dead in the [East Gippsland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Gippsland) region of [Victoria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Victoria_(Australia)) as thousands of people are evacuated from [Mallacoota](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mallacoota,_Victoria) by sea. [State premier](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Premier_of_Victoria) [Daniel Andrews](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_Andrews) has declared a [state of disaster](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_of_disaster) in six government areas. 17 people remain missing. [(News.com.au)](https://www.news.com.au/technology/environment/australian-troops-prepare-for-bushfire-emergency-evacuations-by-sea/live-coverage/cf3d149ec9bbb9b7eb808e663eec8a28)\n*   A military plane crashes shortly after takeoff from an airport in [Sudan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudan)''s [West Darfur](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Darfur), killing the 18 people on board. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-50978258)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [ChinaUnited Kingdom relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China%E2%80%93United_Kingdom_relations)\n    *   [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) temporarily suspends plans to cross-link companies on the [London](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London_Stock_Exchange) and [Shanghai Stock Exchange](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shanghai_Stock_Exchange) due to increased political tensions between the two nations, particularly [Britain](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom)''s stance on the [Hong Kong protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%932020_Hong_Kong_protests). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-britain-ipos-exclusive/exclusive-china-halts-british-stock-link-over-political-tensions-sources-idUSKBN1Z108L)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   Lebanese justice minister says he has received an [arrest warrant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arrest_warrant) from [Interpol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpol) against former Chairman of [Nissan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nissan), [Carlos Ghosn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Ghosn), who escaped [house arrest](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_arrest) in [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) and fled to [Lebanon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanon) days ago. [(AP via Washington Post)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/lebanese-justice-minister-says-lebanon-has-received-an-interpol-issued-wanted-notice-for-nissans-ex-chair-carlos-ghosn/2020/01/02/5641ca3c-2d5c-11ea-bffe-020c88b3f120_story.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Democratic_Party_presidential_primaries)\n    *   Former [Secretary of Housing and Urban Development](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Secretary_of_Housing_and_Urban_Development) [Julian Castro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julian_Castro) drops out of the presidential race. [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2020/01/02/774556481/julian-castro-drops-out-of-the-democratic-presidential-race)\n*   [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy)''s ruling [Five Star Movement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five_Star_Movement) expels [Senator](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Senate_of_the_Republic_(Italy)) [Gianluigi Paragone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gianluigi_Paragone) from its ranks over disciplinary issues, shrinking [the coalition](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conte_II_Cabinet)''s majority in the Senate to five. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-5star/italys-5-star-expels-senator-further-reducing-slim-government-majority-idUSKBN1Z10T0?il=0)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_2','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3224,replace('# 2020-01-04\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Iranian intervention in Iraq (2014present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iranian_intervention_in_Iraq_(2014%E2%80%93present)), [20192020 Persian Gulf crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%932020_Persian_Gulf_crisis), [American-led intervention in Iraq (2014present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American-led_intervention_in_Iraq_(2014%E2%80%93present)), Aftermath of the [Attack on the United States embassy in Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attack_on_the_United_States_embassy_in_Baghdad), [2020 Baghdad International Airport airstrike](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Baghdad_International_Airport_airstrike)\n    *   Militants fire rockets at [Iraqi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq) bases supporting [U.S. personnel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Armed_Forces), nearly hitting the [U.S. Embassy in Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embassy_of_the_United_States,_Baghdad). [(FT)](https://www.ft.com/content/7c49646a-2f28-11ea-9703-eea0cae3f0de)\n    *   U.S. president [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) vows to target 52 sites significant to Iranians and Iranian culture if Iran "strikes any Americans or American assets." [(Politico)](https://www.politico.com/news/2020/01/04/trump-iran-targets-soleimani-detah-093758) [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/rockets-target-baghdad-green-zone-base-housing-troops-200104175916421.html)\n*   [Insurgency in the Maghreb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Insurgency_in_the_Maghreb_(2002%E2%80%93present))\n    *   A [roadside bomb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roadside_bomb) strikes a bus in [Toeni Department](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toeni_Department) of [Burkina Faso](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burkina_Faso), killing fourteen people, including students on their way to school. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-50993439)\n*   [Second Libyan Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Civil_War_(2014%E2%80%93present))\n    *   An airstrike at a [military academy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military_academy) in [Tripoli](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tripoli), [Libya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya), kills at least 28 cadets and wounds dozens more, according to the [Government of National Accord](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_National_Accord). The BBC cites reports saying the attack could be attributed to the [Libyan National Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_National_Army). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-50996450)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   Tens of thousands of mourners, among them [Iraqi prime minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Iraq) [Adil Abdul-Mahdi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adil_Abdul-Mahdi), attend a funeral procession in [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad), [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq), for those [killed in a United States airstrike](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Baghdad_International_Airport_airstrike)among them [Qasem Soleimani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qasem_Soleimani), the head of [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran)''s [Quds Force](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quds_Force) and at least five others. The bodies are then brought to [Karbala](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karbala) and [Najaf](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Najaf), where [Abu Mahdi al-Muhandis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abu_Mahdi_al-Muhandis) and the other Iraqis killed are to be buried. [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2020/01/04/middleeast/qasem-soleimani-airstrike-saturday/index.html) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-security-airstrike/us-led-coalition-did-not-conduct-air-strike-near-taji-iraq-camp-spokesman-idUSKBN1Z3065)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   The [Nicols Maduro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicol%C3%A1s_Maduro) government announces that Venezuela will sell some of its oil and gold to fund its [petro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petro_(cryptocurrency)) [cryptocurrency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptocurrency). [(Yahoo Finance)](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/venezuela-sell-oil-gold-petro-104336950.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [201920 Australian bushfire season](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Australian_bushfire_season)\n    *   Two people are confirmed dead from [bushfires](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bushfire) on [Kangaroo Island](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kangaroo_Island) in [South Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Australia). [(News.com.au)](https://www.news.com.au/technology/environment/climate-change/all-hell-is-breaking-loose-massive-fire-threatens-all-of-kangaroo-island/news-story/6fbad55c97d304431786471fa20c88dd)\n    *   New records for the highest recorded temperature are set in Greater [Sydney](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sydney) (48.9C (120.0F) at [Penrith](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penrith,_New_South_Wales)) and [Canberra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canberra) (44C (111F)). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2020/jan/04/australian-weather-canberra-and-penrith-smash-temperature-records-that-stood-for-80-years)\n*   Four people are killed when a [Mooney M20](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mooney_M20) plane crashes shortly after [takeoff](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Takeoff) near the island of [Lifou](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lifou), [New Caledonia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Caledonia). [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/406711/four-die-in-new-caledonia-plane-crash)\n*   A plane crashes near [Santa Clarita, California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Clarita,_California), killing the pilot. [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/04/us/california-plane-crash-trnd/)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_4','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3229,replace('# 2020-01-06\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Libyan Civil War (2014present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_Civil_War_(2014%E2%80%93present))\n    *   The [Libyan National Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libyan_National_Army) says it has captured [Sirte](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sirte) and the [Al-Qardabiya airbase](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghardabiya_Airbase). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/06/libyan-general-khalifa-haftars-forces-seize-key-city-of-sirte)\n*   [2020 Gamboru bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Gamboru_bombing)\n    *   At least 30 people are killed in [Gamboru](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gamboru), [Borno State](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borno_State), in northeastern [Nigeria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigeria) after an [improvised explosive device](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Improvised_explosive_device) [detonates](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Detonate) at a market on a bridge. No group immediately took responsibility. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nigeria-security/thirty-killed-in-northeast-nigeria-bomb-blast-on-crowded-bridge-idUSKBN1Z526J)\n*   [Mali War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mali_War)\n    *   Five [soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malian_Armed_Forces) are killed after their vehicle hit a [roadside bomb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Improvised_explosive_device) while traveling in the [Alatona](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alatona) region. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/malian-soldiers-killed-roadside-attack-200106143333076.html)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [Funerals of Qasem Soleimani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funerals_of_Qasem_Soleimani)\n    *   A funeral service for [Qasem Soleimani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qasem_Soleimani), the [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) [Quds Force](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quds_Force) commander who was slain in a [targeted killing in Baghdad last week](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Baghdad_International_Airport_airstrike), is attended by hundreds of thousands of people in [Tehran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tehran), [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran). [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2020/01/06/794044616/iran-mourns-slain-gen-qassem-soleimani-and-vows-revenge) [(Axios)](https://www.axios.com/qasem-soleimani-iran-funeral-photos-f83662b9-dce3-4a7c-9e92-e0a24843e8ba.html)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   American retailer [Pier 1 Imports](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pier_1_Imports) announces it will close 450 stores and some [distribution centers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distribution_center), and may soon file for [bankruptcy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bankruptcy_in_the_United_States). [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/06/business/pier-1-imports-bankruptcy/index.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A 5.8 magnitude [earthquake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earthquake) strikes [Puerto Rico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puerto_Rico), causing small [landslides](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landslide), [power outages](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_outage), and severely cracking some homes. [(Associated Press)](https://nbc25news.com/news/nation-world/57-magnitude-quake-strikes-puerto-rico-damage-reported)\n*   A [German](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germans) [tourist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tourism_in_Italy) critically wounded in the crash yesterday in [Luttach](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luttach), [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy), dies from her injuries, bringing the death toll to seven. [(Il Gazzettino)](https://www.ilgazzettino.it/italia/primopiano/incidente_alto_adige_6_morti_ragazzi_chi_sono-4965506.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   A court in the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom) sentences 36-year-old [Indonesian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indonesians_in_the_United_Kingdom) national [Reynhard Sinaga](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reynhard_Sinaga) to [life imprisonment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_imprisonment) for [sexually assaulting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexually_assault) at least 48 young men in [Manchester](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchester). Sinaga was convicted of a total of 159 [sex offences](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sex_offence), and is said to be Britain''s most prolific [serial rapist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serial_rapist). [(BBC News)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-50987823) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-rapist/indonesian-student-jailed-as-britains-worst-rapist-idUSKBN1Z519D)\n*   [Police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_Germany) shoot dead a [Turkish](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turks_in_Germany) man who tried to attack officers with a knife in the city of [Gelsenkirchen](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gelsenkirchen), [North Rhine-Westphalia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Rhine-Westphalia), [Germany](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany). Police say a search of the man''s flat later did not suggest a [terrorist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_Germany) motive and that he was [mentally ill](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mentally_ill). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51003868)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Politics of the Marshall Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politics_of_the_Marshall_Islands)\n    *   [David Kabua](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Kabua) is elected [President of the Marshall Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_Marshall_Islands) by the [national legislature](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legislature_of_the_Marshall_Islands). He succeeds [Hilda Heine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hilda_Heine), who was seeking a second term, but lost in the first session vote. [(Radio New Zealand International)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/406763/new-president-for-marshall-islands)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_6','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3234,replace('# 2020-01-07\n\n## Armed conflict and attacks\n\n*   [Terrorism in Kenya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_Kenya)\n    *   Four children are killed in an [Al-Shabaab](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Shabaab_(militant_group)) attack at a [primary school](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primary_school) in [Garissa County](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garissa_County), [Kenya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenya). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/kenya-school-attacked-al-shabab-children-killed-200108065347512.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [Funerals of Qasem Soleimani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funerals_of_Qasem_Soleimani)\n    *   A [stampede](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stampede) occurs during the funeral of [Qasem Soleimani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qasem_Soleimani) in his hometown of [Kerman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kerman). [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) state-affiliated media say at least 56 people are killed and 213 more are injured. [(CBC)](https://www.cbc.ca/news/world/iran-qassem-soleimani-us-kerman-1.5417178)\n*   A magnitude 6.4 [earthquake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Puerto_Rico_earthquake) strikes [Puerto Rico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Puerto_Rico), 1 person is killed and 9 people are injured. [(NBC)](https://nbcnews.com/news/latino/6-5-quake-strikes-puerto-rico-amid-heavy-seismic-activity-n1111666)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [201920 Persian Gulf crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Persian_Gulf_crisis), [IranUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93United_States_relations)\n    *   [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran)''s [Islamic Consultative Assembly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_Consultative_Assembly) formally designates the [United States Department of Defense](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense) as a "terrorist organization" in response to the assassination of General [Qasem Soleimani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qasem_Soleimani) in a [targeted killing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Baghdad_International_Airport_airstrike) in [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad), [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq). Under the newly adopted bill, all [United States Armed Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Armed_Forces) personnel and [Pentagon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Pentagon) employees are "considered terrorists." [(Xinhuanet)](http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/07/c_138685013.htm) [(Channel News Asia)](https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/iran-designates-us-forces-terrorists-for-killing-general-12240474)\n    *   [Germany](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany) announces a partial withdrawal of the [Bundeswehr](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bundeswehr) troops positioned in [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq), citing security concerns. [(DW)](https://www.dw.com/en/germany-to-partially-withdraw-troops-from-iraq/a-51909308)\n    *   Canada''s Chief of the Defence Staff General [Jonathan Vance](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jonathan_Vance) announces that some of its military personnel in Iraq will be moved to neighboring [Kuwait](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuwait) over safety reasons. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-security-canada/canada-says-some-troops-in-iraq-to-be-moved-temporarily-to-kuwait-for-safety-idUSKBN1Z622W)\n    *   [Kosovo Police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kosovo_Police) arrest Ikballe Berisha Huduti, the founder of a now defunct Islamic organization called Kur''ani, in [Pristina](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pristina) following an order from the prosecution after she was accused of inciting [terrorist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorist) acts for social media comments against the United States over the death of Qasem Soleimani. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-kosovo-iran-crime/kosovo-arrests-iran-supporter-over-comments-after-soleimanis-death-idUSKBN1Z62AH) [(The New York Times)](https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/01/07/world/middleeast/07reuters-kosovo-iran-crime.html)\n*   [North KoreaSouth Korea relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Korea%E2%80%93South_Korea_relations)\n    *   [South Korean President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korean_President) [Moon Jae-in](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moon_Jae-in) says there is a "desperate need" for practical ways to improve ties with North Korea and says he is ready to meet repeatedly with [Kim Jong-un](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Jong-un) in [Pyongyang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyongyang) if necessary. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-southkorea-politics-moon/south-koreas-moon-cites-desperate-need-for-ways-to-improve-ties-with-north-idUSKBN1Z603B)\n*   [Foreign relations of Argentina](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foreign_relations_of_Argentina), [2019 Venezuelan presidential crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Venezuelan_presidential_crisis)\n    *   The government of Argentina says it will not recognize [Juan Guaid](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juan_Guaid%C3%B3) as [President of Venezuela](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Venezuela), and instead as the leader of the opposition in the country, and revokes the credentials of Guaid''s representative in Argentina. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-argentina-venezuela-trotta-idUSKBN1Z62IM)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   Japan issues an arrest warrant for former [Nissan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nissan) Chairman [Carlos Ghosn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Ghosn)''s wife Carole for allegedly lying during testimony. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nissan-ghosn-statement/japan-issues-arrest-warrant-for-ghosns-wife-looks-for-ways-to-bring-him-back-idUSKBN1Z6057)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [November 2019 Spanish general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/November_2019_Spanish_general_election)\n    *   After a year of political deadlock, incumbent [Prime Minister of Spain](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Spain) [Pedro Snchez](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pedro_S%C3%A1nchez_(politician)) is sworn in thanks to the support of left-wing parties and regional nationalists. He will form the first [coalition government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coalition_government) in the democratic era, with [Podemos](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Podemos_(Spanish_political_party)) and its leader [Pablo Iglesias Turrin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pablo_Iglesias_Turri%C3%B3n) as Second [Deputy Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deputy_Prime_Minister_of_Spain). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51019358)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_7','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3240,replace('# 2020-01-09\n\n## Armed conflict and attacks\n\n*   [Insurgency in the Maghreb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Insurgency_in_the_Maghreb_(2002%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [2020 Tillabri attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Tillab%C3%A9ri_attack)\n        *   [Islamist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamist) militants kill over 25 [Nigerien soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger_Armed_Forces) in an attack on an [army base](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Army_base) in [Tillabri Region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tillab%C3%A9ri_Region), [Niger](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger). 63 militants are also killed in the ensuing [shootout](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shootout). [(The Punch)](https://punchng.com/63-terrorists-25-others-killed-in-niger-army-base-attack/) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nigeria-security/suspected-islamists-kill-25-soldiers-in-niger-government-idUSKBN1Z82JN)\n*   [Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine_International_Airlines_Flight_752), [201920 Persian Gulf crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Persian_Gulf_crisis)\n    *   [U.S.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States), [Canadian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada), [British](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom) and [Iraqi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq) officials say they believe the [plane crash](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plane_crash) near [Tehran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tehran) in which 176 were killed yesterday was likely caused accidentally by an [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) [anti-aircraft missile](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anti-aircraft_weaponry), while Iran says it was due to "[mechanical failure](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechanical_failure)". [(Newsweek)](https://www.newsweek.com/iranians-shot-down-ukraine-flight-mistake-sources-1481313), [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2020/01/09/794863678/we-will-surely-find-out-the-truth-questions-linger-about-jet-crash-in-iran) [(Reuters)](https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-iran-crash-britain/johnson-says-there-is-evidence-ukrainian-plane-was-shot-down-by-iran-missile-idUKKBN1Z82LD?il=0)\n    *   _[The New York Times](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_New_York_Times)_ releases a verified video obtained from an Iranian citizen showing the plane being struck by what appears to be a [surface-to-air missile](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surface-to-air_missile). [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/09/video/iran-plane-missile.html)\n    *   In a news conference, [Canadian Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Canada) [Justin Trudeau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Justin_Trudeau) says it''s "too early to draw definitive conclusions" that the downing of the plane was an "[act of war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Act_of_war)". Trudeau also condemns Iran''s attack on U.S. bases in Iraq. [(National Post)](https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/champagne-asks-iran-to-let-canadian-officials-in-to-investigate-plane-crash)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   A bus crashes in Iran''s [Mazandaran Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mazandaran_Province), killing at least 20 passengers and injuring 24 others. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/reported-dead-bus-crash-iran-iranian-media-200109053940090.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   Judge Ghassan Ouiedat, a [Lebanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanon) [prosecutor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prosecutor), imposes a [travel ban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Travel_ban) on former Chairman of [Nissan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nissan) [Carlos Ghosn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Ghosn) after he was summoned over an [Interpol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpol) warrant issued by Japan seeking his arrest on [financial misconduct](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_misconduct) charges. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nissan-ghosn-lebanon-questioning/lebanon-imposes-travel-ban-on-ex-nissan-boss-ghosn-judicial-source-idUSKBN1Z80ZC)\n*   [Trial of Catalonia independence leaders](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trial_of_Catalonia_independence_leaders)\n    *   The [Spanish Supreme Court](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spanish_Supreme_Court) revokes the immunity of jailed [Oriol Junqueras](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oriol_Junqueras) declared by the [European Court of Justice](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Court_of_Justice) in a sentence on 19 December. This happens after the board of [European Parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Parliament) recognized the former [Vice President of Catalonia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_vice_presidents_of_Catalonia) as a [MEP](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Member_of_the_European_Parliament) since 3 July and was elected president of the [GreensEuropean Free Alliance](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greens%E2%80%93European_Free_Alliance) parliamentary group. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2020/01/09/world/europe/ap-eu-spain-catalonia.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Brexit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brexit)\n    *   The [United Kingdom House of Commons](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_of_Commons_of_the_United_Kingdom) votes 330231 to pass the [Withdrawal Agreement Bill](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brexit_withdrawal_agreement) authorizing the countrys departure from the [European Union](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union) at the end of the month. [(Associated Press)](https://nbc25news.com/news/nation-world/lawmakers-approve-brexit-bill-uk-on-course-for-jan-31-exit)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_9','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3245,replace('# 2020-01-10\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine_International_Airlines_Flight_752)\n    *   After [Canadian Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Canada) [Justin Trudeau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Justin_Trudeau) suggests the plane was downed by an Iranian missile, Iranian authorities reject this theory. Iranian civil aviation chief says he is "certain" the plane was not hit by a missile, still asserting the cause was "mechanical failure". [(BBC News)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51062369)\n*   [2020 Quetta bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Quetta_bombing)\n    *   A [bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bomb) claimed by the [Islamic State](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant_%E2%80%93_Khorasan_Province) at a [mosque](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mosque) in [Quetta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quetta), [Balochistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balochistan,_Pakistan), [Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan), kills at least 15 people and wounds 18 others, three days after a motorcycle bombing in the city killed two. [(The New York Times)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/10/world/asia/pakistan-mosque-bombing-isis-taliban.html)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   Death of [Qaboos bin Said al Said](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qaboos_bin_Said_al_Said)\n    *   [Omani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oman) [state television](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_media) announces the death of the [Sultan of Oman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_rulers_of_Oman) [Qaboos bin Said al Said](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qaboos_bin_Said_al_Said) aged 79. At the time of his death he was the longest serving head of state in the [Middle East](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_East) and [Arab world](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arab_world). [(Reuters)](http://news.trust.org//item/20200110233755-nw853/)\n    *   The high military council of [Sultan of Oman''s Armed Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sultan_of_Oman%27s_Armed_Forces) calls on the [Omani royal family](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House_of_Al_Said) to convene to name a successor to the late sultan within three days. A three-day period of [national mourning](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_mourning) is declared. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/11/sultan-of-oman-dies-state-media-announces)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [IraqUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq%E2%80%93United_States_relations), [IranIraq relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Iraq_relations), [201920 Persian Gulf crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Persian_Gulf_crisis)\n    *   Iraqi cleric and Grand Ayatollah [Ali al-Sistani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ali_al-Sistani) condemns both the United States and Iran over the escalation of conflict in [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq), saying it shows blatant disregard for Iraqi [sovereignty](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sovereignty) and the suffering of the [Iraqi people](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi_people). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-security/iraqi-cleric-condemns-u-s-and-iran-as-fears-of-wider-conflict-persist-idUSKBN1Z80P5?il=0)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   An 11-year-old student [opens fire at his school](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/School_shooting) in [Torren](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torre%C3%B3n), [Coahuila](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coahuila), [Mexico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico), killing a teacher and wounding six others [before committing suicide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murder%E2%80%93suicide). [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/10/mexico-school-shooting-torreon)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [201920 Australian bushfire season](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Australian_bushfire_season)\n    *   Thousands of people protest in [Melbourne](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melbourne), [Brisbane](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brisbane) and [Sydney](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sydney), calling for the [resignation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resignation) or ouster of [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Australia) [Scott Morrison](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scott_Morrison), accusing him of negligence over the Australian bushfires. [(News.com.au)](https://www.news.com.au/technology/environment/climate-change/major-rallies-held-in-australian-cities-calling-for-prime-minister-scott-morrison-to-be-sacked/news-story/54b61b35563536a0b8a8fade8580b57f)\n*   [2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Democratic_Party_presidential_primaries)\n    *   Author and [self-help guru](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-help) [Marianne Williamson](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marianne_Williamson) drops out of the U.S. presidential race. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/10/us/politics/marianne-williamson-drops-out.html)\n*   The [Tunisian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tunisia) [Parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Assembly_of_the_Representatives_of_the_People) votes 134 to 72 to reject a cabinet proposed by [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_the_Republic_of_Tunisia)\-designate Habib Jemli. [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Tunisia) [Kais Saied](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kais_Saied) has 10 days to select someone else to build a new government. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-tunisia-politics/tunisian-parliament-rejects-government-coalition-building-must-restart-idUSKBN1Z92EW?il=0)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_10','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3250,replace('# 2020-01-12\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   Four [Iraqi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq) soldiers are wounded when mortar shells strike [Balad Air Base](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balad_Air_Base), 40 miles (64km) north of [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad), which houses [U.S.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) military personnel. The mortars struck the runway inside the base. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-security-base/mortar-bombs-strike-iraqi-military-base-of-balad-four-wounded-military-sources-idUSKBN1ZB0I0?il=0)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   The [Taal Volcano](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taal_Volcano) in southern [Luzon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luzon), [Philippines](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippines), spews an [ash plume](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volcanic_ash) that measures approximately 10 to 15 kilometres (6.2 to 9.3mi). The [Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippine_Institute_of_Volcanology_and_Seismology) designates a "level 4" alert level, indicating "an imminent hazardous eruption". [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/13/philippines-lava-gushes-from-taal-volcano-as-alert-level-raised)\n*   The government of the Canadian province of [Ontario](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ontario) apologizes for issuing a false alert about an incident at a [nuclear plant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_plant) near [Toronto](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toronto) and blames a training exercise mistake. Angry local mayors demand an inquiry, saying the emergency message about the ageing [Pickering Nuclear Generating Station](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pickering_Nuclear_Generating_Station) has caused unnecessary distress. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-canada-nuclear/canada-province-says-sorry-after-training-mistake-sparks-false-nuclear-alert-idUSKBN1ZB0C8?il=0)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [JapanSaudi Arabia relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93Saudi_Arabia_relations)\n    *   Japanese PM [Shinz Abe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shinz%C5%8D_Abe) arrives in Saudi Arabia in his first visit to the Middle East, where he expects to mediate between the United States and Iran amid heightening tensions. [(_The Japan Times_)](https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2020/01/12/national/politics-diplomacy/abe-meets-saudi-king-salman-calls-cooperation-stabilize-middle-east-talks-foreign-minister/)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine_International_Airlines_Flight_752), [201920 Iranian protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Iranian_protests)\n    *   Protests continue for a second day despite a large deployment of security forces. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/amp/world-middle-east-51081833)\n    *   United States President [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) tweeted in [Farsi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Farsi), warned Iranian leaders and showed his support to the protesters. [(CNN)](https://www.amp.cnn.com/cnn/2020/01/11/politics/trump-support-iran-protesters/index.html)\n*   [The Gambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Gambia) warns ousted leader [Yahya Jammeh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yahya_Jammeh) not to return to the country, saying his safety cannot be guaranteed if he returns without permission, a government spokesman says. A spokesman for Jammeh''s party says he could arrive back at any time from exile in [Equatorial Guinea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equatorial_Guinea). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-51082371)\n*   [2019 Malta political crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Malta_political_crisis)\n    *   [Robert Abela](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Abela) wins the [Partit Laburista](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partit_Laburista) leadership election, succeeding [Joseph Muscat](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Muscat) as [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Malta) after Muscat''s resignation. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51080574) [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2020/01/12/europe/malta-robert-abela-prime-minister-intl/index.html)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   [Chinese espionage in the United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_espionage_in_the_United_States)\n    *   The [U.S. Department of the Interior](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_the_Interior) halts its civilian [drone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unmanned_aerial_vehicle) program indefinitely out of concerns that [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China), who manufactured the fleet via the [SZ DJI Technology Company](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DJI_(company)), is using it for espionage. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-drones/trump-to-halt-civilian-drone-program-over-china-tech-concerns-ft-idUSKBN1ZB0MU)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_12','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3255,replace('# 2020-01-15\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   Aftermath of the [Sudanese Revolution](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudanese_Revolution)\n    *   The [Sudanese Armed Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudanese_Armed_Forces) says it has quelled a [mutiny](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mutiny) by soldiers loyal to ousted [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Sudan) [Omar al-Bashir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omar_al-Bashir) in the capital [Khartoum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khartoum). Former Director of the [National Intelligence and Security Service](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Intelligence_and_Security_Service) [Salah Gosh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salah_Gosh) is accused of orchestrating the mutiny, which left two troops dead. His current whereabouts are unknown. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-51112518)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   The [Vatican](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holy_See) appoints [Francesca Di Giovanni](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francesca_Di_Giovanni) undersecretary for multilateral affairs in the [Secretariat of State](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secretariat_of_State_(Holy_See)), the first woman to hold a management position in this office. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51124478)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [EgyptTurkey relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egypt%E2%80%93Turkey_relations)\n    *   [Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey) summons its _[charg d''affaires](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charg%C3%A9_d%27affaires)_ to [Egypt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egypt) after accusing the [Egyptian security forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_Security_Investigations_Service) of raiding the [Cairo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cairo) offices of the state-run [Anadolu News Agency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anadolu_Agency) and arresting four of its employees. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-egypt-security/turkey-says-egyptian-security-forces-raid-news-agency-in-cairo-idUSKBN1ZE1U5?il=0)\n*   [JapanNorth Korea relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan%E2%80%93North_Korea_relations)\n    *   North Korean state media condemn [Japanese Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Japan) [Shinz Abe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shinz%C5%8D_Abe) for his attempts to reform the [pacifist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Article_9_of_the_Japanese_Constitution) [Japanese constitution](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitution_of_Japan). The state media say that "in the event of a constitutional revision, which gives \[Japan''s\] [self-defense forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan_Self-Defense_Forces) legitimacy, the Japanese reactionaries will have all the preconditions necessary to realize military aggression overseas". [(UPI)](https://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2020/01/15/North-Korea-rails-against-Japan-plans-for-constitutional-amendment/6591579104508/)\n*   [ChinaUnited States trade war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China%E2%80%93United_States_trade_war)\n    *   In a meeting at the [White House](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_House), [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) and [Chinese Vice Premier](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vice_Premier_of_China) [Han Zheng](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Han_Zheng) sign "Phase 1" of a new trade deal in which the U.S. will relax some of the tariffs imposed on Chinese imports while China agreed to buy more American products. Both sides also agree to not impose new tariffs. [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2020/01/15/796305300/trump-to-sign-phase-one-china-trade-deal-but-most-tariffs-remain-in-place)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   The [Russian government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Russia) of [Dmitry Medvedev''s Second Cabinet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dmitry_Medvedev%27s_Second_Cabinet) [resigns](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resignation_of_Russian_government) after [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Russia) [Vladimir Putin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vladimir_Putin) delivers the [Presidential Address to the Federal Assembly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Presidential_Address_to_the_Federal_Assembly), in which he proposed several amendments to the constitution. Putin accepts the resignation. [Medvedev](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dmitry_Medvedev) says the constitutional changes would "significantly change Russia''s balance of power". [(_The Independent_)](https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/dmitry-medvedev-resign-russia-prime-minister-putin-quit-latest-a9284741.html) [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51120166)\n*   [Greek](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greece) [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Greece) [Kyriakos Mitsotakis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyriakos_Mitsotakis) nominates [Council of State](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Council_of_State_(Greece)) president [Aikaterini Sakellaropoulou](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aikaterini_Sakellaropoulou) to be [President of Greece](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Greece). If approved, she will be the first female president in Greek history. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-greece-politics-president/greek-pm-taps-top-female-judge-as-countrys-president-idUSKBN1ZE2FE?il=0)\n*   The [Virginia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia) [House of Delegates](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia_House_of_Delegates) votes to ratify the [Equal Rights Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equal_Rights_Amendment) decades after its deadline passed. As the amendment nonetheless now has enough [states](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._state) for it to be fully adopted, legal scholars are divided on whether this means the [Constitution of the United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitution_of_the_United_States) has been amended. [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2020/01/15/796754345/virginia-ratifies-the-equal-rights-amendment-decades-after-deadline)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_15','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3260,replace('# 2020-01-16\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   The [American-led coalition](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combined_Joint_Task_Force_%E2%80%93_Operation_Inherent_Resolve) issues a statement saying that 11 U.S. service members were injured by the [January 8, 2020 attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Iranian_attack_on_U.S._forces_in_Iraq) by [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) on [U.S. forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._forces) in [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq). The [U.S. Department of Defense](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense) had initially assessed that there had been no injuries. [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/16/politics/service-members-injured-iran-strike/index.html)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [LGBT rights in South Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_rights_in_South_Korea)\n    *   In a landmark case, the [South Korean military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korean_military) is set to decide on the first [transgender](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transgender) soldier''s possible discharge. The soldier underwent [surgery](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sex_reassignment_surgery) overseas and is stationed in [Gyeonggi Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gyeonggi_Province). The case sparks a national debate on [LGBT](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT) issues in the military, which punishes [sex between two males](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gay_sexual_practices) with up to two years imprisonment. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-southkorea-military-transgender/south-korea-to-decide-on-first-transgender-soldier-amid-debate-idUSKBN1ZF1S0?il=0)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   The [U.S. Senate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Senate) votes 8910 to pass the [United StatesMexicoCanada Agreement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States%E2%80%93Mexico%E2%80%93Canada_Agreement). Once ratified by [Canada](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada), it will supersede the [North America Free Trade Agreement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_America_Free_Trade_Agreement). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trade-usmca/senate-passes-north-america-trade-deal-canada-still-to-approve-idUSKBN1ZF283?il=0)\n*   [Alphabet Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alphabet_Inc.), parent company of [Google](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google), becomes the fourth American company to hit a stock [market capitalization](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Market_capitalization) of [US$](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._dollar)1 trillion. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-funds-google/which-company-just-hit-1-trillion-google-it-idUSKBN1ZF2SH)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Guatemalan President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Guatemala) [Alejandro Giammattei](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alejandro_Giammattei) cuts ties with [the government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Presidency_of_Nicol%C3%A1s_Maduro) of disputed [Venezuelan President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Venezuela) [Nicols Maduro](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicol%C3%A1s_Maduro) and closes [Guatemala](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guatemala)''s embassy in [Caracas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caracas). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-guatemala-politics-venezuela/guatemalas-new-president-cuts-ties-with-venezuela-as-promised-idUSKBN1ZF2SB?il=0)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   After his escape from [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan), [Carlos Ghosn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Ghosn)''s Japanese lawyer Junichiro Hironaka and seven other members of his defense resign. Hironaka says Ghosn''s escape was a "complete surprise". [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2020/01/16/business/carlos-ghosn-lawyer/index.html)\n*   The bodies of seven people are found in a [mass grave](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_grave) in the indigenous [Ngbe-Bugl](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ng%C3%A4be-Bugl%C3%A9_Comarca) region of [Panama](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panama). Authorities believe a religious sect performed an [exorcism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exorcism) on the victims. Police rescued 15 people who had suffered bodily injuries. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51144629)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Mikhail Mishustin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mikhail_Mishustin) is appointed as new [Prime Minister of Russia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Russia). [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/16/world/europe/mikhail-mishustin.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_16','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3265,replace('# 2020-01-17\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Iraqi protests (2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi_protests_(2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   At least two people are killed and dozens injured after [Iraqi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq) security forces fire upon protesters at Sinak bridge in central [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/iraq-security-forces-kill-protesters-baghdad-200117192553279.html)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   Foreign Minister of the [Maldives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maldives) [Abdulla Shahid](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdulla_Shahid) says that his country could lose entire islands unless it can access cheap financing to fight [climate change](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-climate-change-maldives/we-cant-wait-maldives-desperate-for-funds-as-islands-risk-going-under-idUSKBN1ZG0XS)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Icelandic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iceland) [fishing company](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fishery) [Samherji](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samherji) announces it will cease operations in [Namibia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Namibia). The company was embroiled in [a bribery scandal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fishrot_Files) there that resulted in the resignation of Namibian Fisheries Minister [Bernhardt Esau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bernhardt_Esau) and Justice Minister [Sacky Shanghala](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sacky_Shanghala), as well as the arrest of two employees of [South African](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa) banking corporation [Investec](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Investec). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-namibia-samherji/icelands-samherji-exiting-namibia-following-bribery-scandal-idUSKBN1ZH0DF?il=0)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Crime in China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crime_in_China)\n    *   A man is [sentenced to death](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_punishment_in_China) for [murdering](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murder) a doctor in [Beijing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beijing) on [New Year''s Eve](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Year%27s_Eve). The murder was the latest in a string of attacks on medical staff in [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) by angry relatives blaming them for the lack of medical resources and services. [(Asia One)](https://www.asiaone.com/china/chinese-doctors-murder-overshadows-new-law-improve-public-health-care)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Brazilian federal government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazilian_federal_government) secretary of culture, [Roberto Alvim](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roberto_Alvim), is dismissed after the broadcast of a video where he announces a new national prize on culture. In the video, Alvim seems to paraphrase a speech by [Joseph Goebbels](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Goebbels), [Nazi Germany](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nazi_Germany)''s [_Reichsminister_ of Propaganda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reich_Ministry_of_Public_Enlightenment_and_Propaganda). [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/17/brazil-culture-minister-goebbels-roberto-alvim-nazi)\n*   [Ukrainian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine) [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Ukraine) [Oleksiy Honcharuk](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oleksiy_Honcharuk) submits his [resignation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resignation) after an audio clip of him allegedly criticizing [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Ukraine) [Volodymyr Zelensky](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volodymyr_Zelensky)s economic policies was leaked earlier this week. Zelensky subsequently announces that Honcharuk is allowed to keep his position. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ukraine-pm-resignation/ukraine-pm-offers-to-resign-after-tape-suggests-he-criticized-president-idUSKBN1ZG0RF)\n*   [Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752 protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine_International_Airlines_Flight_752_protests)\n    *   At a [Friday sermon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jumu%27ah) by [Iranian Supreme Leader](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supreme_Leader_of_Iran) [Ali Khamenei](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ali_Khamenei), his first in eight years, he defends the [Revolutionary Guards](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_Revolutionary_Guard_Corps) accidental killing of passengers onboard [Ukraine International Airlines Flight 752](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine_International_Airlines_Flight_752) and praises [Operation Martyr Soleimani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Iranian_attack_on_U.S._forces_in_Iraq) for giving a slap on the face to the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States). His sermon comes as public anger mounts against the government for their handling of Flight 752. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/ayatollah-khamenei-defends-revolutionary-guard-friday-sermon-200117105420440.html)\n*   Protesters squat an oil terminal in the eastern [Libyan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Libya) town of [Zuwetina](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zuwetina) at the request of tribal leaders, who claim that the [Government of National Accord](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_National_Accord) is using oil revenue to pay for foreign fighters, a reference to [Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey)''s sending of troops and arms in support of the GNA. The protesters are swiftly condemned by the state-owned [National Oil Corporation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Oil_Corporation). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-oil/eastern-libyan-protesters-enter-zueitina-oil-port-announce-its-closure-idUSKBN1ZG2B5?il=0)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_17','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3269,replace('# 2020-01-18\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Afghan presidential](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Afghanistan) spokesman Sediq Sediqqi says that the government rejects the proposed "reduction in violence" by the [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) as an "ambiguous term with no legal or military parameters". On Friday, the Taliban proposed a ten-day truce and to hold follow-up discussions with [Afghan government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_government) officials. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/afghan-government-demands-long-term-ceasefire-taliban-200117083410030.html)\n*   [Yemen Civil War (2015present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemen_Civil_War_(2015%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [2020 Ma''rib attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Ma%27rib_attack)\n        *   Eighty [military personnel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_Yemen_Armed_Forces) are killed by [ballistic missiles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ballistic_missile) and [drone strikes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drone_strike) in an attack reportedly carried out by the [Houthis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houthi) against a military camp in the [Yemeni](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemen) city of [Ma''rib](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ma%27rib), according to Saudi state TV. The Houthis have not claimed responsibility for the attack. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51166943)\n*   [Somali Civil War (2009present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somali_Civil_War_(2009%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [2020 Afgooye bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Afgooye_bombing)\n        *   An [al-Shabaab](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Shabaab_(militant_group)) [car bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Car_bomb) kills four people and injures at least 20 others near [Afgooye](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afgooye), [Lower Shabelle](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lower_Shabelle), [Somalia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somalia).\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [Megxit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Megxit)\n    *   Officials with [Buckingham Palace](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buckingham_Palace) announced that effective spring of this year, [Prince Harry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prince_Harry,_Duke_of_Sussex) and his wife [Meghan Markle](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meghan,_Duchess_of_Sussex) will retain, but will no longer publicly use, the [style](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Style_(form_of_address)) [His/Her Royal Highness](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Highness), and will no longer receive public funds for royal duties.[(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51163865)\n    *   The couple will also repay [](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pound_sterling)2.4 million of public money spent on renovating the [Frogmore Cottage](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frogmore_Cottage).[(RT News)](https://www.rte.ie/news/world/2020/0118/1108328-harry-meghan-royals/)\n    *   The couple will keep their titles as Duke and Duchess of Sussex. While Prince Harry will lose all his [military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Armed_Forces) appointments, he will remain a [prince](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_prince). [(Sky News)](https://news.sky.com/story/harry-and-meghan-to-lose-royal-funds-and-hrh-titles-from-spring-11912020)\n    *   Some news reports are calling this the "abdication'' of Prince Harry. [(ITV News)](https://www.itv.com/news/2020-01-19/prince-harry-meghan-markle-royal-abdication-prince-henry-royal-family/)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Seoul](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seoul)\-based _[NK News](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NK_News)_ reports that [North Korean](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Korea) [Foreign Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(North_Korea)) [Ri Yong-ho](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ri_Yong-ho_(diplomat)) has been replaced. His successor is expected to be publicly announced next Thursday. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-northkorea-foreign-minister/north-korean-foreign-minister-replaced-report-idUSKBN1ZH0B3?il=0)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [List of mass shootings in the United States in 2020](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_mass_shootings_in_the_United_States_in_2020)\n    *   A boy shoots and kills three children and a woman before being arrested in [Grantsville, Utah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grantsville,_Utah), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States). A fifth victim is shot but is in a stable condition in hospital. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/jan/18/boy-kills-four-utah-mass-shooting)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_18','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3273,replace('# 2020-01-19\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   The [Philippines](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippines) [military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armed_Forces_of_the_Philippines) announce that they have launched [search and rescue](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Search_and_rescue) operations for five [Indonesian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indonesians) fishermen [kidnapped](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kidnap) by militants belonging to the [ISIL](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant)\-linked [Abu Sayyaf](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abu_Sayyaf) group in [Malaysian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaysia) waters last week in [Sabah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabah). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-philippines-security/philippine-military-says-5-indonesians-kidnapped-by-abu-sayyaf-militants-idUSKBN1ZI0BZ)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [IndiaMalaysia relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India%E2%80%93Malaysia_relations)\n    *   [Indian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India) trade minister [Piyush Goyal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Piyush_Goyal) states when he attends the [World Economic Forum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Economic_Forum) next week, he will not meet with his Malaysian counterpart [Darell Leiking](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darell_Leiking) to discuss India''s tightening of [palm oil](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palm_oil) imports from his country. India tightened imports from Malaysia last week in response to [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Malaysia) [Mahathir Mohamad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahathir_Mohamad)''s criticisms of the [revocation of Jammu and Kashmir''s special status](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Revocation_of_the_special_status_of_Jammu_and_Kashmir) and the [Citizenship Amendment Act](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Citizenship_(Amendment)_Act,_2019). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-india-malaysia/india-says-no-meeting-with-malaysia-in-davos-as-palm-row-simmers-idUSKBN1ZI0DW)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Crime in Hawaii](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crime_in_Hawaii)\n    *   A man facing eviction shoots three police officers, killing two, then sets a house on fire, which spreads to four nearby houses, in [Honolulu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honolulu), [Hawaii](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawaii), United States. He is presumed dead in the fire. [(Hawaii News Now)](https://www.hawaiinewsnow.com/2020/01/19/multiple-honolulu-police-officers-injured-shooting-near-diamond-head/)\n*   [Crime in Kansas City, Missouri](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crime_in_Kansas_City,_Missouri)\n    *   Two people (including the perpetrator) were killed and fifteen others were injured during a shooting at a nightclub in [Kansas City, Missouri](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kansas_City,_Missouri). [(WDAF)](https://fox4kc.com/2020/01/20/two-people-killed-15-others-injured-in-shooting-at-kansas-city-nightclub/)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_19','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3279,replace('# 2020-01-21\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   The [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_the_United_Kingdom) and [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_the_United_States) [governments](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government) announce they have agreed to protect the [wreckage](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wreck_of_the_RMS_Titanic) of the [RMS _Titanic_](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RMS_Titanic). The agreement, signed by the British government in 2003, has come into effect after being ratified by [U.S. Secretary of State](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Secretary_of_State) [Mike Pompeo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_Pompeo). An official also says the UK will work with [Canada](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada) and [France](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France) to bring "even more protection" to the wreckage. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-51188909)\n*   [Rock musician](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock_music) [Ozzy Osbourne](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ozzy_Osbourne) announces that he has been diagnosed with [Parkinson''s disease](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parkinson%27s_disease). [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Culture/ozzy-osbourne-opens-parkinsons-diagnosis-family-helped-back/story)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Gold Fields Ltd](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gold_Fields_Ltd), a [South African](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa) mining company, has hired an [investment bank](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Investment_bank), [RBC Capital Markets](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RBC_Capital_Markets), to help it sell 30% of its gold project in northern [Chile](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chile). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-goldfields-m-a-chile/gold-fields-hires-advisor-to-sell-stake-in-chilean-gold-project-sources-idUSKBN1ZK1YG)\n*   [Boeing 737 MAX groundings](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_737_MAX_groundings)\n    *   After having announced it the previous month, [Boeing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing) temporarily stops production of the new [737 MAX](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_737_MAX) planes. Already produced ones will remain grounded an additional month until June or July. [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2020/01/21/business/boeing-737-max-production-halt/index.html) [(NPR)](https://www.npr.org/2020/01/21/798312515/boeing-737-max-may-stay-grounded-into-summer)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 outbreak of coronavirus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_outbreak_of_novel_coronavirus_(2019-nCoV))\n    *   The [Centers for Disease Control and Prevention](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention) announces the first U.S. case of novel coronavirus in [Snohomish County, Washington](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snohomish_County,_Washington). [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2020/01/21/coronavirus-us-case/)\n    *   The [Centers for Disease Control](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Centers_for_Disease_Control_(Taiwan)) for [Taiwan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taiwan) announces that the first case of novel coronavirus was identified at [Taoyuan International Airport](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taoyuan_International_Airport). [(_The Wall Street Journal_)](https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-virus-case-highlights-chinese-efforts-to-exclude-taipei-from-world-health-organization-11579634031)\n    *   [North Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Korea) reportedly bans foreign tourists and closes the [ChinaNorth Korea border](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China%E2%80%93North_Korea_border) to prevent the spread of the new coronavirus. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/north-korea-bans-foreign-tourists-china-virus-tour-agency-200122042416138.html)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [UkraineUnited Kingdom relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine%E2%80%93United_Kingdom_relations)\n    *   [Ukraine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine) demands the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom)''s [National Counter Terrorism Policing Network](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Counter_Terrorism_Policing_Network) remove the country''s [Tryzub](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coat_of_arms_of_Ukraine) [coat of arms](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coat_of_arms) from a guide on hate symbols associated with [white supremacy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_supremacy) and [Neo-Nazism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neo-Nazism). Counter Terrorism Policing says the coat of arms was included due to its use by [National Action](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Action_(UK)), a proscribed [far-right](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Far-right_politics_in_the_United_Kingdom) [terror](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_the_United_Kingdom) group. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-trending-51174898)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   Two judicial sources announce that the trial of seven [Cameroonian soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cameroonian_Armed_Forces) has begun for the killing of two women and two children in July 2018, in a case that sparked international outcry. Six of the soldiers admit to the charges, but say they were [given the order](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Superior_orders) to open fire. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cameroon-security/cameroonian-soldiers-go-on-trial-over-shooting-of-women-and-children-idUSKBN1ZK197)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Labour Party leadership election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Labour_Party_leadership_election)\n    *   [Birmingham Yardley](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birmingham_Yardley_(UK_Parliament_constituency)) [MP](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Member_of_Parliament_(United_Kingdom)) [Jess Phillips](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jess_Phillips) drops out of the [UK Labour Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Labour_Party_(UK)) leadership race. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-51195059)\n*   [201920 Lebanese protests](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Lebanese_protests)\n    *   [Lebanon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanon) forms a new [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Lebanon) with former [American University of Beirut](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_University_of_Beirut) professor [Hassan Diab](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hassan_Diab_(politician)) as its [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Lebanon), ending a three-month deadlock. Protestors subsequently march on [Parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parliament_of_Lebanon) to protest the new government. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/lebanon-announces-formation-government-200121200947113.html)\n*   The [2020 United States Census](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_United_States_Census) begins, with [Census Bureau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau) director [Steven Dillingham](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steven_Dillingham) visiting [Toksook Bay](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toksook_Bay,_Alaska), [Alaska](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alaska) to meet with [indigenous](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alaska_Natives) leaders and distribute census materials to residents. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-51200808)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_21','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3284,replace('# 2020-01-23\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Syrian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Civil_War) and [Northwestern Syria offensive (November 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(November_2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   The [Russian Ministry of Defence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Defence_(Russia)) says that hundreds of rebels stormed [Syrian Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Army) positions in [Idlib Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib_Governorate), the ensuing fighting left 50 rebels dead and 90 wounded while government forces lost 40 dead and 80 wounded. A military source cited by Syrian state news agency [SANA](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Arab_News_Agency) says the [Jabhat al-Nusra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jabhat_al-Nusra) terrorists used various weapons such as [car bombs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Car_bomb), under an "intensive [fire cover](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suppressive_fire)". [(Reuters via Al Arabiya English)](https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/01/23/Up-to-40-Syrian-Soldiers-killed-80-wounded-in-Idlib-attack-IFAX-.html) [(SANA)](https://sana.sy/en/?p=183197) [BBC](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51221225)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   The _[Bulletin of the Atomic Scientists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulletin_of_the_Atomic_Scientists)_ advances the [Doomsday Clock](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doomsday_Clock) to 100 seconds before midnight, citing the threats to human survival posed by [nuclear proliferation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_proliferation), [climate change](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change) and "cyber-based disinformation." This is the closest to midnight that the clock has been since the project began in 1947. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-51213185)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Malaysian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaysia) agriculture giant [FGV Holdings Berhad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FGV_Holdings_Berhad) announces it will increase its sugar imports from [India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India) from 88,000 tonnes to 133,000 in an attempt to resolve the [palm oil](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palm_oil) trade dispute between the two nations. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-india-malaysia-exclusive/exclusive-malaysia-to-buy-more-indian-sugar-to-resolve-palm-oil-spat-sources-idUSKBN1ZM0E8)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [201920 Australian bushfire season](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Australian_bushfire_season)\n    *   A [C-130](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C-130) [water bomber](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Water_bomber) crashes in southern [New South Wales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_South_Wales), [Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia), while helping control a [bushfire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bushfire). Three [American](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americans) [firefighters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Firefighters) are killed. [(ABC News)](https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-01-23/nsw-rfs-air-tanker-crashes-near-numeralla-bushfire/11893554)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   The death toll from the new [coronavirus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronavirus) rises to 25 and 830 confirmed cases in [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) as four more Chinese cities, [Huanggang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huanggang), [Ezhou](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ezhou), [Chibi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chibi) and [Zhijiang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zhijiang,_Hubei) are to be placed under [quarantine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quarantine). The total number of people under quarantine is now over 20 million people. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-51230011) [(Business Insider)](https://www.businessinsider.com/china-wuhan-coronavirus-quarantine-extended-cities-cut-off-2020-1?r=US&IR=T)\n    *   [Singapore](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Singapore) confirms its first case of new coronavirus, a 66-year-old Chinese man from [Wuhan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wuhan) who was travelling with his family. [(Channel News Asia)](https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/wuhan-virus-pneumonia-singapore-confirms-first-case-12312860)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   Heads of state and dignitaries from around the world attend the fifth [World Holocaust Forum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Holocaust_Forum) at [Yad Vashem](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yad_Vashem) in Jerusalem to commemorate the 75th anniversary of the liberation of the [Auschwitz extermination camp](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Auschwitz_extermination_camp) and to address the resurgence of [antisemitism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antisemitism) worldwide. [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/world-leaders-convene-in-jerusalem-to-remember-holocaust-and-counter-anti-semitism/2020/01/23/e82fa964-3d56-11ea-afe2-090eb37b60b1_story.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   The [International Court of Justice](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Court_of_Justice) orders [Myanmar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myanmar) to protect the [Rohingya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohingya) population from atrocities. [The Gambia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Gambia) had brought a lawsuit before the court over charges of [genocide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genocide). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-rohingya-world-court/world-court-orders-myanmar-to-protect-rohingya-from-acts-of-genocide-idUSKBN1ZM00H)\n*   A judicial source close to former [Nissan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nissan) chairman [Carlos Ghosn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Ghosn) says that [Lebanon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanon) and [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) will have 40 days to decide whether he will be extradited back to Japan or stand trial in Lebanon. [(Reuters via Al Arabiya)](https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/01/23/Lebanon-Japan-have-40-days-to-agree-on-fate-of-ex-Nissan-boss-Ghosn.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Brexit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brexit)\n    *   The [European Union (Withdrawal Agreement) Act 2020](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union_(Withdrawal_Agreement)_Act_2020) is given [royal assent](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_assent) in the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom), formally making the bill law. [(Vox)](https://www.vox.com/world/2020/1/23/21070594/brexit-royal-assent-january-31-uk-eu-trade)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_23','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3289,replace('# 2020-01-24\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Iraqi protests (2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi_protests_(2019%E2%80%93present)), [American-led intervention in Iraq (2014present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American-led_intervention_in_Iraq_(2014%E2%80%93present)), [201920 Persian Gulf crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Persian_Gulf_crisis)\n    *   Hundreds of thousands march in [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad) to protest the U.S. presence in Iraq. [(CNN)](https://amp.cnn.com/cnn/2020/01/24/middleeast/iraq-protests-us-troops-intl/index.html)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Indonesia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indonesia) agrees to increase its imports of [buffalo meat](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buffalo_meat), [automobiles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automotive_industry_in_India), and [sugar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sugar) from [India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India) in exchange for an increase in imports of Indonesian-produced [palm oil](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palm_oil), amid a growing trade dispute between India and [Malaysia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaysia). [(_Times of India_)](https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/indonesia-may-ease-auto-solar-imports/articleshow/73569439.cms) [(Yahoo! Finance)](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/exclusive-indonesia-increase-imports-india-113106563.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   Two people are killed in a [warehouse explosion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Houston_explosion) in [Houston](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houston), [Texas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texas), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States). [(Associated Press)](https://www.abc12.com/content/news/Explosion-at-Houston-building-shakes-city-scatters-debris--567259021.html)\n*   [2020 Elaz earthquake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Elaz%C4%B1%C4%9F_earthquake)\n    *   At least 22 are killed and more than a thousand injured in an [earthquake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_earthquakes_in_Turkey) centered near [Elaz](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elaz%C4%B1%C4%9F) in [Eastern Anatolia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Anatolia_Region). [(_BBC_)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51245088)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [Shanghai Disney Resort](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shanghai_Disney_Resort) temporarily closes ahead of the [Lunar New Year](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_New_Year) "in response to the prevention and control of the disease outbreak." [(AFP via _GMA News Online_)](https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/world/723443/shanghai-disneyland-closes-over-china-ncov-concerns/story/)\n*   The [Cook Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cook_Islands) Ministry of Health issues an edict mandating that all [expatriate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expatriate) workers receive [MMR vaccines](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MMR_vaccine), or risk losing their permits. [(_Cook Islands News_)](http://www.cookislandsnews.com/national/health/item/75674-it-s-only-fair-overseas-workers-must-prove-they-are-vaccinated)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [IranSaudi Arabia relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Saudi_Arabia_relations)\n    *   Responding to [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) Foreign Minister [Javad Zarif](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javad_Zarif)''s comments that Iran is "open to dialogue with its neighbors", [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia)''s [Adel al-Jubeir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adel_al-Jubeir) blames Iran for recent tensions in the [Middle East](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_East) and for [attacks on](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/May_2019_Gulf_of_Oman_incident) [ships](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/June_2019_Gulf_of_Oman_incident) and [oil facilities](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Abqaiq%E2%80%93Khurais_attack); which Iran denies. [(CNBC)](https://www.cnbc.com/2020/01/24/saudi-foreign-minister-iran-has-to-change-its-behavior-and-policies.html)\n*   [Censorship in Singapore](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Censorship_in_Singapore), [MalaysiaSingapore relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malaysia%E2%80%93Singapore_relations)\n    *   Malaysian [human rights](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights) [advocacy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advocacy) group [Lawyers for Liberty](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lawyers_for_Liberty) sues [Singaporean](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Singapore) [Home Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Home_Affairs_(Singapore)) [K. Shanmugam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Shanmugam) in [Malaysian High Court](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High_Courts_(Malaysia)) after his office invoked the country''s anti-[fake news](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fake_news) law to censor the group''s criticisms of the [death penalty there](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_punishment_in_Singapore). The [plaintiff](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plaintiff) argues that the move represents "an attempt by Singapore to encroach upon, stifle or crack down on freedom of speech in Malaysia". [(_South China Morning Post_)](https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/article/3047550/malaysian-watchdog-accused-singapore-brutal-execution-methods)\n*   [MoroccoSpain relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morocco%E2%80%93Spain_relations)\n    *   The foreign ministries of [Spain](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spain) and [Morocco](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morocco) announce they will hold talks to resolve a dispute over [territorial water](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Territorial_water) rights in the [North Atlantic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlantic_Ocean#Northern_Atlantic), caused by the [Moroccan parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parliament_of_Morocco) passing two laws that extended its claims to the coast of [Western Sahara](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Sahara) earlier this week. Spain expressed concerns that these laws would encroach on its claims near the [Canary Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canary_Islands). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-morocco-spain/morocco-spain-to-hold-talks-about-overlapping-territorial-waters-idUSKBN1ZN2EQ)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [2020 Rot am See shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Rot_am_See_shooting)\n    *   Six people are killed and two others wounded when a man [opens fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_shooting) on his family members in [Rot am See](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rot_am_See), [Baden-Wrttemberg](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baden-W%C3%BCrttemberg), [Germany](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany). The mass shooter''s parents are among the dead. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/International/injured-probable-deaths-shooting-germany-police/story?id=68502982)\n*   [LGBT rights in Mauritania](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_rights_in_Mauritania)\n    *   Police detain a gay couple in [Nouakchott](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nouakchott) after a video purportedly of them marrying in a secret location emerges, in what is considered to be the first major prosecution of its kind in recent years. The attendees in the video were also detained. [(_North African Post_)](http://northafricapost.com/37280-mauritania-gay-couple-arrested-in-nouakchott-after-marriage.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_24','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3293,replace('# 2020-01-25\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   Two women, one of them pregnant, are killed and seven others are injured when artillery hits a [Rohingya](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohingya) village in [Rakhine State](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rakhine_State). The locals blame [Myanmar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myanmar)''s [armed forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tatmadaw). The armed forces deny responsibility and blame the [Arakan Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arakan_Army_(Kachin_State)), and say the artillery hit the village amid ethnic clashes. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-myanmar-rohingya/two-rohingya-women-killed-as-myanmar-army-shells-village-mp-idUSKBN1ZO08H)\n*   [Iraqi protests (2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi_protests_(2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   Iraqi security forces raid a protest site in [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad) and try to remove protesters in southern cities, firing [tear gas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tear_gas) and live bullets, killing four and wounding dozens more. The raid comes after [Muqtada al-Sadr](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muqtada_al-Sadr) ordered his followers to withdraw. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iraq-protests/iraqi-security-forces-raid-protest-camps-4-killed-after-sadr-supporters-withdraw-idUSKBN1ZO0AN?il=0)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [General Secretary of the Communist Party of China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_Secretary_of_the_Communist_Party_of_China) [Xi Jinping](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xi_Jinping) holds a special [Party Politburo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politburo_of_the_Communist_Party_of_China) meeting where he says that the country faces a "grave situation" as he warns the virus is "accelerating its speed". [(_People''s Daily_)](http://en.people.cn/n3/2020/0125/c90000-9651799.html)\n    *   The [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) orders the evacuation of the [Consulate General of the United States, Wuhan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consulate_General_of_the_United_States,_Wuhan) employees and U.S. citizens in the city. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/25/world/asia/china-coronavirus.html#link-3db7b2fe)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   The [Boeing 777X](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boeing_777X) completes its first test flight near [Seattle](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seattle), [Washington](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washington_(state)), United States, after two delayed attempts. [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/boeing-777x-9-first-flight/index.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_25','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3298,replace('# 2020-01-26\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Afghan forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_Armed_Forces) launch ground and air operations against the [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban), killing 51 of them in nine [provinces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Provinces_of_Afghanistan) of the country. Afghanistan''s [Ministry of Defense](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Defense_(Afghanistan)) say that the military conducted thirteen ground offensives and twelve airstrikes. In the northern province of [Balkh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balkh_Province), local officials say that three women and four children were killed. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-afghanistan-attacks-surge/afghan-forces-launch-air-ground-attacks-on-taliban-killing-51-idUSKBN1ZP0EG)\n*   [Syrian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Civil_War), [Northwestern Syria offensive (November 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(November_2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Syrian government forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Armed_Forces) retake several cities in the [Idlib Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib_Province) area, amid a push from [Syrian President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_President) [Bashar al-Assad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bashar_al-Assad) to recapture the last rebel strongholds. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-security/syrian-government-forces-capture-towns-in-advance-on-rebel-held-idlib-idUSKBN1ZP0FC)\n*   [Mali War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mali_War)\n    *   Nineteen [Malian soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malian_Armed_Forces) are killed in an attack on an [army camp](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Army_camp). No group has claimed responsibility. [(France24)](https://www.france24.com/en/20200126-mali-militant-attack-army-camp-al-qaeda-islamic-state-sokolo-niono-kill)\n*   [Iraqi protests (2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi_protests_(2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   Amid further heavy clashes in [Baghdad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baghdad) rockets hit the United States embassy wounding at least one. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/iraq-rockets-hit-baghdad-green-zone-anti-gov-protests-200126195616176.html)[(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/27/us-embassy-iraq-rocket-attack-injuries)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [62nd Annual Grammy Awards](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/62nd_Annual_Grammy_Awards)\n    *   [Billie Eilish](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billie_Eilish) sweeps the major categories winning [Song of the Year](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammy_Award_for_Song_of_the_Year), [Record of the Year](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammy_Award_for_Record_of_the_Year), [Album of the Year](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammy_Award_for_Album_of_the_Year), and [Best New Artist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grammy_Award_for_Best_New_Artist). [(_Los Angeles Times_)](https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/music/story/2020-01-26/billie-eilish-sweeps-major-categories-2020-grammys)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   A leading group on the prevention and control of the novel coronavirus outbreak is established, led by Chinese Premier [Li Keqiang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Li_Keqiang). The leading group decides to extend the [Spring Festival](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_New_Year) holiday to contain the coronavirus outbreak. [(Xinhua News)](http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-01/26/c_138735589.htm)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   At least 39 people are dead in the [Brazilian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil) [states](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/States_of_Brazil) of [Minas Gerais](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minas_Gerais) and [Esprito Santo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esp%C3%ADrito_Santo) after heavy rains hit the country''s [southeast region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southeast_Region,_Brazil). [(VEJA)](https://veja.abril.com.br/brasil/minas-registra-cinco-mortes-por-causa-das-chuvas-e-buscas-continuam/)\n*   [Death of Kobe Bryant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death_of_Kobe_Bryant)\n    *   Retired [NBA](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NBA) player [Kobe Bryant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kobe_Bryant), his daughter and seven other people are killed in a helicopter crash in [Calabasas, California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calabasas,_California), U.S. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/US/dead-helicopter-crash-southern-california/story?id=68545466)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Peruvian parliamentary election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Peruvian_parliamentary_election)\n    *   People in [Peru](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peru) head to the polls to elect the members of the country''s [congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congress_of_the_Republic_of_Peru) after its dissolution in September 2019. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51208274)\n*   [Impeachment trial of Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_trial_of_Donald_Trump)\n    *   An unpublished manuscript of former [National Security Advisor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Security_Advisor_(United_States)) [John Bolton](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Bolton)''s book reveals that [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) told him that unfreezing military aid to [Ukraine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine) was conditional on their performing investigations into [Joe Biden](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Biden) and [Hillary Clinton](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hillary_Clinton). [(New York Times)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/26/us/politics/trump-bolton-book-ukraine.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_26','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3303,replace('# 2020-01-28\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Syrian civil war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_civil_war), [Northwestern Syria offensive (November 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(November_2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   The [Syrian Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Army), backed by [Russian Air Force](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Air_Force) support, enters the largely deserted city of [Ma''arrat al-Nu''man](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ma%27arrat_al-Nu%27man) in the northern [Idlib Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib_Governorate). Only light resistance is reported as most rebel groups, including [Hayat Tahrir al-Sham](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hayat_Tahrir_al-Sham), withdrew their fighters. The city had been under rebel control since October 2012. [(Middle East Eye)](https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/pro-government-forces-enter-syrian-rebel-town-maaret-al-numan)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   The [Barakah nuclear power plant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barakah_nuclear_power_plant) in the [United Arab Emirates](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Arab_Emirates), the first commercial [nuclear plant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_plant) in the [Arab world](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arab_world), is declared ready for operation after years of delays. It is expected to go online sometime during this quarter. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/emirates-energy-nuclearpower-idAFL8N29X4CQ)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [2020 Caribbean earthquake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Caribbean_earthquake)\n    *   A magnitude 7.7 [earthquake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earthquake) is recorded off the coast of [Jamaica](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jamaica). [(KRON 4 News)](https://www.kron4.com/news/world/7-3-magnitude-earthquake-hits-near-jamaica/)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [Palau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palau)''s [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Palau) [Thomas Remengesau Jr.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Remengesau_Jr.) bans [chartered flights](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chartered_flight) from [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/People%27s_Republic_of_China) and suspends charter flights from [Macau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macau) and [Hong Kong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong) until further notice. Remengesau is set to issue an executive order to that effect after a meeting with the National Emergency Committee. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/408269/two-men-in-quarantine-in-samoa-over-coronavirus-fears)\n    *   The Health Commission in the central [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) province of [Hubei](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubei) say there are 1,291 new confirmed cases of [novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novel_coronavirus_(2019-nCoV)) and 24 more deaths, bringing the total death toll to 106 people. [(AFP via New Straits Times)](https://www.nst.com.my/world/world/2020/01/560268/china-virus-death-toll-jumps-106-nearly-1300-new-cases)\n    *   [Chinese President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_President) [Xi Jinping](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xi_Jinping) tells the [World Health Organization](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Health_Organization) he is confident about defeating the "devil virus". [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health/chinas-xi-tells-who-hes-confident-of-slaying-devil-virus-idUSKBN1ZR0CF)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   Prosecutor General of [Tajikistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tajikistan), Yusuf Rakhmon, announces the arrest of 113 alleged members of the [Muslim Brotherhood](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muslim_Brotherhood). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-tajikistan-islamist/tajikistan-arrests-113-alleged-muslim-brotherhood-members-idUSKBN1ZR1C5)\n*   [Investigations involving Benjamin Netanyahu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Investigations_involving_Benjamin_Netanyahu)\n    *   [Prime Minister of Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Israel) [Benjamin Netanyahu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benjamin_Netanyahu) withdraws a request for [immunity](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunity) to the [Knesset](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knesset). [Attorney General](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attorney_General_of_Israel) [Avichai Mandelblit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avichai_Mandelblit) formally indicts Netanyahu on charges of [bribery](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bribery), [fraud](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fraud), and [breach of trust](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breach_of_trust) in three cases of suspected [corruption](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corruption). [(Vox)](https://www.vox.com/2020/1/28/21111500/israeli-prime-minister-benjamin-netanyahu-corruption-trump-peace-plan)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 New Zealand general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_New_Zealand_general_election)\n    *   [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_New_Zealand) [Jacinda Ardern](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacinda_Ardern) announces that the next general election is to be held on September 19. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/28/new-zealand-election-jacinda-ardern-sets-september-date-for-poll)\n\n*   [IsraeliPalestinian conflict](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israeli%E2%80%93Palestinian_conflict), [Trump peace plan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trump_peace_plan)\n    *   [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) and [Israeli Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Israel) [Benjamin Netanyahu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benjamin_Netanyahu) unveil a peace plan developed by the Trump administration for three years. The plan recognizes Israeli sovereignty over major settlement blocs in the [occupied](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israeli_occupation_of_the_West_Bank) [West Bank](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Bank), as well as the [annexation of the Jordan Valley](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annexation_of_the_Jordan_Valley), in exchange for a freeze on new Israeli settlements in certain areas for four years. [Palestinian President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Palestine) [Mahmoud Abbas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahmoud_Abbas) dismisses the plan as "nonsense", while Israeli opposition leader [Benny Gantz](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benny_Gantz) casts his support for the plan. [(_Associated Press_)](https://apnews.com/f7d36b9023309ce4b1e423b02abf52c6)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_28','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3306,replace('# 2020-01-29\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Syrian civil war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_civil_war), [Northwestern Syria offensive (November 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(November_2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   The [Syrian Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Army) say that the [armed forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Armed_Forces) are now in full control of the city of [Maaret al-Numan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maaret_al-Numan), after they entered it yesterday with little resistance. [(France24)](https://www.france24.com/en/20200129-syrian-army-takes-over-key-idlib-town-from-rebels-assad-damascus-aleppo)\n*   [Mali War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mali_War)\n    *   [Mali](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mali)''s [Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Mali) [Boubou Ciss](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boubou_Ciss%C3%A9) announces that his country will increase the size of its [armed forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malian_Armed_Forces) by 50% in recruitment to uproot [jihadist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jihadist) groups. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mali-security-army/mali-plans-to-increase-the-size-of-its-army-to-rein-in-jihadists-idUSKBN1ZS2ZG)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   The [British government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_government) announces that rail firm [Northern](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northern_(train_operating_company)) will be [nationalized](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nationalization) following public outcry over [Arriva UK Trains](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arriva_UK_Trains) handling of the firm. Arriva says it "understood the government''s decision", but blames problems on "external factors" such as rail infrastructure. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-51298820)\n*   [Facebook](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facebook) agrees to pay [US$](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._dollar)550 million to settle a [class action](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Class_action) lawsuit launched in 2015 over its mass harvesting of [biometric](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biometrics) data in the [state](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._state) of [Illinois](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illinois). [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/29/technology/facebook-privacy-lawsuit-earnings.html)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   In the [Indian state](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_state) of [Maharashtra](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maharashtra), two vehicles collide and plunge into a well, killing 26 people and injuring 32 others. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-india-accident/twenty-six-killed-in-india-as-bus-plunges-into-well-idUSKBN1ZS1IF)\n*   Thirteen people are injured in a fire at a high rise apartment building in [Los Angeles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Los_Angeles), [California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California), United States. [(KTLA)](https://ktla.com/2020/01/29/fire-erupts-at-high-rise-apartment-building-near-brentwood-for-2nd-time-since-2013/)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [French](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France) Agriculture Minister [Didier Guillaume](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Didier_Guillaume) announces that the [culling of unwanted male chicks](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chick_culling) will be outlawed by the end of 2021, becoming one of the first countries to initiate such a ban. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51301915)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [AlgeriaBangladesh relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algeria%E2%80%93Bangladesh_relations)\n    *   [Algeria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algeria) reopens its [embassy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embassy) in [Dhaka](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dhaka), after closing it in 1990. [(_New Age_)](https://www.newagebd.net/article/97994/algeria-reopens-embassy-after-3-decades-of-closure)\n*   [Brexit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brexit)\n    *   The [European Parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Parliament) votes 62149 to pass the [2020 Brexit agreement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union_(Withdrawal_Agreement)_Act_2020), making today the last day Britain will be represented in Parliament. [MEP](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Member_of_the_European_Parliament) and Brexit campaigner [Nigel Farage](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigel_Farage) applauds its passage by saying "we''d be better off out", while [UK Labour](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Labour_Party_(UK)) MEP [Judith Kirton-Darling](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Judith_Kirton-Darling) tearfully states it "attacks the very foundation of our identity". [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu-parliament/tears-and-cheers-as-eu-lawmakers-give-final-nod-to-brexit-idUSKBN1ZS1EE)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_29','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3311,replace('# 2020-01-30\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Syrian civil war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_civil_war), [Northwestern Syria offensive (November 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(November_2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Warplanes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warplane) backed by the [Syrian Government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Government) strike [Ariha](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ariha), [Idlib Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib_Governorate), killing at least ten people. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/warplanes-kill-10-strike-hospital-syrian-offensive-68634917?cid=clicksource_4380645_2_heads_hero_live_headlines_hed)\n*   Armed men kill at least six [Mayangna Indians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mayangna_people) and kidnap another ten in the [Bosaws Biosphere Reserve](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bosaw%C3%A1s_Biosphere_Reserve), [Nicaragua](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicaragua). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51319198)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Arvind Krishna](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arvind_Krishna_(executive)) is appointed chief executive officer of [IBM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IBM), taking over from [Ginni Rometty](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ginni_Rometty). [(_Wall Street Journal_)](https://www.wsj.com/articles/ginni-rometty-stepping-down-as-ibm-ceo-11580420650)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   Massive floods in [Madagascar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madagascar) kill 31 people and displace 16,000 others. [(_The Weather Channel_)](https://weather.com/news/news/2020-01-30-photos-from-space-show-madagascar-flooding)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   More than 6,000 passengers are barred from disembarking a [cruise ship](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cruise_ship) docked at [Civitavecchia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civitavecchia), [Lazio](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lazio), [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy), after authorities expressed concern that two [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_people) passengers have the [coronavirus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronavirus). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/30/6000-passengers-stuck-on-cruise-ship-in-italy-over-coronavirus-fears)\n    *   Two cases of [novel coronavirus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novel_coronavirus_(2019-nCoV)) are confirmed in [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy) after two Chinese tourists are recovered in [Rome](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rome). [(_Il Messaggero_)](https://www.ilmessaggero.it/mondo/coronavirus_diretta_news_oggi_30_gennaio_2020_morti_casi_sospetti_cina_civitavecchia-5018156.html)\n    *   The [World Health Organization](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Health_Organization) declares a "global emergency", a rare designation that helps the international agency mobilize financial and political support to contain the outbreak. [(CNBC)](https://www.cnbc.com/2020/01/30/coronavirus-latest-updates.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   The [Virginia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia), [Nevada](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nevada), and [Illinois](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illinois) [state attorneys general](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_attorney_general) file a lawsuit to get the [Equal Rights Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equal_Rights_Amendment) added to the [Constitution of the United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitution_of_the_United_States). [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/30/politics/equal-rights-amendment-virginia-litigation-trnd/index.html)\n*   [Japanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) [prosecutors](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prosecutor) issue [arrest warrants](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arrest_warrant) against a former [United States special operations forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_special_operations_forces) [soldier](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Army) and two others for allegedly helping [Carlos Ghosn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Ghosn) to escape from Japan. Another arrest warrant was issued against Ghosn himself. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nissan-ghosn/japan-issues-arrest-warrants-for-ex-u-s-soldier-two-others-for-ghosn-escape-idUSKBN1ZT0DK)\n*   The [U.S. Customs and Border Protection](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Customs_and_Border_Protection) reports that in August it discovered a 1,313m (4,308ft) [smuggling tunnel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smuggling_tunnel) running from [Tijuana](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tijuana) to [San Diego](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Diego), making it the longest tunnel of its type along the [MexicoUnited States border](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico%E2%80%93United_States_border). It was possibly used by the [Sinaloa Cartel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sinaloa_Cartel). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-51304861)\n*   [Catholic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catholic_Church) [Cardinal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardinal_(Catholic_Church)) [Philippe Barbarin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippe_Barbarin) is acquitted by an [appellate court](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Appellate_court) of having covered up allegations of [child sexual abuse](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Child_sexual_abuse) by a former priest. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-church-abuse-france/french-court-overturns-earlier-guilty-verdict-on-cardinal-barbarin-idUSKBN1ZT1M1)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_30','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3316,replace('# 2020-01-31\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Fossil fuel divestment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fossil_fuel_divestment)\n    *   _[The Guardian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Guardian)_ becomes the first major [news outlet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/News_media) to stop accepting ads from the [fossil fuel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fossil_fuel) industry. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/media/2020/jan/29/guardian-to-ban-advertising-from-fossil-fuel-firms-climate-crisis) [(_The Hill_)](https://thehill.com/policy/energy-environment/480533-the-guardian-stops-accepting-ads-from-fossil-fuel-companies-over)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   The [Royal Solomon Islands Police Force](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Solomon_Islands_Police_Force) stop searching for nine people who disappeared at sea on January 15 when their boat capsized. Five men, two women and two children are now presumed dead. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/408543/search-called-off-for-9-lost-at-sea-in-solomons)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [Delta Air Lines](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delta_Air_Lines) and [American Airlines](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Airlines) announce that they have suspended all flights to and from China amid the coronavirus outbreak. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/Health/delta-suspends-us-flights-china-amid-coronavirus/story?id=68666037)\n    *   An airplane with 195 [Americans](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americans) coming back from China is [quarantined](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quarantined). [(CBS)](https://www.cbsnews.com/live-updates/coronavirus-outbreak-china-evacuations-wuhan-death-toll-today-flights-us-cases-2020-01-31/)\n    *   The [Department of Health and Human Services](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Health_and_Human_Services) declares the coronavirus a public health emergency in the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States). [(CNBC)](https://www.cnbc.com/2020/01/31/white-house-to-hold-briefing-on-coronavirus-friday-afternoon.html)\n    *   The [Ministry of Health](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Health_(Spain)) of [Spain](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spain) confirms the first case of coronavirus in the country in [La Gomera](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/La_Gomera), [Canary Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canary_Islands), from a German tourist. [(_El Mundo_)](https://www.elmundo.es/salud/2020/01/31/5e3463effdddfffa7a8b45ac.html)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Brexit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brexit)\n    *   The [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom) formally withdraws from the [European Union](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Union) at 23:00 GMT. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-51194363)\n*   [TanzaniaUnited States relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tanzania%E2%80%93United_States_relations)\n    *   The U.S. bans Tanzanian official [Paul Makonda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Makonda) from entering the U.S. for his announcement about a crackdown on Tanzanian homosexuals in [Dar es Salaam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dar_es_Salaam) in 2018, among other accusations. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-tanzania-sanctions/u-s-bans-tanzanian-official-who-launched-anti-gay-crackdown-idUSKBN1ZU2W9)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   In [Farrukhabad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Farrukhabad), [Uttar Pradesh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uttar_Pradesh), India, a man is shot and killed by police after taking more than 20 children as hostages for more than 10 hours. Angry locals later beat the hostage-taker''s widow to death. It is unknown whether she was involved in her husband''s plan. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-51320991)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Democratic_Party_presidential_primaries)\n    *   Former [Maryland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maryland) [Representative](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_of_Representatives) [John Delaney](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Delaney_(Maryland_politician)) drops out of the U.S. presidential race. [(_Los Angeles Times_)](https://www.latimes.com/politics/story/2020-01-31/john-delaney-2020-candidates-ends-bid)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_January_31','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3319,replace('# 2020-02-01\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   Suspected [Islamist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamist) militants kill at least 62 [civilians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian) in a series of [massacres](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massacre) in eastern [Democratic Republic of the Congo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo) as killings of civilians intensify. The country''s [armed forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Armed_Forces_of_the_Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo) launch counter-offensives against [insurgents](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Insurgent) of the [Allied Democratic Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_Democratic_Forces). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-congo-violence/militants-kill-dozens-in-east-congo-as-attacks-on-civilians-intensify-idUSKBN1ZV3OS)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   400500 people are left stranded at the [Sasquatch Mountain Resort](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sasquatch_Mountain_Resort) in [British Columbia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Columbia), [Canada](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada), after the road to the resort was damaged from landslides caused by heavy rain. Train service between [Vancouver](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vancouver) and [Seattle](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seattle) was also suspenced until Monday due to mudslides. [(CTV News)](https://bc.ctvnews.ca/landslide-washouts-strand-500-people-on-sasquatch-mountain-ski-hill-1.4793567) [(CTV News)](https://bc.ctvnews.ca/mudslide-means-passenger-trains-between-vancouver-and-seattle-won-t-resume-until-monday-1.4793612)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [Kiribati](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kiribati) becomes the latest country in the Pacific to block [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_people) travelers by placing all [visa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Travel_visa) applications from [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) on hold and ordering all those coming from countries with confirmed cases of the virus to self-[quarantine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quarantine). [(Radio NZ International)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/408618/coronavirus-kiribati-blocks-chinese-travellers)\n    *   [Apple Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple_Inc.) announces it will close all of its stores and offices in China until February 9 due to the outbreak. [(Gizmodo)](https://gizmodo.com/apple-is-closing-all-of-its-stores-and-corporate-office-1841410459)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Trump peace plan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trump_peace_plan)\n    *   The [Palestinian Authority](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palestinian_Authority) cuts all ties with the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) and [Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel), including those relating to security, after rejecting a peace plan presented by [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._President) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-israel-palestinians-security/palestinian-authority-cuts-ties-with-israel-and-u-s-idUSKBN1ZV3PO)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   A court in [Egypt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egypt) sentences a former special forces officer and 36 others to the [death penalty](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_punishment_in_Egypt) after being convicted on charges of [terrorism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_Egypt), court officials say. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-egypt-security/egypt-sentences-officer-turned-militant-and-36-others-to-death-idUSKBN1ZV3IW)\n*   Police in [South Africa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa) launch a manhunt for the killers of nine illegal [miners](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miner) who were stoned to death in western [Johannesburg](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johannesburg). All nine killed were from [Lesotho](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesotho). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-51341567)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Iraqi protests (2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraqi_protests_(2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   Former Communications Minister [Mohammed Tawfiq Allawi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohammed_Tawfiq_Allawi) is appointed [Prime Minister of Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Iraq) by [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Iraq) [Barham Salih](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barham_Salih). Protestors reject his appointment, seeing him as part of the establishment. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/iraq-president-appoints-mohammed-allawi-pm-state-tv-200201150554113.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_1','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3324,replace('# 2020-02-02\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2020 Streatham stabbing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Streatham_stabbing)\n    *   Three people are injured after a man attacked people with a [machete](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machete) in [Streatham High Road](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Streatham_High_Road), [London](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London), [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom). The attacker is shot dead by police. The incident is declared as [terrorism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_the_United_Kingdom)\-related. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-london-51349664)\n*   [2020 Ghent stabbing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Ghent_stabbing)\n    *   A female attacker reportedly stabs two people in [Ghent](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghent), [East Flanders](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Flanders), [Belgium](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belgium). The suspect is shot and wounded by [Belgian police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belgian_police). [(Metro)](https://metro.co.uk/2020/02/02/police-shoot-knifeman-belgium-just-minutes-london-terror-attack-12169611/)\n*   [Syrian civil war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_civil_war), [Northwestern Syria offensive (November 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(November_2019%E2%80%93present)), [Turkish involvement in the Syrian Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_involvement_in_the_Syrian_Civil_War)\n    *   More than 200 [Turkish Armed Forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_Armed_Forces) vehicles cross the [SyriaTurkey border](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria%E2%80%93Turkey_border) into rebel-held [Idlib Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib_Governorate) in an effort to halt the [Syrian Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Army) advance on the city of [Saraqib](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saraqib). [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/turkish-military-convoy-crosses-into-rebel-held-nw-syria/2020/02/02/17651c30-45d8-11ea-91ab-ce439aa5c7c1_story.html) [(Al Masdar News)](https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/turkish-military-attempts-to-block-syrian-armys-path-to-saraqib/)\n*   [Sinai insurgency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sinai_insurgency)\n    *   [Islamist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamism) militants bomb a [gas pipeline](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pipeline_transport) between [Egypt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egypt) and [Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel) in the northern [Sinai Peninsula](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sinai_Peninsula). [(Ynet news)](https://www.ynetnews.com/article/rJyLd2VfI)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   The first [coronavirus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novel_coronavirus_(2019-nCoV)) death outside China is reported in the [Philippines](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippines). The victim was a [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_people) [tourist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tourism_in_the_Philippines), also infected with _[Streptococcus pneumoniae](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Streptococcus_pneumoniae)_ and [influenza B](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Influenza_B), who recently arrived in the country. [(CNN Philippines)](https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/2/2/novel-coronavirus-cases-death-Philippines.html)\n    *   [New Zealand](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Zealand) closes its borders to all foreign visitors from [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China) and bolsters screenings at its airports in response to the coronavirus outbreak. The travel ban will be in place for at least fourteen days. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/03/coronavirus-outbreak-new-zealand-bans-foreign-travellers-from-china)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [IranSaudi Arabia relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran%E2%80%93Saudi_Arabia_relations)\n    *   According to Iranian [Foreign Ministry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Iran)), [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia) has blocked [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) from an [Organization of Islamic Cooperation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization_of_Islamic_Cooperation) meeting in [Jeddah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeddah) after Saudi authorities refuse to issue [visas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Travel_visa) to Iranian officials. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-saudi-oic-meeting/saudi-arabia-blocks-iran-from-islamic-groupings-meeting-tehran-idUSKBN1ZW0OP?il=0)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [201920 Persian Gulf crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Persian_Gulf_crisis)\n    *   [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) sends [a destroyer](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JS_Takanami) to the [Gulf of Oman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gulf_of_Oman) amid heightening tensions in the region. The [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Japan) says it is prepared to authorize the use of force to protect Japanese interests if needed. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-iran-japan/japanese-warship-departs-for-gulf-to-patrol-oil-lifeline-idUSKBN1ZW02D)\n\n## Sports\n\n*   [2019 NFL season](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_NFL_season)\n    *   In [American football](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_football), the [Kansas City Chiefs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Kansas_City_Chiefs_season) defeat the [San Francisco 49ers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_San_Francisco_49ers_season) 3120 to win [Super Bowl LIV](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Super_Bowl_LIV), the team''s first Super Bowl win since [1970](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Super_Bowl_IV). [(ESPN)](https://www.espn.com/nfl/recap?gameId=401131047)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_2','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3329,replace('# 2020-02-05\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [2020 Van avalanches](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Van_avalanches)\n    *   [Avalanches](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avalanches) in [Van Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Van_Province), eastern [Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey), kill at least 38 people, leaving more trapped. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51384440)\n*   [Pegasus Airlines Flight 2193](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pegasus_Airlines_Flight_2193)\n    *   A [plane crashes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plane_crash) after overrunning the runway at [Sabiha Gken International Airport](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabiha_G%C3%B6k%C3%A7en_International_Airport), [Istanbul](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istanbul), Turkey, killing 3 people and injuring 155 others. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51384667)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   Around 3,700 people aboard a [cruise ship](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cruise_ship) named _[Diamond Princess](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diamond_Princess_(ship))_ are [quarantined](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quarantine) after ten passengers test positive for the illness at the [port of Yokohama](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Port_of_Yokohama), Japan. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-japan/ten-passengers-on-cruise-liner-docked-in-japan-test-positive-for-coronavirus-idUSKBN1ZY2YE)\n    *   A baby is diagnosed with the virus 30 hours after birth, in the first recorded case of the virus in a newborn. [(New Straits Times)](https://www.nst.com.my/world/world/2020/02/562896/baby-tests-positive-china-virus-just-30-hours-after-birth)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Mexico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico) establishes diplomatic relations with the [Central African Republic](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_African_Republic), resulting in Mexico having diplomatic relations with all [African](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_sovereign_states_and_dependent_territories_in_Africa) states. [(Government of Mexico)](https://www.gob.mx/sre/prensa/mexico-establishes-diplomatic-relations-with-the-central-african-republic?idiom=en)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   The [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom)''s [Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Department_for_Digital,_Culture,_Media_and_Sport) begins a [public consultation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_consultation) on [decriminalizing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decriminalization) the failure to pay the [television licence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Television_licensing_in_the_United_Kingdom) fee. Currently, failure to pay the fee while using a television can result in fines and imprisonment. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51373372)\n*   [Bayard Rustin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayard_Rustin) is posthumously [pardoned](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pardon) by [California Governor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Governor_of_California) [Gavin Newsom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gavin_Newsom) for "anti-gay charges". [(NBC News)](https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/bayard-rustin-gay-civil-rights-icon-pardoned-california-governor-anti-n1130501)\n*   [Denmark](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denmark) jails three men for potentially spying for [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia). [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/denmark-jails-men-suspected-spying-saudi-arabia-68769753?cid=clicksource_4380645_11_heads_posts_headlines_hed)\n*   [LGBT rights in Nigeria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_rights_in_Nigeria)\n    *   A court in [Nigeria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigeria) grants 47 men another delay in their trial over [homosexuality](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homosexuality) and public displays of affection with members of the same sex. Judge Rilwan Aikawa says it is the last accepted delay at the [Lagos](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lagos) court. The men face up to 10-year imprisonment if convicted in a closely watched trial. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nigeria-lgbt/court-case-of-47-nigerian-men-charged-under-homosexuality-law-delayed-again-idUSKBN1ZZ2HJ?il=0)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Impeachment trial of Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_trial_of_Donald_Trump)\n    *   The [United States Senate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Senate) votes on whether to acquit [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump). By a vote of 5248 almost entirely along party lines, the [Republican](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republican_Party_(United_States))\-majority Senate acquits Trump on the first article of impeachment, [abuse of power](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abuse_of_power), and acquits him on the the second charge, [obstruction of Congress](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contempt_of_Congress), in a separate 5347 vote. [Utah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Utah) Senator [Mitt Romney](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mitt_Romney) casts the sole Republican guilty vote, against party lines, on the first article. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/05/us/politics/trump-acquitted-impeachment.html)\n*   The [Romanian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romania) minority [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Romania) led by [Ludovic Orban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludovic_Orban) is toppled by a [vote of no confidence](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vote_of_no_confidence). The event could lead to an [early election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next_Romanian_legislative_election). [(DW)](https://www.dw.com/en/romanias-centrist-government-collapses-after-no-confidence-vote/a-52269157)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_5','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3335,replace('# 2020-02-07\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Credit Suisse](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Credit_Suisse) [CEO](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chief_executive_officer) [Tidjane Thiam](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tidjane_Thiam) resigns after a spying scandal. [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/07/business/credit-suisse-ceo-resigns/index.html)\n*   [Batterygate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batterygate)\n    *   [Apple Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apple_Inc.) is fined [](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euro)25 million by [French](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France) [regulatory agency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regulatory_agency) [General Directorate of Competition, Consumption & Repression of Frauds](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DGCCRF) for deliberately slowing down older [iPhone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPhone) models. The fine amounts to less than 0.003% of Apple Inc.''s current worth. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-51413724)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   Five people are killed in a [plane crash](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plane_crash) in Western [Alaska](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alaska), [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States). [(NBC News)](https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/five-dead-commuter-plane-crash-western-alaska-n1132131)\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [Chinese President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China) [Xi Jinping](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xi_Jinping) declares [people''s war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/People%27s_war) on the [coronavirus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronavirus) outbreak. [(_The National_)](https://www.thenational.ae/world/asia/coronavirus-china-declares-people-s-war-on-outbreak-1.975219) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health/china-wages-peoples-war-on-coronavirus-as-cruises-companies-hit-idUSKBN20003J)\n    *   [Li Wenliang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Li_Wenliang), the doctor who tried to issue the first warnings about the coronavirus outbreak, dies after contracting the virus. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-51403795)\n    *   [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy) confirms that an [Italian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italians) man has contracted the virus, after he visited his girlfriend in [Wuhan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wuhan). [(_Il Messaggero_)](https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_diretta_italia_italiano_contagiato_quarantena_cecchignola_chi_e_ultime_notizie-5034364.html)\n    *   [Royal Caribbean Cruises](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Caribbean_Cruises) bans [China](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China), [Hong Kong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong) or [Macau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macau) passport holders from boarding its ships amid concerns over the coronavirus outbreak. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-royal-caribbean/royal-caribbean-bans-china-hong-kong-macau-passport-holders-from-ships-on-coronavirus-fears-idUSKBN2012I5)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [Esperanza Base](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esperanza_Base) on the [Antarctic Peninsula](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antarctic_Peninsula) reaches a temperature of 18.3C (64.9F), the [hottest on record](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_weather_records#Antarctica) for continental Antarctica. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/07/antarctica-logs-hottest-temperature-on-record-with-a-reading-of-183c) [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/weather/2020/02/07/antarctica-just-hit-65-degrees-its-warmest-temperature-ever-recorded)\n*   It is reported January 2020 was the warmest January ever on record in Europe. [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/weather/2020/02/03/warmth-is-really-unheard-much-eastern-europe-including-helsinki-moscow-saw-warmest-january-record) [(_Time_)](https://time.com/5779142/global-temperatures-warmest-january)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Russia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia) repatriates 26 [Russian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russians) children from a [Syrian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria) refugee camp. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/russia-repatriates-26-children-syrian-refugee-camp-68820291?cid=clicksource_4380645_2_heads_hero_live_headlines_hed)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Manish Shah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manish_Shah), a [general practitioner](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_practitioner) in the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom), is given three [life sentences](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_sentence) at the [Old Bailey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Bailey) for 90 [sexual assaults](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_assault) on 24 of his female patients. [(BBC)](https://bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-51415001)\n*   Patrick Crusius, accused of perpetrating the [2019 El Paso shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_El_Paso_shooting), is charged with 90 counts of federal [hate crimes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hate_crime). Under the new charges, he could face the [death penalty](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_punishment_in_the_United_States). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-51413425)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) fires [National Security Council](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_National_Security_Council) advisor [Lt. Col. Alexander Vindman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Vindman) and [E.U. ambassador](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Ambassador_to_the_European_Union) [Gordon Sondland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gordon_Sondland), who both testified as witnesses at the [impeachment inquiry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impeachment_inquiry_against_Donald_Trump) against him. Vindman''s twin brother, Lt. Col. Yevgeny Vindman, an [Army JAG](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Judge_Advocate_General%27s_Corps,_United_States_Army) officer also part of the National Security Council staff, is also fired. [(_New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/07/us/politics/alexander-vindman-gordon-sondland-fired.html) [(Politico)](https://www.politico.com/news/2020/02/07/donald-trump-pressure-impeachment-witness-alexander-vindman-111997)\n*   [2020 Republican Party presidential primaries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Republican_Party_presidential_primaries)\n    *   Former [Illinois](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illinois) [representative](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_House_of_Representatives) [Joe Walsh](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Walsh_(American_politician)) suspends his [presidential campaign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Walsh_2020_presidential_campaign), following his poor perfomance in the [Iowa caucuses](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Iowa_Republican_caucuses). [(_The Hill_)](https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/481979-joe-walsh-ends-primary-challenge-to-trump)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_7','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3338,replace('# 2020-02-08\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2020 Nakhon Ratchasima shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Nakhon_Ratchasima_shooting)\n    *   A soldier [opens fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_shooting) in a [military camp](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military_camp) and a [shopping center](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shopping_center) in [Nakhon Ratchasima](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nakhon_Ratchasima), [Thailand](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thailand), killing 29 people and injuring 58 others before being shot dead by [police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Thai_Police) the next day. It is considered the deadliest mass shooting in the country''s history. [(_Bangkok Post_)](https://www.bangkokpost.com/thailand/general/1853334/17-killed-as-soldier-opens-fire-in-korat) [(USA Today)](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/02/08/thailand-soldier-terminal-21-mall-shooting-rampage-korat/4700184002/)\n*   At least eight people have been killed and dozens have been injured in ethnic clashes in [Kazakhstan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kazakhstan). About 30 houses and 15 commercial properties were destroyed during the clash. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51425938)\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present))\n    *   A [shootout](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shootout) during [joint exercises](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military_exercise#Joint_exercise) with [U.S.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Army) and [Afghan soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_National_Army) in [Nangarhar Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nangarhar_Province) leaves between four and six Americans, and six Afghans dead. It is unknown if the [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) or [rogue Afghan forces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NATO_Training_Mission-Afghanistan#Green-on-blue_attacks) were responsible. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-afghanistan/american-afghan-soldiers-killed-in-shootout-in-afghanistan-ny-times-idUSKBN2020Q9)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Argentine Vice President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argentine_Vice_President) [Cristina Fernndez de Kirchner](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cristina_Fern%C3%A1ndez_de_Kirchner) declares that the [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Argentina) will not pay back its [US$](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._dollar)57 billion debt to the [International Monetary Fund](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Monetary_Fund) until the country exits its [recession](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recession). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cuba-argentina/argentina-wont-repay-imf-debt-till-recession-over-vp-fernandez-say-idUSKBN20302R?il=0)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   Two people  one [Japanese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_people) and one [American](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Americans)  die from coronavirus in [Wuhan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wuhan). They are the first foreigners (excluding [Hong Kong](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong) and [Macau](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macau)) to die from it. [(NBC News)](https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/coronavirus-updates-u-s-japanese-citizens-die-wuhan-global-deaths-n1132951)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [SyriaTurkey relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria%E2%80%93Turkey_relations)\n    *   [Iranian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran) [Foreign Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Iran)) [Mohammad Javad Zarif](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohammad_Javad_Zarif) offers to mediate between [Syria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria) and [Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey) over escalating conflicts between the two nations following the [recent offensive in the Idlib Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(November_2019%E2%80%93present)). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-security-iran-turkey/iran-says-it-is-ready-to-mediate-between-turkey-and-syria-idUSKBN2020HO)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Irish general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Irish_general_election)\n    *   Citizens of [Ireland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_Ireland) head to the polls in the country''s latest [general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elections_in_the_Republic_of_Ireland). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/08/ireland-general-election-sinn-fein-tipped-breakthrough)\n    *   Exit polls show the [republican](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Irish_republicanism) [Sinn Fin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sinn_F%C3%A9in), the ruling [Fine Gael](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fine_Gael), and main opposition party [Fianna Fil](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fianna_F%C3%A1il) in a virtual tie. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/08/ireland-general-eleciton-sinn-fein-surge-to-22-in-exit-poll)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_8','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3343,replace('# 2020-02-09\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   [92nd Academy Awards](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/92nd_Academy_Awards)\n    *   At this year''s [Oscars](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Awards), [South Korean](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cinema_of_South_Korea) film _[Parasite](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parasite_(2019_film))_ wins the most awards, including [Best Picture](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Picture) and [Best International Film](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_International_Feature_Film). It becomes the first foreign-language film to win Best Picture. [(_The Hollywood Reporter_)](https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/oscar-winners-2020-updating-live-full-list-1275973/item/director-1275980)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   The death toll of the coronavirus outbreak surpasses the death toll of the [200203 SARS outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Severe_acute_respiratory_syndrome#Outbreak_in_South_China), at 910 deaths. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/09/coronavirus-global-death-toll-overtakes-sars-epidemic) [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/china-virus-death-toll-surges-800-infections-mount-200209003721741.html)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [Cross-Strait relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cross-Strait_relations)\n    *   [Taiwan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taiwan) scrambles its [air force](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_China_Air_Force) to intercept [Chinese jets](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/People%27s_Liberation_Army_Air_Force) after they circled the island during a combat drill. The drill is denounced by the [Taiwanese Defense Ministry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_National_Defense_(Republic_of_China)) as a violation of its sovereignty. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-taiwan-china-defence/taiwan-scrambles-armed-jets-as-chinese-air-force-flies-around-island-idUSKBN2030AE)\n*   [IsraelPalestine relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel%E2%80%93Palestine_relations)\n    *   Israel blocks all Palestinian export of agricultural products from the occupied West Bank following Palestinian limitations on imports of Israeli cattle. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/israel-blocks-palestinian-agricultural-exports-jordan-200209104227779.html) [(_Haaretz_)](https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/israel-to-bar-palestinians-from-exporting-produce-via-jordan-as-trade-war-escalates-1.8506459)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Azerbaijani parliamentary election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Azerbaijani_parliamentary_election)\n    *   [Azerbaijan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azerbaijan) holds a [snap election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Snap_election) after [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Azerbaijan) [Ilham Aliyev](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ilham_Aliyev) dissolved the [National Assembly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Assembly_(Azerbaijan)) last December. The opposition accuses Aliyev of limiting their ability to campaign, and calls for boycotts against the election. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-azerbaijan-election/azeri-president-moves-to-modernize-parliament-with-snap-election-idUSKBN2020S9) [(France24)](https://www.france24.com/en/20200209-azerbaijan-holds-elections-decried-as-sham-by-opposition)\n*   [2020 Cameroonian parliamentary election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Cameroonian_parliamentary_election)\n    *   After having been postponed twice, [parliamentary elections](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elections_in_Cameroon) are held in [Cameroon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cameroon). The ongoing [Anglophone Crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anglophone_Crisis) overshadows the process, with supporters of [Ambazonia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ambazonia) calling for a boycott of the election. [(DW)](https://www.dw.com/en/cameroon-elections-a-vote-marked-by-violence-and-abstention/a-52304640)\n*   [2020 Irish general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Irish_general_election)\n    *   Counting of the first preference votes show [Sinn Fin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sinn_F%C3%A9in) leading with 24.1% of the vote, ahead of ruling party [Fine Gael](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fine_Gael) and main opposition party [Fianna Fil](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fianna_F%C3%A1il), each with 22.1%. Sinn Fin leader [Mary Lou McDonald](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mary_Lou_McDonald) claims victory, declaring that Ireland "is no longer a two-party system", and hopes to form a coalition government. [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/09/sinn-fein-to-try-to-form-ruling-coalition-after-irish-election-success)\n*   [2020 Swiss referendums](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Swiss_referendums), [LGBT rights in Switzerland](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_rights_in_Switzerland)\n    *   [Swiss](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Switzerland) voters head to the polls to vote on a proposal to mandate quotas for affordable housing in new residential development projects, and whether to criminalize discrimination on the basis of [sexual orientation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_orientation). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51370820) [(_Irish Times_)](https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/europe/switzerland-is-putting-its-housing-crisis-to-a-referendum-1.4155510)\n    *   The proposal to mandate quotas is rejected, the proposal to criminalize discrimination on the basis of [sexual orientation](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_orientation) passes. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51370820)\n*   [President of El Salvador](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_El_Salvador) [Nayib Bukele](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nayib_Bukele) breaks into the [Legislative Assembly](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legislative_Assembly_of_El_Salvador) with the Army and occupies the chair of the Speaker to demand the approval of a financial measure which couldn''t pass earlier as there was no quorum. In a public release, the Presidency department calls for calm after a "demand of insurrection". The opposition accuses the president and the army of intimidation and a "[self-coup](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-coup)". [(_El Pas_)](https://elpais.com/internacional/2020/02/10/america/1581294344_999638.html) [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51439020) [(_The Washington Post_)](https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/el-salvador-standoff-deepens-over-loan-for-security-forces/2020/02/09/1eb51fb6-4b97-11ea-967b-e074d302c7d4_story.html) [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2020/02/09/world/americas/ap-lt-bc-el-salvador-loan-standoff.html)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   The [United Launch Alliance](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Launch_Alliance) successfully launches the [European Space Agency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Space_Agency)''s [Solar Orbiter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_Orbiter) (SolO) satellite from [Cape Canaveral Air Force Station](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cape_Canaveral_Air_Force_Station). The probe will study the [Sun](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sun), and in particular its inner [heliosphere](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heliosphere). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-51420402)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_9','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3348,replace('# 2020-02-15\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Yemeni Civil War (2015present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yemeni_Civil_War_(2015%E2%80%93present))\n    *   The [Houthis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houthis) accuse [Saudi Arabia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Arabia) of [airstrikes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airstrike) that killed 30 people, including [civilians](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civilian), in [Al Jawf Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al_Jawf_Governorate). The Houthis say women and children were among those killed in the strike, which was said to be a retaliation for the downing of a coalition plane the previous day. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-yemen-security/yemens-houthis-say-coalition-strikes-kill-30-including-civilians-idUSKBN2090AC)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [201920 Wuhan coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_Wuhan_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   The first death from the disease inside [Europe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Europe) occurs in [France](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France). He was an 80-year-old [Chinese](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_people) [tourist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tourism_in_France) who had arrived in [Paris](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris) with symptoms of the illness on January 16. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837)\n*   [Storm Dennis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storm_Dennis)\n    *   The [British Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Army) is deployed to help with rescue efforts as the [bomb cyclone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Explosive_cyclogenesis) kills two people. [(UPI)](https://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2020/02/15/Army-deployed-to-help-combat-deadly-Storm-Dennis-in-Britain/2671581794747/)\n\n## International relations\n\n*   [AustraliaUnited Kingdom relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia%E2%80%93United_Kingdom_relations)\n    *   Several senior [Australian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia) MPs cancel a planned trip to the [United Kingdom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom) next month due to the latter allowing [Huawei](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huawei) to help build its national [5G](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/5G) network. Australia had banned the Chinese telecom from participating in [their network](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telecommunications_in_Australia) due to [security concerns](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Criticism_of_Huawei#Espionage_and_security_concerns). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-australia-51513886)\n*   [IndiaTurkey relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India%E2%80%93Turkey_relations)\n    *   [Indian Ministry of External Affairs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_External_Affairs_(India)) spokesman [Raveesh Kumar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raveesh_Kumar) tells [Turkish President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Turkey) [Recep Tayyip Erdoan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo%C4%9Fan) to "not interfere in [India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India)''s internal affairs" after he and [Pakistani Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Pakistan) [Imran Khan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan) issued a joint declaration yesterday condemning the [lockdown](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019-20_Jammu_and_Kashmir_lockdown) in [Jammu and Kashmir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jammu_and_Kashmir). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/kashmir-india-tells-turkey-don-interfere-internal-affairs-200215182136914.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Labour Party leadership election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Labour_Party_leadership_election)\n    *   [Shadow First Secretary of State](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shadow_First_Secretary_of_State) [Emily Thornberry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emily_Thornberry) is eliminated from the [UK Labour](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Labour_Party_(UK)) leadership race after falling two nominations short of advancing to the next round. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-51505547)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_15','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3353,replace('# 2020-02-16\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [South Sudanese Civil War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudanese_Civil_War)\n    *   [SPLM-IO](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudan_People%27s_Liberation_Movement-in-Opposition) leader and former [Vice President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vice_President_of_South_Sudan) [Riek Machar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riek_Machar) rejects a peace proposal by President [Salva Kiir Mayardit](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salva_Kiir_Mayardit). While Machar welcomes the provision to reduce the number of [states](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/States_of_South_Sudan) from 32 to 10, he opposes the creation of three administrative areas. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/south-sudan-machar-rejects-president-kiir-peace-offer-200216090638473.html)\n*   [Syrian civil war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_civil_war), [Northwestern Syria offensive (December 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(December_2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   Backed by [Russian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Air_Force) [airstrikes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airstrike), [Syrian Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Army) troops take control of most of the [Aleppo countryside](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Simeon_District), including the towns of [Anadan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anadan), [Haritan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haritan) and [Kafr Hamrah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kafr_Hamrah) and over 30 villages amid a collapse in rebel defences. Much of the area has been under rebel control since 2012. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-security-army/russian-backed-syrian-army-seizes-most-of-rebel-held-aleppo-province-state-media-idUSKBN20A0KQ?il=0) [(NBC News)](https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/syrian-forces-seize-most-aleppo-province-eve-turkey-russia-talks-n1137631)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   The [United States District Court for the Eastern District of Missouri](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_District_Court_for_the_Eastern_District_of_Missouri) rules that chemical companies [Bayer](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayer) and [BASF](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BASF) are accountable for the adverse effects of their [Dicamba](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dicamba)\-based [herbicides](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herbicide) on American farmlands, and awards the plaintiff, a [peach](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peach) farmer, [US$](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._dollar)265 million in damages. Bayer announces it will appeal. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bayer-dicamba-lawsuit/u-s-peach-grower-awarded-265-million-from-bayer-basf-in-weedkiller-lawsuit-idUSKBN20A0JJ?il=0)\n*   A [German](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany) court orders [Tesla, Inc.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tesla,_Inc.) to temporarily halt construction of new manufacturing plant [Giga Berlin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giga_Berlin) in [Grnheide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gr%C3%BCnheide_(Mark)), [Brandenburg](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brandenburg), due to the threat it poses to the local wildlife and water supplies. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/business-51525673)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [Storm Dennis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storm_Dennis)\n    *   The [bomb cyclone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Explosive_cyclogenesis) claims another victim, bringing the death toll to three. 198 [flood warnings](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flood_warning) have been placed across [England](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England). [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/16/uk/storm-dennis-sunday-intl-gbr/index.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Azerbaijani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azerbaijan) [police](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_enforcement_in_Azerbaijan) detain three opposition party leaders and more than 100 activists for attempting to protest the results of last week''s [parliamentary election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Azerbaijani_parliamentary_election). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-azerbaijan-election-opposition/azeri-police-detain-opposition-leaders-block-protest-against-election-result-idUSKBN20A0F3?il=0)\n*   Nine [homeless](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homelessness) drug users are shot dead while sleeping rough in the [Afghan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan) capital [Kabul](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kabul). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/homeless-drug-users-shot-dead-afghan-capital-police-200217032011711.html)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Paris municipal election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Paris_municipal_election)\n    *   [French](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France) Health Minister [Agns Buzyn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agn%C3%A8s_Buzyn) announces she will run for the [Parisian mayoral](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_mayors_of_Paris) position on the [La Rpublique En Marche!](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/La_R%C3%A9publique_En_Marche!) ticket, after the party''s original candidate [Benjamin Griveaux](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benjamin_Griveaux) withdrew yesterday due to a [sexting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexting) scandal. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-france-politics/french-health-minister-to-run-for-paris-mayor-after-macron-ally-quits-idUSKBN20A0HI?il=0)\n*   [2020 North Macedonian parliamentary election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_North_Macedonian_parliamentary_election)\n    *   The [Assembly of North Macedonia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Assembly_of_North_Macedonia) votes 10812 to dissolve itself after [the country](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Macedonia) failed to start [accession talks with the European Union](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accession_of_North_Macedonia_to_the_European_Union), and sets the parliamentary election date for April 12. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-north-macedonia-election/north-macedonia-parliament-dissolves-sets-poll-date-after-eu-shuns-talks-idUSKBN20A0ON)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_16','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3358,replace('# 2020-02-17\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Syrian civil war](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_civil_war), [Northwestern Syria offensive (December 2019present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northwestern_Syria_offensive_(December_2019%E2%80%93present))\n    *   [Syrian President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Syria) [Bashar al-Assad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bashar_al-Assad) gives a televised speech on the [military](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Armed_Forces) offensives in north-western Syria, saying the offensives in [Aleppo Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aleppo_Governorate) and [Idlib Governorate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idlib_Governorate) will continue regardless of [Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey)''s threats while adding that the recent [Syrian Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syrian_Army) victories are a prelude to the opposition''s "final defeat, sooner or later". [(Al Masdar News)](https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/victory-in-aleppo-does-not-mean-end-of-syrian-war-assad/) [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-security-assad/syrias-assad-says-his-forces-gains-are-prelude-to-rebels-final-defeat-idUSKBN20B1MM)\n*   [February 2020 Quetta bombing](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/February_2020_Quetta_bombing)\n    *   At least 10 people are killed by a [suicide bomber](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicide_bomb) on a motorcycle in [Quetta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quetta), [Balochistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balochistan,_Pakistan), [Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-pakistan-blast/suicide-blast-kills-10-in-pakistan-city-of-quetta-idUSKBN20B1B5)\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [General Motors](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_Motors) pulls out of [right-hand drive markets](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Left-hand_traffic), ending the [Holden](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holden) brand in [Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia). [(9 News)](https://www.9news.com.au/national/holden-axed-from-australia-in-2020-ending-72-years-of-car-making/29ba88b5-3061-4839-921d-b2fea77dcd21)\n*   [Emirati](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Arab_Emirates) port operating firm [DP World](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DP_World) returns to being wholly [state-owned](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State-owned_enterprise) by the [Dubai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emirate_of_Dubai) government, after its [sovereign wealth fund](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sovereign_wealth_fund) [Dubai World](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dubai_World) buys back the company''s remaining stakes. DP World is subsequently delisted from the [NASDAQ Dubai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASDAQ_Dubai) exchange. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-dp-wrld-delisting/dubais-dp-world-to-delist-return-to-full-state-ownership-idUSKBN20B0F8?il=0)\n*   The [Aleppo International Airport](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aleppo_International_Airport) in [Aleppo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aleppo), [Syria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria), opens to the public for the first time since 2013. Syrian Transport Minister [Ali Hammoud](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ali_Hammoud) says regular commercial flights will begin within days, starting with [Cairo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cairo), [Egypt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egypt). [(Reuters)](https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-syria-security/syrian-forces-consolidate-control-of-aleppo-air-strikes-under-way-idUKKBN20B0X3) [(Al Masdar News)](https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/syria-to-reopen-aleppo-international-airport-for-first-time-in-9-years/)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [Storm Dennis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storm_Dennis)\n    *   The lower reaches of many rivers, including the [Severn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/River_Severn) at [Shrewsbury](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shrewsbury), continue to rise as a result of excess runoff from upstream. The [River Wye](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/River_Wye) in [Hereford](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hereford) has now reached its highest level in recorded history. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51526879)\n*   At least 20 people, mostly women and children, are killed in a [stampede](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_stampede) during a rush to collect aid supplies upon the opening of the gates to an aid facility in [Diffa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diffa), south-eastern [Niger](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niger). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-51537144)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Sagamihara stabbings](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sagamihara_stabbings)\n    *   Prosecutors in [Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan) announce they are officially seeking the [death penalty](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_punishment_in_Japan) against [Satoshi Uematsu](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satoshi_Uematsu) for stabbing 19 [disabled](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disability_in_Japan) people to death in 2016. [(CNA)](https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/care-home-murder-trial-court-satoshi-uematsu-death-penalty-12441848)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [Andrew Sabisky](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Sabisky), an advisor to [UK Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_the_United_Kingdom) [Boris Johnson](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Johnson), resigns after [racist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Racism_in_the_United_Kingdom) and [sexist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexism) comments, as well as comments supporting [eugenics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eugenics), allegedly attributed to him resurface. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-51538493)\n\n## Sports\n\n*   [2020 Daytona 500](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Daytona_500)\n    *   Denny Hamlin wins his second consecutive Daytona 500, and his third overall, becoming the first driver to win the race consecutively since [Sterling Marlin](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sterling_Marlin) did so between 1994 and 1995. [Ryan Newman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ryan_Newman_(racing_driver)) is hospitalized with serious but non-life threatening injuries after an airborne crash coming to the finish. [(WESH)](https://www.wesh.com/article/daytona-500-ryan-newman-crash/30972164)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_17','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3362,replace('# 2020-02-21\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [War in Afghanistan (2001present)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%93present)), [Afghan peace process](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_peace_process)\n    *   A seven-day "reduction of violence" between [United States troops](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Armed_Forces), [Afghan troops](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan_Armed_Forces), and the [Taliban](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taliban) is due to start at midnight local time (19:30 UTC). If the partial [truce](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ceasefire) is successful, a USTaliban agreement on withdrawing American troops would be signed on February 29. [(NBC News)](https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/u-s-taliban-reduction-violence-start-friday-ahead-broader-deal-n1140206)\n*   [Kashmir conflict](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kashmir_conflict)\n    *   India and Pakistan have engaged in a military confrontation across the _de facto_ border in [Kashmir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kashmir); [Indian](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Armed_Forces) and [Pakistani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_Armed_Forces) forces [exchanged fire](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_India%E2%80%93Pakistan_border_skirmishes) near the [Line of Control](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Line_of_Control) (LoC) in [Kupwara district](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kupwara_district), [Jammu and Kashmir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jammu_and_Kashmir_(union_territory)). One Pakistani soldier died in the exchange of fire. [(Hindustan Times)](https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/indian-forces-respond-to-ceasefire-violation-by-pakistan-in-jammu-and-kashmir/story-6MexMQaEkfMVDSz59WGvfP.html)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel) and [Lebanon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanon) report their first cases of 2019-nCoV coronavirus. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/cloneofcloneofcloneofcloneofcloneof2002152244372-200220231446112.html)\n    *   [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy) confirms 18 more coronavirus cases in the country, bringing the confirmed cases to twenty-one. All eighteen are Italian citizens. [(Corriere della Sera)](https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_21/coronavirus-italia-cosa-sappiamo-casi-codogno-lombardia-27fa736c-548b-11ea-9196-da7d305401b7.shtml)\n    *   [North Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Korea) cancels this year''s [Pyongyang Marathon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyongyang_Marathon) due to concerns about coronavirus. [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/cloneofcloneofcloneofcloneofcloneof2002152244372-200220231446112.html)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   [Prime Minister of Lesotho](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Lesotho) [Tom Thabane](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Thabane) fails to appear in court for the murder of his former wife, and his son says he has traveled to [South Africa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Africa) to see a doctor. Police warn that if he does not return, they will issue an [arrest warrant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arrest_warrant). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-lesotho-politics/lesotho-pm-due-in-court-over-first-wifes-death-travels-to-south-africa-idUSKBN20F19L) [(_Independent Online_)](https://www.iol.co.za/news/africa/lesotho-police-if-thomas-thabane-tries-to-flee-justice-we-will-issue-arrest-warrant-43134096)\n*   The [Constitutional Court of Thailand](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constitutional_Court_of_Thailand) orders the [Future Forward Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Future_Forward_Party) to be dissolved. [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/thai-court-orders-popular-opposition-party-dissolved-69120382)\n*   [Mexico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico) [extradites](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extradition) [Rubn Oseguera Gonzlez](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rub%C3%A9n_Oseguera_Gonz%C3%A1lez), the son of [Nemesio Oseguera Cervantes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nemesio_Oseguera_Cervantes), to the [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) to face drug charges. [Nemesio Oseguera Cervantes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nemesio_Oseguera_Cervantes) is the leader of the [Jalisco New Generation Cartel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalisco_New_Generation_Cartel). [(ABC News)](https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/mexico-extradites-son-jalisco-cartel-face-us-charges-69125126)\n*   [Wells Fargo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wells_Fargo) is set to pay $3 billion over their 2016 scandal of creating fake accounts in customers'' names. [(NBC News)](https://www.nbcnews.com/news/all/wells-fargo-pay-3-billion-over-fake-account-scandal-n1140541)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Dominican Republic municipal elections](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Dominican_Republic_municipal_elections)\n    *   The [Major opposition party (PRM)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modern_Revolutionary_Party) asked for protection for its presidential security chief. [(Dominican Today)](https://dominicantoday.com/dr/local/2020/02/21/opposition-party-wants-protection-for-candidates-security-chief/)\n    *   The Protest-in-black continues into the fourth day. [(Dominican Today)](https://dominicantoday.com/dr/local/2020/02/21/a-4th-protest-in-black-in-dominican-republic/)\n    *   [Attorney General](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Attorney_General_of_the_Republic_(Dominican_Republic)) [Jean Alain Rodrguez Snchez](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Alain_Rodr%C3%ADguez_S%C3%A1nchez) launches a plan to [sequester](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sequestration_(law)) the [Justice Ministry](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministry_of_Justice,_Immigration_and_National_Security_(Dominica)) for [partisan purposes.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partisan_(politics)) [(Dominican Today)](https://dominicantoday.com/dr/local/2020/02/21/dominican-rep-ag-aims-to-sequester-the-justice-ministry/)\n\n*   [2020 Iranian legislative election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Iranian_legislative_election)\n    *   [Parliamentary elections](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elections_in_Iran) are being held in [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran). The election is criticized for the barring of around 9,000 candidates, thus raising the concerns of an unusual low [voter turnout](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Voter_turnout). [(DW)](https://www.dw.com/en/iran-polls-open-in-parliamentary-elections/a-52457553) [(The Guardian)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/21/irans-leaders-warn-low-turnout-in-election-will-boost-trump)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_21','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3366,replace('# 2020-02-22\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Kashmir conflict](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kashmir_conflict)\n    *   Two Kashmiri civilians alleged to be [Lashkar-e-Taiba](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lashkar-e-Taiba) militants are killed by [Indian soldiers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Army) at [Anantnag](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anantnag), [Jammu and Kashmir](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jammu_and_Kashmir_(union_territory)), in a [counter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Counter-terrorism)\-[terrorism](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_India) operation. [(DNA India)](https://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-jk-two-terrorists-affiliated-with-lashkar-e-taiba-gunned-down-in-south-kashmir-s-anantnag-2814523) [(ARY News)](https://arynews.tv/en/indian-troops-martyr-two-kashmiris-indian-occupied-kashmir/)\n*   Five [terrorists](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terrorism_in_Pakistan) are killed in [Peshawar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peshawar), [Khyber Paktunkhwa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khyber_Paktunkhwa), [Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan), by the Counter-Terrorism Department ([CTD](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_Army)) in a heavy exchange of fire during a search operation. [(Geo News)](https://www.geo.tv/latest/273607-ctd-kills-five-terrorists-in-security-operation-near-peshawar)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Italy)\n        *   [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy) confirms that a 78-year-old man in [Padua](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Padua), [Veneto](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veneto), and a woman in her 70s in [Codogno](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Codogno), [Lombardy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lombardy), have died after contracting the virus. They are the first two coronavirus deaths in Italy. [(Tgcom24)](https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/coronavirus-nuovo-caso-di-contagio-in-veneto-un-67enne-di-dolo_15145712-202002a.shtml?refresh_cens)\n        *   58 more coronavirus cases are confirmed in Italy, bringing the number of cases to 79. [(Open)](https://www.open.online/2020/02/22/coronavirus-nuovo-caso-nel-padovano-19-contagiati-nel-nord-italia-tampone-in-corso-su-600-persone-tutti-gli-aggiornamenti/)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in South Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_South_Korea)\n        *   [South Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea) confirms that 229 more people have contracted the coronavirus in the country, raising the total number to 433. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51596665)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in the United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_the_United_States)\n        *   The [United States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States) reports 34 confirmed cases of the illness and expects more. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/21/health/coronavirus-cases-usa.html)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Asia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Asia)\n        *   The first coronavirus case is confirmed in [Iraq](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iraq). [(Anadolu Agency)](https://www.aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraq-reports-first-coronavirus-infection/1741593)\n        *   [Samoa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samoa) bans all [cruise ships](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cruise_ship) from visiting the country amid growing efforts to keep the virus away. [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/410113/samoa-places-blanket-ban-on-cruise-ship-visits)\n\n*   [France](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France) shuts down its first [nuclear power](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_power) [reactor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_reactor), at the [Fessenheim Nuclear Power Plant](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fessenheim_Nuclear_Power_Plant). [(Deutsche Welle)](https://www.dw.com/en/france-shuts-down-first-reactor-of-fessenheim-nuclear-plant-near-german-border/a-52466064)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   Lesotho PM [Tom Thabane](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Thabane) is granted sick leave until 27 February when he is due to appear in court for the murder of his former wife. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-lesotho-politics/lesotho-pm-granted-medical-leave-from-wife-murder-case-police-idUSKCN20G0FD)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Dominican Republic municipal elections](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Dominican_Republic_municipal_elections)\n    *   The [Dominican Republic government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politics_of_the_Dominican_Republic) wants the [Organization of American States](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization_of_American_States) to investigate what occurred in the controversial February 16 elections. [(Dominican Today)](https://dominicantoday.com/dr/local/2020/02/21/dominican-govt-wants-oas-probe-into-elections-fiasco/)\n*   [2020 Togolese presidential election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Togolese_presidential_election)\n    *   Voters in [Togo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Togo) head to the polls to elect the country''s [president](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_presidents_of_Togo). Incumbent president [Faure Gnassingb](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faure_Gnassingb%C3%A9), accused of an authoritarian rule, seeks to run for a fourth term which was made possible by a constitutional amendment in 2019. [(DW)](https://www.dw.com/en/togo-goes-to-the-polls-as-ruling-family-seeks-sixth-decade-in-power/a-52474650)\n*   [2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Democratic_Party_presidential_primaries)\n    *   [Senator](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Senate) [Bernie Sanders](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bernie_Sanders) wins the [Nevada Caucus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Nevada_Democratic_caucuses). [(CNN)](https://www.cnn.com/politics/live-news/nevada-caucuses-live-results-updates-2020/index.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_22','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3372,replace('# 2020-02-23\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [Israel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel) kills two members of [Islamic Jihad](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_Jihad_Movement_in_Palestine) in an aerial attack near [Damascus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Damascus), [Syria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria). [(Al Jazeera)](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/israel-claims-air-strikes-syrian-capital-damascus-200223232221593.html)\n\n## Arts and culture\n\n*   The [Carnival of Aalst](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carnival_of_Aalst) in [Belgium](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belgium) goes ahead despite [UNESCO](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UNESCO) withdrawing its recognition of the event as a [Masterpiece of the Oral and Intangible Heritage of Humanity](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masterpieces_of_the_Oral_and_Intangible_Heritage_of_Humanity) because of [Jewish caricatures](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stereotypes_of_Jews). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-belgium-carnival-aalst/belgian-carnival-defies-calls-to-cancel-parade-with-jewish-caricatures-idUSKCN20H0ND) [(newsmonkey)](https://newsmonkey.be/aalst-carnaval-gaat-door-ondanks-stormweer-internationale-media-kijken-met-argusogen-wegens-antisemitische-praalwagen-van-vorig-jaar/)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [2020 IranTurkey earthquakes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Iran%E2%80%93Turkey_earthquakes)\n    *   An [earthquake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earthquake) in [West Azerbaijan Province](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Azerbaijan_Province), [Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran), kills at least nine people and injures more than a hundred others. [(Daily Sabah)](https://www.dailysabah.com/turkey/2020/02/23/8-dead-after-magnitude-57-quake-jolts-turkey-iran-border)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Italy)\n        *   Seventy-six more coronavirus cases are confirmed in [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy), bringing the number of the cases in the country to 155. [(La Repubblica)](https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/23/news/coronavirus_italia-249329434/)\n        *   A 68-year-old woman dies of coronavirus in [Crema](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crema,_Lombardy), Italy, bringing the number of deaths in the country to three. [(Tgcom24)](https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/lombardia/coronavirus-aumentano-i-contagi-il-norditalia-si-blinda-divieto-di-ingresso-e-allontanamento_15195468-202002a.shtml)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in South Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_South_Korea)\n        *   [South Korea](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea) confirms that 169 more people have contracted the coronavirus in the country, raising the total number to 602. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51603251)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Iran)\n        *   [Pakistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan) has closed [its border](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran-Pakistan_border) from [Taftan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taftan) with Iran due to increasing cases of coronavirus in Iran. [(Geo News)](https://www.geo.tv/latest/273901-pakistan-seals-taftan)\n        *   [Turkey](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkey) has closed its border with Iran and halted incoming flights due to more cases of coronavirus in Iran. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-turkey/turkey-shuts-iran-border-halts-flights-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKCN20H0GH)\n        *   [Afghanistan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghanistan) suspended travel between it and Iran and reported three suspected virus cases in [Herat](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herat). [(TRT World)](https://www.trtworld.com/middle-east/turkey-pakistan-shut-iran-border-afghanistan-bans-travel-over-virus-fears-34039)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Comorian legislative election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Comorian_legislative_election)\n    *   The second round of the latest election in [Comoros](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comoros) takes place. The election is still boycotted by the political opposition. [(RFI)](http://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique/20200222-comores-elections-legislatives-second-tour)\n*   [2020 Dominican Republic municipal elections](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Dominican_Republic_municipal_elections)\n    *   Protests begin in [New York](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_(state)) and [Massachusetts](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massachusetts) in the United States, [Paris](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris) in France, [Toronto](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toronto) in Canada, [Madrid](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madrid), [Navarre](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Navarre), and [Barcelona](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barcelona) in Spain, [San Juan, Puerto Rico](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Juan,_Puerto_Rico), and [London](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London) in England. [(Dominican Today)](https://dominicantoday.com/dr/local/2020/02/23/thousands-of-dominicans-around-the-world-request-resignation-from-the-central-electoral-board/)\n    *   Protestors demand the [Central Electoral Board](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_Electoral_Board) resign. [(Dominican Today)](https://dominicantoday.com/dr/local/2020/02/23/thousands-of-dominicans-around-the-world-request-resignation-from-the-central-electoral-board/)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_February_23','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3375,replace('# 2020-03-06\n\n## Armed conflicts and attacks\n\n*   [2020 Kabul shooting](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Kabul_shooting)\n    *   At least 32 people are killed and 81 are injured when gunmen [attack](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_shooting) a ceremony in [Kabul](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kabul), Afghanistan. Afghan politician [Abdullah Abdullah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdullah_Abdullah) was present and escapes unharmed. [ISIL](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant) claims responsibility for the attack. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-afghanistan-attack/islamic-state-attacks-kabul-gathering-killing-at-least-32-idUSKBN20T0RO)\n*   Two [suicide bombers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicide_bomb) on a motorcycle [detonate](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Detonate) their [explosives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Explosive) near the United States [embassy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embassy) in [Tunis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tunis), [Tunisia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tunisia), killing a policeman and wounding five others. [(Middle East Eye)](https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/suicide-bombing-near-us-embassy-tunis)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [United States tornado outbreak of March 23, 2020](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tornado_outbreak_of_March_2%E2%80%933,_2020)\n    *   [U.S. President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_the_United_States) [Donald Trump](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_Trump) approves a [disaster declaration](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disaster_area) for all areas affected by the [tornadoes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tornado). [(WSMV Nashville)](https://www.wsmv.com/news/president-trump-approves-tennessee-disaster-declaration/article_b8666ad8-5f52-11ea-86b8-87d789a72767.html)\n    *   The [National Weather Service](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Weather_Service) concludes the [EF3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enhanced_Fujita_Scale) tornado that went through [Davidson](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Davidson_County,_Tennessee), [Wilson](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wilson_County,_Tennessee), and [Smith](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smith_County,_Tennessee) counties was confirmed on the ground for 60.13 miles (96.77km), becoming the second longest path a tornado has taken in Tennessee. [(NWS)](https://www.weather.gov/ohx/20200303)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Asia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Asia)\n    *   [Bhutan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhutan) confirms its first [coronavirus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronavirus_disease_2019) case. [(Hindustan Times)](https://www.hindustantimes.com/world-news/bhutan-confirms-first-coronavirus-case/story-PcSzXGtlS7knArQeDdJLKP.html)\n*   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Europe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Europe)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Serbia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Serbia)\n        *   [Serbia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serbia) reports its first case. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-healthcare-coronavirus-serbia-idUSKBN20T152)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Vatican City](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Vatican_City)\n        *   The [Vatican City](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vatican_City) reports its first case. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-vatican/vatican-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-in-vatican-city-idUSKBN20T13O)\n\n## Law and crime\n\n*   The [Committee on the Rights of the Child](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Committee_on_the_Rights_of_the_Child) of the [United Nations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations) condemns the [government of the Cook Islands](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_the_Cook_Islands) for criminalizing [homosexual sex](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gay_sexual_practices). [(RNZ)](https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/411138/un-committee-grills-cooks-govt-over-same-sex-treatment)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Guyanese general election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Guyanese_general_election)\n    *   Police in [Georgetown](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Georgetown,_Guyana), [Guyana](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guyana), surround the nation''s election commission after there are accusations that the elections results were altered to help incumbent President [David A. Granger](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_A._Granger) win the election. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-guyana-election/guyana-police-surround-elections-council-amid-dispute-over-vote-results-idUSKBN20T23T?il=0)\n\n## Science and technology\n\n*   [SpaceX CRS-20](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SpaceX_CRS-20)\n    *   [SpaceX](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SpaceX) successfully launches a [Dragon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SpaceX_Dragon) spacecraft in orbit to resupply the International Space Station. This marks the last launch of a Dragon spacecraft, soon to be replaced by [Dragon 2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragon_2), and the 50th successful recovery of a [Falcon 9](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Falcon_9) first stage booster. [(Space.com)](https://www.space.com/spacex-launches-cargo-international-space-station.html)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_March_6','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3380,replace('# 2020-03-07\n\n## Business and economy\n\n*   [Lebanon](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebanon) says it will [default](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Default_(finance)) on a [Eurobond](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eurobond_(external_bond)) repayment and pursue restructuring its debt. The country has never before defaulted. Lebanon''s [government](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Lebanon) debt is about 170% of its yearly [gross domestic product](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gross_domestic_product). [(_The Guardian_)](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/07/lebanon-to-default-on-debt-for-first-time-amid-financial-crisis)\n\n## Disasters and accidents\n\n*   [Collapse of Xinjia Express Hotel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collapse_of_Xinjia_Express_Hotel)\n    *   A hotel being used for [quarantining](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quarantining) those with coronavirus [collapses](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Building_collapse) in [Quanzhou](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quanzhou), China. Ten people were killed and twenty-three are trapped. Thirty-eight have been rescued alive. [(CNN)](https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/07/china/china-coronavirus-hotel-collapse/index.html)\n*   Twenty-two people are killed and more than 70 are injured when a [tank truck](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tank_truck), two buses and another vehicle [collide](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiple-vehicle_collision) in the road between [Damascus](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Damascus) and [Homs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homs), in [Syria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syria). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-syria-crash/road-crash-in-syria-kills-22-injures-70-state-media-idUSKBN20U0V7?il=0)\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Europe](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Europe)\n        *   [Malta](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malta) reports its first case of coronavirus. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-malta/italian-girl-becomes-maltas-first-coronavirus-case-idUSKBN20U0GK?il=0)\n        *   [Bulgaria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulgaria) reports its first two cases. [(Darik News)](https://dariknews.bg/novini/bylgariia/koronavirus-v-bylgariia-dvama-s-polozhitelni-probi-bez-da-sa-pytuvali-v-chuzhbina-2215559)\n        *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Italy)\n            *   [Nicola Zingaretti](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicola_Zingaretti), the [President of Lazio](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Lazio) since 2013 and [Secretary](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Secretaries_of_the_Democratic_Party_(Italy)) of the [Democratic Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Party_(Italy)) since 2019, confirmed that he has contracted the virus. [(La Repubblica)](https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2020/03/07/news/coronavirus_zingaretti_positivo_al_test-250519476/)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Asia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Asia)\n        *   The [Maldives](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maldives) report its first two confirmed cases of the new coronavirus. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-maldives/maldives-confirms-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus-idUSKBN20U0QP)\n        *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Iran](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Iran)\n            *   Newly elected member of [parliament](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_Consultative_Assembly) [Fatemeh Rahbar](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatemeh_Rahbar) dies after contracting [COVID-19](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronavirus_disease_2019). [(Straits Times)](https://www.nst.com.my/world/world/2020/03/572595/another-iranian-mp-dies-covid-19)\n        *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Japan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Japan)\n            *   A 50-year-old man is arrested for breaching quarantine and travelling to two crowded bars in [Gamagri](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gamag%C5%8Dri) after testing positive for the coronavirus the day prior. He reportedly told family members he intended to spread it and bragged to bar employees that he had tested positive. [(Tokyo Reporter)](https://www.tokyoreporter.com/japan/aichi-man-infected-with-coronavirus-goes-to-bars-to-spread-it/)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in South America](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_outbreak_by_country_and_territory#South_America)\n        *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Argentina](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Argentina)\n            *   The Ministry of Health of Argentina confirmed the country''s first death due to coronavirus, a 64-year-old man who had travelled to Paris who also had other health conditions. This marks the first death due to coronavirus in [Latin America](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_America). [(_Infobae_ in Spanish)](https://www.infobae.com/sociedad/2020/03/07/confirman-la-primera-muerte-por-coronavirus-en-argentina/)\n        *   [Paraguay](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paraguay) reports its first case of coronavirus. [(_Infobae_ in Spanish)](https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2020/03/07/paraguay-confirma-primer-caso-de-coronavirus/)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2019 Afghan presidential election](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Afghan_presidential_election)\n    *   A spokesman for politician [Abdullah Abdullah](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdullah_Abdullah) announces he will hold a parallel presidential inauguration ceremony next week after he declares himself the winner of the election. Incumbent [President](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Afghanistan) [Ashraf Ghani](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashraf_Ghani) was declared the winner. [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-afghanistan-politics/afghan-political-rivals-issue-parallel-invites-for-inauguration-ceremonies-idUSKBN20U0WA?il=0)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_March_7','\n',char(10)));
REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3386,replace('# 2020-03-08\n\n## Health and environment\n\n*   [201920 coronavirus outbreak](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_coronavirus_outbreak)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Canada](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Canada)\n        *   The first virus-related death is confirmed in [Canada](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada). [(_CBC News_)](https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/covid-19-coronavirus-update-bc-march-9-1.5483932)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Albania](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Albania)\n        *   [Albania](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albania) reports [its first case](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Albania). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-albania/albania-confirms-first-coronavirus-cases-in-father-and-son-back-from-italy-idUSKBN20W012)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Moldova](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Moldova)\n        *   [Moldova](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moldova) reports [its first case](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Moldova). [(Reuters)](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-moldova/moldova-reports-first-coronavirus-case-idUSKBN20V08U)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Italy), [2020 Northern Italy coronavirus lockdowns](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Northern_Italy_coronavirus_lockdowns)\n        *   [Italian Prime Minister](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italian_Prime_Minister) [Giuseppe Conte](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giuseppe_Conte) extends the [quarantine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quarantine) lockdown, to cover all the [region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regions_of_Italy) of [Lombardy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lombardy) and 14 other [northern](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northern_Italy) [provinces](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Provinces_of_Italy), affecting over a quarter of the national population. [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238)\n        *   The number of virus-related deaths in [Italy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Italy) rise to 366, while the confirmed cases are 7,375. [(Sky Tg24)](https://tg24.sky.it/cronaca/2020/03/08/coronavirus-italia-news-diretta.html)\n        *   Inmates at several prisons in Italy revolt with reports of riots at [prisons](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prison) in [Modena](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modena), [Foggia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foggia), [Naples](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naples), [Frosinone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frosinone) and [Alessandria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alessandria) due to fears the coronavirus lockdowns will end visits from relatives. At least eight inmates, six in Modena, have died of [overdose](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Overdose) after assaulting the prison''s pharmacy, while about 20 escaped in Foggia. [(Open)](https://www.open.online/2020/03/09/coronavirus-rivolta-in-un-carcere-di-modena-morto-un-detenuto/)\n        *   [Chief of Staff of the Italian Army](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chief_of_Staff_of_the_Italian_Army) [Salvatore Farina](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salvatore_Farina_(soldier)) tested positive for coronavirus and self-isolates, as well as [President of Piedmont](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Piedmont) [Alberto Cirio](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alberto_Cirio). [(BBC)](https://www.bbc.com/news/live/world-europe-51789355/page/2)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Portugal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Portugal)\n        *   [President of Portugal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/President_of_Portugal) [Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marcelo_Rebelo_de_Sousa) self-isolates after a coronavirus case is confirmed in a school he visited a few days ago. [(US News)](https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2020-03-08/portugals-president-self-isolates-amid-virus-outbreak)\n    *   [2020 coronavirus outbreak in Russia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_outbreak_in_Russia)\n        *   3 new cases registered in [Russia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia) (one is in [Kaliningrad Region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kaliningrad_Region), one is in [Belgorod Region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belgorod_Region), one is in [Moscow Region](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moscow_Region)). All of them visited Italy within the past 14 days. [(Sputnik)](https://sputniknews.com/russia/202003081078511973-three-new-covid-19-cases-registered-in-russia/)\n        *   Twenty-seven people have died from methanol poisoning in Iran after rumours that drinking alcohol can help cure the coronavirus infection, state news agency IRNA reported on Monday. [(BOL News)](https://www.bolnews.com/international/2020/03/bootleg-booze-kills-27-in-iran-after-coronavirus-cure-rumours/)\n\n## Politics and elections\n\n*   [2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_Democratic_Party_presidential_primaries)\n    *   [California](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California) [U.S. Senator](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Senator) and former presidential candidate [Kamala Harris](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kamala_Harris) endorses former Vice President [Joe Biden](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Biden) in [his campaign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Biden_2020_presidential_campaign) for the Democratic nomination for the presidency. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/us/politics/kamala-harris-endorses-joe-biden.html)\n    *   Civil rights activist [Jesse Jackson](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jesse_Jackson) endorses [Vermont](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vermont) U.S. Senator [Bernie Sanders](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bernie_Sanders) in [his campaign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bernie_Sanders_2020_presidential_campaign) for the Democratic nomination for the presidency. [(_The New York Times_)](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/us/politics/jesse-jackson-bernie-sanders-michigan.html)\n\n## Sports\n\n*   [2020 ICC Women''s T20 World Cup Final](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_ICC_Women%27s_T20_World_Cup_Final)\n    *   [Australia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia_women%27s_national_cricket_team) wins the tournament, beating [India](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India_women%27s_national_cricket_team) by 85 runs, to win their fifth title. [(BBC Sport)](https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/51789306)\n\n---\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Current_events/2020_March_8','\n',char(10)));
