REPLACE INTO posts VALUES(3492,replace('Our county is doing the same. It makes absolutely no sense. The cashier and bagger are touching groceries, which have already been touched multiple times, so I can''t figure out what kind of marginal protection not allowing reusable bags provides. I feel a little guilty bagging for myself because I know there''s a line outside and I want to cooperate with whatever helps keep everyone moving, but the stores aren''t saying "this is unsafe for us". \n\nOne grocery store let me bag my own a few weeks ago but there was clearly still some confusion about the rules. One store is packing things into used boxes, which is definitely an improvement, since those would get recycled anyway, whether they go in my bin or the stores isn''t a big difference. \n\n','\n',char(10)));
